name: Canadian Tire
address: Canadian Tire, 2290 Cambie St, Vancouver, BC V5Z 2T7

detailed_reviews.review_text: Excellent customer service, very friendly and helpful staff! I love the products at this store and some stuff can be surprisingly cheap especially when on sale! I definitely will be planning on going back as there is a wonderful selection of stuff to buy and good staff members there who are helpful!

I enjoy shopping here immensely. Especially around the holidays, very exciting for me. I love how they have everything arranged, very easy to find what you are looking for. I cant wait until Halloween to go shopping for stuff or Christmas time, they always have beautiful displays. I love the lights and just about anything you can think of they have it all. Just beautiful.

This is by far the best spot for anything automobile related. What truly sets this Canadian Tire apart, however, is their commitment to customer satisfaction. The entire team always go above and beyond to answer any questions or concerns and ultimately, to make sure your leave their facility with a smile on your face. The technicians always deliver high-quality work promptly, and their commitment to customer satisfaction is unparalleled. Keep up the great work!

Has to check it out, as it was much more than the name leads you to believe. They have a deep and wide variety of items from  aisles and aisles of camping gear to electronics and upstairs was almost all Christmas decorations.  Very cool store

5 stars for their impressive inventory tracking system. Asked a staff member about a heater in early summer, an off-season product, & the guy looked on his phone & knew exactly what high shelf it was on. Rolled a mechanized elevating machine to the right aisle that lifted him to the top shelf & he found the item in an instant. Website accesses same database & seems to be reliably up to date on what is physically in the store & what has to be ordered from someplace else.

A big thank you to Dustin (manager of the fishing dept) for the assistance over the last few days on my spinning reel. He was able to solve the issue right away on the line and I couldnt be more thankful. Thanks again Dustin for all your hard work.

Great place for all your house hold needs! They usually have some great deals as well. It can be a bit confusing finding things in the aisles as its such a big store but they do have item locator screens around the store. I recommend getting their triangle reward card and MasterCard as you tend to accumulate points faster and able to redeem quicker.

It was a great service with Canadian tire center! We had a nail on one of our rear tire. We went to costco, bigotire and Mr. lube to get opinions. We were told that we had to replace all 4 tires without even checking. But we just replace a brand new front tire a year ago and only drove less than 3000 Km since. Costco was the worst of all! They were so impatience and told us they had to replace all four tires because they had to be the same brands because they did not carry my tires brand. Their attitude was the worst!  Canadian tire was our last store to get opinion on.  Gensis, Nash and Steven were very helpful and Gensis was very patience with us. He explained a lot of things to us and help us understand the situation. After listening to our story, Gensis told us that they would first check if our tire was repairable then offered options if it was not.  Both Costco and Mr. Lube never even bothered to do what Canadian tire did. They just assumed that we had a nail and all our four tires were needed to be replaced. Gensis at Canadian tire is such a nice guy and a great supervisor/manager I assumed. He went an extra mile for the customer and put our best interest first! As a business owner myself, I really think it is hard to find a great employee like Gensis these days.  In the end, it turned out to be that our tire only needed a patch. It only cost us 70 dollar! At Costco, they quoted us for almost $3000 to replace all tires. We will for sure go back to Canadian for future replacement!  We would 100% recommend this Canadian tire center at Cambie.

Great New Battery Warranty Experience...  After sitting for for sometime my 1974 Alfa GTV failed to start.  I lugged (yes - its heavy) my new Optima battery back to Canadian Tire on Cambie for testing and to find it unchargable.  30 minutes later the warranty papers are complete and I walk out with a brand new  battery. I chose to purchase here because of this exact confidence in the warranty system.  A 1965 Mini Cooper Woody owner was right behind me with the same issue. Great company, with car guys that love the older stuff, wanted to see pictures etc...
The only thing I didnt like about this location was the security gaurd. He regularly harassed people trying to leave, but hes been gone for at least a couple months, so, I have no complaints.
Had no trouble find a helpful staff to point out exactly what we needed. Parking is a breeze because of proximity to elevators and checkout.

I went in for a quick stop to purchase a Piler, I was pretty confused on which one to get and the staff member there was very helpful and knowledgeable and was able to help me find the one that I need. Great service

This review is for Booth in the auto dept. I came in about 30 mins before close because I had to get my car towed to the nearest auto shop. While the service department was already closed, Booth stopped what he was doing to immediately make sure the store would have my contact info and licence plate number. He took down all my details and told me to call him if I needed anything at all.  As someone who worked for two separate Canadian tires for about 3 years, Booth I appreciate you. Customer coming in frantically 30 mins before close? Likely underpaid/undervalued, and definitely overworked? Its tough, Ive been there but man did you make an already annoying situation for me just a little bit better. Thank you sir!
very convenient location! Just FYI they check your receipt at the door, like at Costco...I never expect this and always end up spending an embarrassing amount of time trying to fish out my receipt
I took my partners Jeep Wrangler in today for a minor issue and got incredible service. Super great communication and extremely fair prices. The intake person deserves a raise.

Thanks Canadian Tire for another great deal with our employees its was great meeting with the same people specially when we talk nice groups I love see that team again we have a lovely day!! - ALMASRI,0011

The best thing about this Canadian Tire is the camping scene with nature sounds as you go up the escalator to the second floor. Thats the only kind of camping I can get behind. This store is huge and had what I needed and Im sure what you need. Hate all the self checkouts though. Wish that wasnt a thing.
Thank you    Canadian tire . For the friendly , fast service  also reasonable prices . I usually always get everything I had on my list .

The selection of goodies is enough to overwhelm anyone, not that its a bad thing, I mean they have literally everything. Easy self checkout, even though I miss interacting with actual people but technology right? Also they have something to suit any budget, and I have never returned anything to Canadian Tire so kudos to them for that.

One of my favorite stores ever. No matter what you are looking for you can find it in Canadian Tire, sports, plumbing,  electrical,  consumables, gardening, house decorating, car features and maintenance, school, stools, tables, fireplaces! I bought mine there for black Friday and was a super good deal.
Had a great experience with  Booth  from the auto section. He was very kind, helpful and had a wealth of knowledge. Thanks again for all your help Booth!

I bought a cheap air conditioning and it turns out that its absolutely fabulous. Thank you Canadian Tire The air conditioning for $169.00 is fabulous works better than my old RCA It even has an air purifier in it and it works so great my apartment smells great

Favorite Store in this location! Amazing items ( especially Kitchen household items ). Love the Cat sections selections! Finally a place for more cat choices items. Love it! Great staff! Rosa Cashier was amazing services and friendly.
Good store, had lots of great appliances and tools, would come back again
A pretty good selection of outdoor . gear(camping,fishing,airsoft)
The staff at Canadian Tire Cambie street were extremely knowledgeable, helpful and kind. They made my experience great and efficient when I was very time pressured.
More than 100 aisles of stuff. Can cater to all your needs - tire to attire, from hair to toe. Whenever youre lost, ask a staff. They pull out a palmtop & are never wrong about their suggestions.
Purchased three DOT approved full face VCAN Rival helmets c/w visors for snowmobile and atv use. Good customer service at the Cambie @ 7th location in Vancouver.

I saw online that there was one remaining in store. I got there and ask the fellow if he could help me locate it. There was no more on shelf so he checked in warehouse and I got the last one...thanks for your over and above assistance...made me feel so happy as its gonna be a hot one this week
They have everything. Lots of sales. Located near the Canada Line subway.
The gentleman at the car service was very friendly with me and patient with a new employee being trained. I grabbed the parts I needed and I was in and out!
Great service as always! Check in is quick with online booking. Great team as well, handled my little Sypder very carefully. Thanks!
Recently we bought a bicycle. The staff were so pacient and helpful. I really appreciat them.
Garden staff were super helpful! Wide variety of plants and were able to provide some tips and tricks
Convenient location. So much selection like an old fashioned department store.

Great store!.  Clean, well organized and with PEOPLE! to whom you can ask questions and they are very polite.  Free parking as it gets refunded (if you purchase something) before you leave the store. One word: CIVILIZED!
Great experience with curbside pick up! Highly recommended! Ill definitely use this service more often.
a cactus that changes lives I keep it with me in my coat perfect for late night drives remember to take it with you on the boat
Its huge.  Lots of products.   Never had an issue with a return.
The place is really clean and organized. The attention is good and prices are accesibles. I love that you can get in with your pet.

This is a great store! Theyre busy changing things around right now and I couldnt find something I wanted, and the staff were so helpful and friendly. The garden centre Up on the Roof looks fairly decent and the prices werent that bad. My main thing to be grateful for was the vast amount of non LED lighting that they are still carrying at a reasonable price.

Very busy location. i had to call the store from inside the store to help me cut a key. Once I found someone, they were fast, efficient and extremely helpful. I loved their positive attitude, even though it was crazy busy. This shows professionalism. Please note: pay parking only

Very helpful staff member helped me get the correct battery for my car.  Also reminded me to return my old battery for a $20 core refund.  I ll be sure to return to this location. Also, their car battery price for my Jaguar was cheaper than anywhere else, even cheaper than Costco.

We had an amazing experience today at Canadian Tire Broadway! Our whole Christmas vacation was saved. After getting 2 tires slashed, and spending hours trying to get it sorted, staff member Genesis was extremely empathetic and showed real kindness. Great job Genesis and thank you !!! :)
One stop shop for a variety of products . Totally dependable and affordable products . My go to for sports good, hiking, kitchen goods,.......

This was my first time. Loved the  discounts, please be sure of what you want to buy before visiting. You can note down the product and aisle no in their app. Saves a lot of time. I would definitely recommend this store.

Old comment: Bought my snow tires here, then still charged me $300 for changing snow tires (put on rims and installation).   A friend working in Midas told me they charge $170 for the same service. Well, guess I should not trust this big brand at the first place. Won t go back again. (1 star review) New comment: Johnny who the manager made a reasonable explanation, so I am all good.  (Changed to 5 stars)
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Colin, We suspect there may either be an error, or misunderstanding on your installation costs. When purchasing new tires from us, the install cost will range from $150 to $200 +tax,  depending on size. This seems to be in line with the cost mentioned at Midas. Please feel free to reach out to me so I can look into your recent visit with us. Thank you kindly! Johnny Ray Ritchie Operations Manager Automotive Service Center 604-707-2291

detailed_reviews.review_text: They had a washroom and the product I was looking for at what resembled market price.

Great customer service from the Automotive Service Department! Very polite and understanding, given I have been driving 12 hours straight. Gentleman named Genesis was very accomodating too(I parked my car in the 2nd floor parking area and he had someone move the car to the right area)and friendly. Overall a great experience
Hate shopping,but could be here for hrs... The one just over the Pitt bridge is 5x better
We found everything
Im always happy to bring my car in to this location. Even once when there was an issue they addressed it and fixed it right away!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Catherine, Thank you so much for the positive feedback on our shop! Your kindness is much appreciated and we value your business here. If you ever need anything more, please do not hesitate to reach out to me or my staff! Have a great weekend! Johnny Ray Ritchie Operations Manager 604-707-2291

detailed_reviews.review_text: Incredibly helpful and friendly staff here. They really go out of their way to assist customers and make sure you are taken care of. Great experience each time!
IA super costumer service by Jack in bike service . Was wonderful thank you so much

boxing week of course it was a great deal, this is a good store for deals if you are patient. It doesnt hurt to have manners too, kindness, temperance, self-control. These are all required virtues if you want to shop in this store.
This store got everything from spice containers to car tools, adapters, plush toys, Halloween decorations, cooking ware, electronics but price is bit higher as compared to other stores.

This is the place. Not going anywhere but here to find detergent and other good deals. They also have a inclined escalator. Crazy stuff. Feel like I should apply just so I can keep tabs on gnar deals.

Been going to the Cambie location for Canadian tires for multiple years, and they do such an incredible job. My go to place if I need camping equipment or purchasing storage containers for my belongings. The staff is friendly and very accommodating.
Right before the heat wave hit I was able to get two ac units here when everywhere else was sold out.
Staff are always willing to help find the items that are needed. The store has a great layout and is very well stocked.

The Auto Center here has a really sound team- Communication between each other is top notch. Sal and his colleagues are very patient and incredibly friendly. I dropped my car off to get new tires and the turn around time was super fast. Highly recommend going here for your tire needs.
A1 auto shop that spotted a junk car I bought from a dodgy dealer and helped me get a full refund. Alex is the best, totally calm throughout, helped me with the process and saved me a lot of cash
Very good variety under one roof

Really enjoy the customer service here. Brought my dog to the store and was treated like a star. No issues whatsoever especially with the ongoing societal scamdemic policies in place that is ubiquitous. If youre looking for an item and need to help, customer service is friendly and available to assist you. They genuinely enjoy their jobs unlike other CT locations (Surrey) where bathroom availability and customer service is non-existent.
One stop shop for all your household needs.  They have very good COVID protocols in place.
The manager in fishing/outdoor is absolutely awesome. I walk in needing a complete fishing set up on 2 different occasions. He asked a few questions and built my set ups.

Huge selection of all sorts of outdoor stuff, automotive and housewares.  Very competitive sales and fun gizmos. This location was very busy because of the Christmas rush and they had loads of easy to find staff that knew where things were. Saved me lots of time and saved my Xmas since they were the only place in town that still had real cut Christmas trees available. They were blowing them out by the time I got there so I got a beautiful $99 tree for $30. The universe loves me :) The Canadian Tire money promos also save me lots of money. I like that I get points at Sportchek and Atmosphere that I can spend here. Excellent value. Ill be back

This is a large Canadian Tire and I have to say that I have received some of the best customer service at this specific location. Each staff member I have dealt with was extremely helpful and friendly. During one of my visits I was doing a self check out and to my surprise one of the staff created a handle for my bag because I had an awkward and oversized item. It was so thoughtful. A positive customer experience can make or break a shopping trip and I go out of my way to shop here because of the phenomenal service. Keep up the great work!! ***IF YOU FOUND THIS REVIEW HELPFUL KINDLY  LIKE  IT***
Always a pleasure  to shop at Canada Tire. Except  crippy Cambie  location with  pay parking on top  of it S hitt hole.

This review is for the automotive garage only - I do not have any experience shopping here otherwise. I had quite the experience here over the past month, which started from me trying to simply get my seasonal tire change done. A lot went wrong, but, each time, the service advisors were extremely helpful in explaining why and how, and doing their best to make it right. Which they did. Due strictly to their fantastic service (specifically, Laura and Daniel, A+), this shop gets a no-questions 5/5. Good customer service is the single most important aspect of a successful business, in my opinion, and here it was knocked out of the park. If things go wrong and time is lost to visits where nothing gets done, a good service advisor can make all the difference. When the job finally got done, it got done right, so no issues there. It ended up with me buying a new set of tires and the aligning/balancing that goes with that. The tires are on, the wheels are aligned and balanced, and nothing feels off.

It is centrally located and yet, they have a very big inventory and space. They even have plastic kayaks on stock, when other Canadian Tire locations dont. Awesome, beautiful, clean store. Their credit card is of all my cards, my favourite!
Had good experience in canadian tire. Staff was helpful all the time.

Any Concerns or product inquiries go ASK FOR BROCK. Superior Excellence in Customer Satisfaction n Experience. Just ask for Him. Fantastic Listener n has Solutions for all your Needs. Superior Friendly and easy to talk to. Many Thanks Brock for your Kindness and Helpfulness on the Spot.

Staff were friendly and had approachable attitudes. Got there at the last minutes before closing, but rather than bother my unsure choice of products, they were patient enough to let me make my decisions and pay for them at the till!

Everything i need. I realy like this canadian tire because the staff has allways been good and the big security gaurd at exit watchs my bike for me  well i shop. I would say thats cool to do that he lets me bring it in and put it beside him and he is a very nice guy. I wanted to give him a tip but he said he is not allowed to except tips so he is very kind. Keep up the good work. I like to see people around that treat me like a human being and the staff at this canadian tire all have been very good to me. Thank you
Customer service desk always super friendly and efficient!!
Helped my to exchange my old battery. Nice people!

Brought my car into the service centre to replace my tires. Had an overall great experience with their service advisor Alex. Ended up doing a whole bunch of work done to my car because my interaction was so pleasant. Will definitely come back. BTW their tire warranty is a great deal would recommend to everyone who suffer from random nails and debris always getting in their tires

Very convenient location, staff are helpful and knowledgeable even if you asked items out of their department theyll tell you where to find items. So people please ask and be nice to staff because theyre working really hard!

This has got to be one of the easiest stores to find things you need.  Last year I got my Christmas decorations from here and my tree still looks amazing this year!  Also, I always spend too much time in their housewares department, they have all of the great kitchen stuff at great prices and wonderful sales.  Their staff are very helpful and its such a nice clean store with great hours to shop at!  In addition, they are excellent community partners, and have participated in community events! THANK YOU!!!

Gee! Such a huge store that took me sometime to find what I intend to buy.  On the other hand, was happy to buy the flowering plants I have seen for the first time  in my life, so unique and colorful! Beautiful plants!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Melodina, were happy to hear you found everything you needed. Come back soon! Corporate Customer Experience Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: I recommend the bike shop here and kudo to Bahsa who is bike shop manager. He is very kind and also professional! I bought my bike a few days ago and he gave me a great service. I am very satisified with him. I also visited the bike shop in Richmond but this place has more bikes too.
The only place I could find reasonabke priced tire for my car

I always enjoy going to Canadian Tire. Even though the store is large it has a good use of floor space. They have everything you could possibly want for your home and automotive needs. They are usually well stocked and they do give out raincheques when they have to. The staff are helpful and friendly and make my visit pleasant. I highly recommend this business.
Great customer service and great price for everything!

What do you know about Canadian Tire. It has a lot of stuff. And good prices, quality varies, but you know what youre getting into.  I found what I wanted on line, went to the store, found it and got out of there.  So, its efficient now to shop there as the online version tells you which store has what or if it is in stock.  If you want to wander, theres plenty to see ... And this Canadian tire has auto repair shop, crazy expensive parking in the area. I parked 2 blocks away and walked there. They have good plant sales in the summer, too.

I called this afternoon with an urgent issue and Genesis was able to fit me in with Robbie, the shop foreman. He was able to diagnose and repair the issue last minute. Im so grateful for the help, absolutely above and beyond service at this location.   Thank you guys so much for helping me out, I appreciate it more than you could know.  Anxiety attack avoided!   Thank you so much!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Elicia! We thank you so much for your kind words and positive review! However youve left your review on the retail side of our business. If you wouldnt mind taking a minute of your time to transfer your review to our service center, we would very much appreciate the support! You can find the link below. https://g.page/r/CVVGZCa4SxpCEAE Sincerely, Johnny Ray Ritchie Operations Manager Canadian Tire Auto Service 604-707-2291

detailed_reviews.review_text: I really enjoy shopping at Cdn Tire n I usually go to the one nearest to me on Cambie and 7th Ave. Today was one where I had a great experience with one particular staff working in the plants section upstairs. I usually like to look over the discount plant shelf to see if theres anything there that Im care to try to rescue. I ended up picking up two plants (one 5 cm & 10 cm) n the bigger one was almost dried out. I decided to dunk it in a large container nearby that was filled with water n it had a watering can. After I was done n was trying to get out of the closely packed area, a staff member noticed that I picked up some discount plants n complimented me on trying to rescue some of them. After a short conversation, she ended up offering me two of the small 5 cm plants for free as her Xmas gift to me as it was clear that it easily made me happy. Her name was Pat n she said that why not make someone happy if its easy for her to do so n wished me Merry Xmas. I was very pleased with her kindness and wished her the same. TYVM again Pat giving me such a great experience. One more thing, I dont really enjoy being made to use the self check out machines n sincerely wish that theres an option to purchase products from a humin cashier. So many issues come up with using these machines and I dont enjoy the experience. Thats it. Thanks again, Pat!!

No matter which Canadian Tire I go to, I always walk out knowing theres more I want to run back into the store and buy. I stopped by the Cambie store because (1) I happened to be in the area during the boxing week promotions and (2) I saw that this location carried a bunch of items that my local branch was out of. I liked what I saw in the store: good deals & good selection. I dont know if it is my favourite layout but I found my way around.

I went to get helium balloons and party supplies at the Party City pop-up area inside of the Canadian Tire and Jessica was really amazing. She was very friendly and gave me really good tips on how to keep the balloons safe while transporting them. I will definitely come back!

I was looking for a garden hose nozzle and I got one at $7.99. Its the certified metal rear-trigger pistol. It can do some spray painting but Ill try it as is. Reviews on Canadian Tire app says its pretty good compared to more expensive ones including the plastic options. The Canadian Tire employees were very helpful too. I asked three employees for directions since its my first time in this branch and I was wheeling a very cranky taby (toddler baby). If you want to the garden centre, the entrance is the one adjacent to Cambie, not the Cambie one. I repeat not the entrance on Cambie street. Its especially helpful to know this when you also have a stroller or on a wheelchair and going up to  the garden centre. I wanted to buy other things such as veggie seedlings on sale but it was almost impossible with a wailing kid in tow.
Beautiful decoration, good store

Love this store. Huge selection of outdoor / sports equipments, half a floor of gardening, and one full floor of appliances and kitchen necessities. Make sure you take your parking recipt to the cashier for a validation! We did not know they do so for a while.
Alex has best customer service!
Picked up Dog/Coyote Repellent less than $20 tax included, in & out in less than 10 minutes.

Ive been here dozens of times and Ive bought everything from bikes to seeds to screws to kitchen utensils. Staff is helpful and knowledgeable and I see the same faces quite a bit so the turnover must be lower than at other stores, which is encouraging. True you have to pay for parking, but if you buy over $15 worth of goods you get reimbursed. Great selection; I have never failed to find what I came for. Bag policy: free, as needed.

I ve gone here a few times. Got a helmet, a bike and last purchase was a wok. Yesterday I was looking into a coffee machine and a staff member noticed and asked if I needed help. I find staff is attentive and doing the best they can during this situation we re all in.
Great super shop does have every thing you need for you home, gardening and technical activities. Its staff are helpful and their prices are reasonable. It has its own parking place.

I have been (casually) looking for a drill for about 2 years. The other day I bought what I thought was a drill, but wasnt... I just returned it and took a look at the isle with drills, to try to catch what I missed. A Canadian Tire associate named *MAGGIE* came to assist me. Though she didnt laugh at me (thank you), she did give me a ton of - easy to understand - info on drills, and even took the time to go over pricing with me, even after I said I wasnt going to buy today. You folks have a blazing gold star with this associate, please give her all the kudos/stars/BONUSES/prize. Maggie is the reason I will get this item from Canadian Tire (instead of Amazon or Wal-Mart). Thanks again!!!
Ample parking.  Friendly service.

name: Canadian Tire
address: Canadian Tire, 2830 Bentall St, Vancouver, BC V5M 4H4

detailed_reviews.review_text: I have to give a shout out to the parts department. The person working there had excellent mechanical knowledge of cars and had great customer service, I had a no start issue with my truck and it turn out his suggestion about the starter coils was correct. Especially since my Dodge dealership failed to understand the issue and find the fault. Also want to commend him for his patience with the number of customers requiring his help.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the fantastic 5-star review! Were thrilled to hear about your positive experience with our parts department. Its great to know that our staff provided excellent mechanical knowledge and outstanding customer service. Were glad they were able to correctly diagnose and resolve the issue with your truck, especially when your Dodge dealership couldnt. Well make sure to pass along your compliments and commendation for their patience. Were here to help, and your satisfaction is important to us. We look forward to serving you again in the future! CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: The Garden Center at Canadian Tire this Year is Superb.  Better Prices and WAY more selection and variety than the Lowes and Home Depot close by. A shame Canadian Tire is associating itself with the Retail Failure London Drugs in a shared Flyer.  Makes me not look at it and throw it out.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your fantastic review! Were delighted to hear that you had an excellent experience at our Garden Center. Providing a wide selection and variety of products at competitive prices is something we take pride in. Your satisfaction is our priority, and were thrilled to know that we surpassed the offerings of other nearby stores. We appreciate your support and look forward to being your top choice for all your gardening needs. If theres anything else we can do to enhance your experience, please let us know. Nice photos... Happy gardening!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Very often you can get discounts on wheels in this store.Also, you don t have to wait long, you can register for literally the next day.The staff was polite and courteous.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind words! Were delighted to hear you had a great experience with us. Providing discounts and prompt service is our priority, and were pleased you noticed our polite and courteous staff. We look forward to serving you again soon! CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Awesome customer service and the supervisor at the key replacement booth saved my butt. They were able to duplicate 5 different keys (mailbox, pad locks, drawers) that the minutekey machine couldnt.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Were thrilled to hear about your positive experience! Our team takes pride in assisting customers like you, and were glad we could help with your various key replacements. Thank you for your 5-star review, and we look forward to assisting you again in the future if needed. CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Went shopping the day before the so-called  Black Friday sale not expecting anything but average pricing. Was absolutely thrilled to have spent no more than my budget could afford and managed to buy the name brand products I intended to purchase at amazingly low discount pre-sale prices. I saved enough to complete my project and then some. Staff encountered were available, friendly and helpful answering the questions I had for them. No hassle check-out and I was out the door for curb side pick up.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Doug! We really appreciate the 5-stars and look forward to seeing you the next time you visit. CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Bill Clarke Service advisor @ Granview Hwys location was able to source parts on Easter Monday , after carefully diagnosing Battery-Alternator was the issue .we had a Game plan & an exact price .The Team including  Nathan were all pros and the car was  back by suppertime. EXCELLENCE on a Holiday Weekend That deserves a GOOD Review !
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for sharing your outstanding experience with us and leaving a glowing review! We are thrilled to hear that Bill Clarke went above and beyond to source parts for your vehicle on Easter Monday and carefully diagnosed the issue with your battery and alternator. We are proud to have a team of professionals, like Bill and Nathan, who provided you with excellent service and worked efficiently to have your car repaired and back to you by suppertime. We appreciate your recognition of our teams commitment to providing exceptional service. Thank you for taking the time to share your experience! CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Every time Im here its always a wonderful shopping experience. Love all the products they sell, especially the heater in the pictures. I own multiple units of this model. (Works well) They sell lots of great brands known as: Honeywell Mastercraft Noma. Quality of their products are great. (Their stuff is better than Walmart) Good prices! Excellent customer service! Convenient Location! What more can you ask for...PERFECT!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks, Ray! We really appreciate the 5 stars and look forward to seeing you the next time you visit. Nice photos! CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: A big, busy store but when I connected with an employee the service was earnest and helpful. The garden center is good. Always a seasonal section of deals. And you can shop with your dog! Bonus Points!

I tell a young man I need help because of my damaged gift card. He says I will help you. He is fun and friendly, and BOOM everything is taken care of. I just had one part of the entire purchase that was a bit weird. The product is working fine but the no return/refund policy was weird. I initially thought that it would just be on this brand but when I checked, it was present for all AC products, it was not brand specific. I am not sure of the reason of this policy but that was the case when I visited this outlet. I do believe that any issues we can address with the brand itself.

detailed_reviews.review_text: I wouldn t ever expect to give a Canadian Tire a 5 star review, but I had such a great experience at this location I thought I better share this positive feedback. As my family was preparing to leave for a camping trip early the next morning, we discovered our roof box was broken beyond repair, and since we don t camp light, getting a replacement was crucial. Canadian Tire s website showed a few models in stock, so a friend and I went down to check them out and buy one. It was about an hour before store closing, and I was feeling a bit stressed to be having to buy something without knowing much about the different brands and options. The automotive manager, Kyle, was happy to help, knew the products well, and had lots of good advice on things I wouldn t have thought to consider had he not suggested them. He even helped us get the roofbox installed on my car, and was cheerful and chill the whole time. I left the store confident with the purchase I had made and was so impressed by the quality of customer service.

Amazing customer service over the phone with Ward! I called in ahead of time to make sure they had an item because I had a terrible experience at another Canadian Tire location. You could hear that it was busy but Ward went out of his way to provide exceptional customer service. He asked for the item number and had support to make sure the item was available. He confirmed it was and told me what aisle it was in and the location where it would be in the aisle. I walked in, purchased the item and walked out within 5 minutes. My background to the whole experience below. I wanted to pick up Settlers of Catan and saw there were 7 available at the Cambie & 7th location. I went to the location and it took forever to find someone for support. When I did find someone, they told me it wasn t their department and to find the other rep. I found the other rep and had to chase after him as it felt like he was trying to avoid helping clients. Odd when you are hired to help clients. When I asked him about it he said if they are not on the shelf then it s going to be in a box somewhere as they are redoing their toy section. There were a bunch of boxes around the area but he was not even willing to walk over and look on the shelves or even offer to look into a couple of the boxes of items. He just said he can t help and smirked. I am purchasing this item as a family member of a friend of mine is battling cancer. This was a gift to bring their family together through the battle as I heard it s getting tougher at the moment. I was so angry that no one was willing to help. They were clearly unorganized and understaffed.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Ward sure is amazing and were glad you think so too Jamie. Team Grandview is wishing your friend all the best with their battle against cancer. We hope the family enjoys the new game and it helps bring them closer together during this difficult time. Thanks for sharing your experience! CT Grandview Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Upon arriving in BC to retrieve a truck my son bought on an online auction, then deployed with the US Navy to parts unknown, I (dad) was left to figure out how to get it back to North Carolina in the States. My plan was to fly into YZR, get the truck and be across the border by nightfall. Loooong story short, its been 5 days and dont know when US BPC and Ram of the US will supply needed paperwork and let me cross to begin my cross country journey. Having to live in the truck since this was unexpected to say the least. I spent 2 days going from WM to WM trying to get supplies needed to stay warm in the truck etc (heater core leaked, had to bypass until I get home to my tools). Turns out Canadian Tire not only had EVEYTHING I needed, they had several options and were only 6 minutes from home base! Besides the people of Canada, Canadian Tire will be the only thing I will miss upon returning home. If youre a man (or woman) this is guy heaven! Everything guys shop for, its here. Period, I only wish I had discovered them earlier.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks! We look forward to seeing you again soon. Corporate Customer Experience Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: I have been coming to Canadian Tire at Market Crossing in Burnaby for many years ever since I bought my car. Their garage service is excellent and I have never had the feeling that they were trying to sell me anything that I didnt need. Im quite knowledgable with cars and would know if they were trying. Usually, they have returned my car without any problems found, which underlines their honesty. The staff and mechanics are friendly and funny. They take their time to explain everything and answer any questions you might have. Only once, my car wasnt locked up when I returned to the parking lot. I asked why and noticed that they had a trainee driving it to the parking lot. I havent seen her since. I usually keep an eye out to see when my car is back on the lot and ready for pick-up, because they do not always call you right away when theyre busy, but the time they tell you it requires to fix your car or do the oil change and inspection is usually correct, so you know when to be back. The one thing I would like to suggest is to always apply the handbrake when taking a customers car back to the lot, because I have never seen anyone do that. All of this being said, I would recommend Canadian Tires garage service at Market Crossing any time due to their honesty.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you, Sarah! We love hearing from great customers like you and we hope to see you again very soon. Corporate Customer Experience Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Well, that was refreshing ! A good experience at Canadian Tire - Whod Da Thunk It?! It turns out that June is a very bad time to be looking for a bicycle and, we needed 2, a mans and a ladys. Shops are sold out all over the lower mainland, even several of the Canadian Tire stores were also low on stock. We found a ladys bike we liked at the store in Burnaby South and drove from North Vancouver to have a look. When we got there we were not able to find it (it turns out that it was there; however, it had a yellow tag on it indicating that it was put on layaway). We were disappointed and were about to settle for something else when we happened upon Rod, the manager. We talked some and eventually got around to the point that we were actually looking for an E-Bike but were having trouble finding one for a reasonable price. Rod said that he has a mans and a ladys E-Bike in stoke and before I could say hold the phone he went to the back to bring  out the ladys version. We talked some more when Rod said Ill see what I can do about the price. My wife and I discussed the merits of purchasing an E-Bike from Canadian Tire when Rod came back and quoted an amount which was 30% less than the ticketed price. Wow, that is a good deal. We will buy both of them! I said. As it turned out, the mans bike had a couple of issues which I noticed later: 1) it didnt have a rear rat trap and 2) the motor would not engage when I peddled. After fiddle farting around with the electronics , I discovered that the crank sensor was mounted on the wrong side of the crank assembly. On the working ladys bike , the sensor was on the left hand side of the crank assembly. On the mens bike , the sensor was on the right side. I decided not to try to fix this and simply return this to another Canadian Tire store which had these bikes in store for an exchange. The South Burnaby store was sold out. Great price and happy ending.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks, Felix! We appreciate the 5-star review! Corporate Customer Experience Team

detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the 5-star review, Jason! Your feedback is important to us and we are proud that we were able to provide you with great service. See you again soon. Corporate Customer Experience Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: I don t usually write letters like this, but I had to tell you what an exceptional person you have working for you.  I came into your store located at 7200 Market Crossing (Burnaby, BC) to purchase bicycles. Rod Louie was extremely efficient, polite, and helpful.  These are rare qualities.  I was not expecting to have such a pleasant experience, but I did, and now I m left with a very positive impression of your business. Employees like this one are a company s  secret weapon .  These days, employers undervalue the impact their front-line employees make on the bottom line. You ll have my repeat business for as long as my experience remains consistently good   so I suggest doing your best to attract and keep more people like Rod Louie And I will definitely spread the word, both verbally and through social media. Let me know if you need help installing this bike rack on your car, I would be happy to step out and assist you    Rod Louie ( Now that s going above and beyond my expectations  JUST WOW, I don t think I ve ever encountered such great customer service.) Very truly yours, Sameer V

I didnt get the ladys name at the register. It was 9am Feb 9/18. Pleasant and friendly service, a good interaction. Please hire more of these individuals because the competition is. Also pay them more!!!!
What can I say I love em
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for sharing your positive feedback! Were glad that you enjoy our store and we cant wait to have you back! Corporate Customer Experience Team

name: Canadian Tire
address: Canadian Tire, 8277 Ontario St, Vancouver, BC V5X 0A7

detailed_reviews.review_text: This location of Canadian Tire is one of the best location and free parking. They are located independently along with other brand names like Sports Check, Best Buy, Marshals. There is a Starbucks and a LifeLab in the next door. Not to traffic before 3.00 PM. A lot of things in here. Perfect to come and get everything.

I basically found what I wanted on my own. But when I asked for help. Customer service person helped me right away. Very nice...and cashier was great and good to talk to.... but as usual you always end up buy what you didnt go there for. Like this watch for only $9.99!

Automotive Department Store We came by to check out their Black Friday sales event. I came to see the two household appliances that were advertised and scored excellent buys. Brightly lit aisles and well stocked displays. The microwave oven section was half empty but I managed to find a boxed Cuisinart air fryer convention toaster oven in stock as advertised at 50% off along with an additional $50 discount at the checkout! Wow! I also purchased a magic bullet brand personal blender on sale for $29.95. This place is a wonderful store for incredible buys. I come often to purchase specials from their flyers when there are things we need. The staff are helpful and knowledgeable. They publish and distribute a flyer every week or every other week depending on the season. This place is advertised as an automotive store but it has so much more to offer with a great selection of housewares, sporting goods and making your home beautiful. Well worth a visit.

I love their Christmas decor section. All the happy Christmas songs. Very festive arrangement and  free photo booth Inspired me to decorate my house very early. And now my neighbors are doing the same
I am impressed how clean the store and nicely decorated. Their washroom reminds me of my house every time my cleaner visits.
Great  customer service. I like their pots and pans section reasonable prices. Be careful  of  the quality of their producs. A much better choice than  Winners for dishes.

The largest selection of products out of any other Canadian Tire location Ive been to. Its very clean and tidy. As it should be for a newer location. Shopping atmosphere is calm and relaxing as a result of how spacious it is. The merchandising methods deployed also helps. Older gentlemen in auto parts is awesome. Knowledgable, kind and direct.

This location of Canadian Tire is one of the best location compared to what they used to have few decades ago. They are located independently along with other brand names like Sports Check, Best Buy, Marshals. There is a Starbucks and a LifeLab in the next door.

Today,  I went to this store to buy some portable BBQ and TENT for our camping and I was so grateful for RJ who assists me all through out. He was so knowledgable about the products and showed an excellent costumer service. I will definitely shop here again and hopefully RJ will be there when I come back.
I always visit this location. The staff are helpful, and the auto service department is top-notch. I do most of my household shopping here.

HUGE Canadian Tire! Lots of ample parking everywhere and they also have a good selection of live plants at this one but not as good as Cambie. What I really liked about this location is that they have their patio/outdoor furniture setup and on display. This way you can test out the furniture to see if it s what you were envisioning online. The other CTs don t really do this so this one was great for that. One thing though is this one doesn t have any self checkout stations and there was a huge lineup and only one person jumped on to another cashier to help the one cashier for the longest time. I m a fan of self checkouts for this reason.
I like this Canadian Tire location a lot, the staff is always friendly and knowledgeable. Great parking as well as a Starbucks nearby.
Fantastic store , they have everything and better price than Amazon,  see for yourself, plus friendly and professional people ready to help,  by supporting local business you support local economy

Best customer service by Michael. Took ownership to look for a part I was looking for, couldnt find it even in the storage. Offered to help me by calling other store. Thank you Michael for going above and beyond.

Canadian Tire handles auto inspections and RIV inspections with expert precision. Comfortable waiting area and convenient indoor parking spaces. Highly recommend their capable and friendly staff and I ll be coming back for basic auto needs and  guy toys  shopping for sure.

Scosche cell phone magnet holder for the car is extremely good quality. The magnet is much easier and convenient over other products. It s easy to reposition to eye level, and can hold any phone size. After three months of use when the product was super tight in the socket, I had a small issue by pulling the plug out on an angle too fast. Rather than fixing it, I returned it to the store with my triangle card and exchanged it for a new one. They found my receipt by tracking the purchase date. Very satisfied with service and auto accessories!
Had a few questions about my truck Staff were very knowledgeable and were really quick to help me!
Everything required for a house other than groceries,  vegetables and fruits under one roof. Best was gardening material.
I love this place for garden needs all the way to tools and activities for the kids. Tons of varieties for summer fun.
Helpful with choosing car tires. Answered all my questions thoroughly. Their assistance was nice.

One of the largest Canadian Tires I know. Loads of parking. Clean and well stocked. Easy to find where my items were located. If not, there is always help just around the corner. Will recommend especially for car lovers like my self the whole bottom section is for cars.
Helpful and Kind Staff!! Best Car accessories

If you want to get the best service at this Canadian Tire, Connor is the guy you should ask for help. I wanted to change my battery of my car today. I was so lucky to get Connors service. He asked a couple of questions to make sure I did need to change the battery. He even took his time to test the battery for me. When I decided to change the battery, he recommended the reasonable one for me. He also offered me two options to replace it: let their machinists do that for me (charge 68$) or by myself. In order to save the money, I chose to do that by myself.  I asked Connor to lent me the tools and tried it. Unfortunately, it was not as simple as I thought and gave it up, and I turned to the machinists for help, but none of them were available at that moment and asked me to leave my car there and they might replace it tomorrow. I was so disappointed and turned to Connor for help again. By the rule, Connor is not allowed to replace the battery for me, but he still be so nice to stand beside and guide me how to do that properly. With his instructions, I finally replace my battery. To be honest, I bothered Connor so many times today, but he was so patient and offered me the best service all the time! Connor, thank you so much for saving my day!

If you have the right car, use the curbside pick up if you have heavy items. Just do your part by clearing your car, and everything will go smoothly. They got the equipment to help you put it in your car. The guy that helped us was quick and knew what to do. We didnt have to wait long when we checked in at the designated spot -- approx. 5-10 minutes on a Sunday afternoon.
I always enjoy going to Canadian tire  they have everything you need and more    I just got my Audi A4 tires replaced. They did a good job!
Great selection of various products and clean branch, staffs are great willing to help. Fast check out time. Lots of free parking available on First and second floor.

The auto service was spectacular. Great prices and didnt change from when I called them. Reliable technicians and they had the skills to trouble shoot the problem. They called me when they encountered a problem and told me honestly why they had to trouble shoot the problem and what their recommendations were.  Ill definitely be going again. About $50 for changing winter tires with rims

I had an issue with a product that they are selling and they went above and beyond to help me figure out the defect and fix it. Multiple staff members helped and they were all really understanding, kind, and solution oriented. I was so happy with the service they provided!
Big, annoying to have to go up and down but overall good location
So easy to pop in and quickly get what you need. There is plenty of parking too.
Getting an oil change and tune up. I talked with the front desk person who took my information and I am all set to take my car in and have the work done. No problems all went well.
Great place to shop for automotive needs, home and garden etc. Occasional kitchenware is great too. This Canadian Tire is really in the middle of nowhere. Plenty of parking to work with.

I went to this Canadian tire and asked for helped and the employee helped and even went into the warehouse to look for my product, didn t give up until he found what I was looking for. Service was great! Store has a big great selection of products that I don t get where I live. I was really satisfied with the service and store layout. Lots of parking, wheelchair accessible with elevators.
Big place, clean and lots of options. But I really like to Male white manager (Forgot his name) his always been helpful and friendly. Upstairs department.

We went to the Marine Drive and Ontario Steet store. What a pleasant customer service. We were pushed around by the other  two stores in Richmond such as no, we cannot accept other store rain cheques, or the rain cheques are good for 30 days, no extension.  This Marine Drive store has a lot of inventory, accept other stores rain cheques. The cashier and the manager were polite and friendly. Keep up with the good customer service please especially in this stressful period of the economy. People deserve to be treated well and vice verses.

Tons of free parking. Totally wheelchair accessible. This is a good store to come to for all kinds of housewares. Pro tip: look up the item you want online to find out what aisle number to find it in. Otherwise it is such a big store, you will be shopping all the aisles.

Auto department was very well managed. Extremely comfortable and lovely open concept for a waiting room. This location does have underground parking, 2 floor levels. 1st floor being your typical canadian tire store, the 2nd floor being the auto department. which is nice it makes shopping super easy especially if your the type of shopper to get in and get out.

Free parking underground, 2 levels at this store, need to use elevators. Service is excellent at this location! Super friendly and helpful. Found everything we were looking for, great location, will be back.

You can find everything here even electrical and plumbing supplies. Theyve greatly improved their returns process. I find it way easier to return now when compared to last year. However, theyre still a little bit more room to get to hassle free returns status like their competitors. Good to see they continue to strive to enhance their customers experience.

5 stars for Joe and Pat in the Service Department! They always provide top notch service and I have never felt pressured or strong armed into anything. They provide friendly customer service every time.
Really big store carry so many thing
Found all the items I went there for. Including sale items. Im impressed that they still have hand sanitizer at the door.

First time at this location and was impressed. Great customer service, staff were helpful and friendly. Extra thanks to Brian who assisted us with baby strollers and we bought one. Clean store, Covid protocols in place. Plus theres a Party City within the store!
Recently shopped for hiking gear. Very pleased

Came in looking to cut some house keys the kid who directed me to where i needed to go could have cared less about giving me proper directions and really only cared about restocking shelves. Kind of a joke. However the guy at the automotive booth was amazing. He multi-tasked cutting my keys and ringing up other customers was pleasant and talkative and went above and beyond! That should be your next employee of the month!  Operator #: 605123. Give this guy a raise and a promotion!!!

Well stocked. Had exactly what I wanted at a good price. Bought an air compressor because I had a slow leak in a tire. Great product. Great price (on sale - under $50). Worked a treat. Also had the dome light for my ten year old car in stock. Opened till 9pm on Sunday. Just an all round win for Canadian tire.

Like this marine drive location. Good parking. Stock always there specially the sale items. Very convenient as it is closer to super store. When buy groceries can pick up stuff from here at the same time save me a trip
Tons of product , pretty well organized.  Huge store with good parking.
A variety of products. Really good and good service too.

Seems like i have been to most CanTire stores in Vancouver; a real go to when you are looking for general supplies and you can almost be guaranteed that it will be here in stock. This location is large and has everything and is full service. Seasonal stuff is out for Xmas already and the location is clean and well organized. Would come again.

Was looking for a starter bike for my special needs son and Sachi, Manager at the Canadian Tire on Marine Drive was so very helpful and patient.  We purchased the bike we were looking for.  I am so appreciative to Sachi for his expertise to explain and for being understanding with my son.  Thank you, Sachi!

Had a great experience with buying a new rim for my car, then having the tire taken off old rim & put on new. Louis from the Automotive Dept, went the extra for me to set things up where I was very appreciative! Had great service along with friendly...! Definitely be going back!

I shop here regularly so when I went in to do a big spring garden shopping I figured I may as well apply for the points credit card. There was a technical issue with the printer and while the credit card company was NOT AT ALL helpful in troubleshooting the issue so that I could get points on that purchase, the in-store staff went above and beyond to help me out. Special thanks to Ranjot Nagra who was patient and competent and made sure that I was happy before I left the store. Could have been a real nightmare and Im still really mad about the credit companys customer service representatives complete lack of customer service, but the Canadian Tire staff at the front desk and in the garden department were really lovely.
Good for purchasing home needs, garden needs, carpentry needs, garage needs, car equipment, workers equipment, kitchen items, etc.

A good selection of products.  Staff has always been very helpful.  We find  Canadian Tire sale prices are better than most.  I prefer because of the parking.  When you do make a purchase it is easy to take to the car and load.  Great kitchen supply selection that the wife likes. Check out the kitchen small appliances and other goodies.   Watch for sale prices.  Sometime they are up to 70% lower than competition.  Worth a visit.

I shop fairly routinely at Canadian Tire and even got m y last set of tires here. The store has practically everything! I can always find my SodaStream flavours, for example, whereas most other businesses have no selection.
Awesome place for Christmas  shopping

The staff were very helpful and friendly. The store was very organized, clean and well stocked. I enjoyed my shopping experience and I highly recommend people go there for just about almost everything one needs in todays demanding lifestyle.

Parking is ample and theres fun car-shaped carts if you have kids. Stock is always plentiful and the seasonal stuff is good, too. Floor staff are plentiful and easy to find, which cant be said for all locations. Theyre generally very knowledgeable and have pointed me in the right direction.

Had some tires installed recently, and was very impressed with the service provided by two employees in the auto department - Joe and Louis. They certainly went above and beyond. Tires were mounted, balanced, and installed within 30 minutes. Extremely happy with my visit! Thanks!

Love, so much about this place. If you go to the car section ladies you will find terry cloths to dry cars BUT EVEN BETTER use these on your DISHES for drying as there is nothing more absorbent then these for dishcloths. This store has friendly cashiers and lovely return policies.
I love the products here and service is awesome
I was glad to know this Canadian tire has a dedicated garden center. Found everything I was looking for. Some nice deals.
Staff and customer service was amazing will definitely drive out of my way to go to this store again :)

I shop here often. I feel that alot of the young employees need a bit more training on helping customers. Often times when I ask they dont know what Im looking for and then I find it. I rated well cuz its big they have what I need. Just train the young employees better.
The parts manager  mark was extremely helpful in finding my battery for my volkswagen rabbit. Took battery to my car aswell, plus hes a pro pubg player

Everybody was extremely kind and helpful to help me find this bike Ive been wanting! - I live far from the area and this was the only location which had it in stock, so customer service and the manager very kindly offered to assemble it and have it ready for pick up the next day. Really made my whole experience a blast. Thank you guys!

This Canadian Tire location service department is very efficient.  Joe confirmed tires were in stock & put on hold, appointment time was accommodating, installation was fast, and price was exactly as quoted.  Best part about this service department is they listen & do not use high pressure sell tactics.  Will recommend others and will come again
I love items on clearance here

Now I had just come from a bad experience at the Canadian Tire Burnaby Byrne road location where I found a salesman named Mark at the Marine and Ontario location. I phoned and asked if he had a particular tire I needed.  He said yes it says we have a set but let me check before you get there.  He came back on the line and said yes they are in stock. I told him I would be there in ten minutes.  When I arrived he had them waiting on a cart.  I paid for them and he helped load them in my truck. Now this was a great experience.   Mark I really appreciate the great customer service.  Thanks.

This is my go-to place for auto services. Ive been a customer since theyve opened and have never been wronged by the service team. Joe and Pat have always treated me in the utmost professional manner. You might have heard of all the horror CT stories and Im sure most are true. However, I believe this store is definitely an exception. To the CT auto service team, keep up the great work!

This is the usual Canadian tire store that I go to, sometimes I go here to get pots for planting things, other times they come here to get the odd tool or something, maybe a hammer, maybe a ladder, I have once even came here and got some pants. And I was an exciting time. They have red bowls at the counter which is nice, one time I bought a cigarette lighter plug adapted compressor. But it broke after the first use, I was unhappy so I took it back to Canadian tire and they gave me a full refund, no questions asked, good time

Was a well organized and well stocked store. Was a bit of a walk to get to from the bus, and the regular store is on the upper level so you have to take the elevator if you have no car. Was clean and had what I was looking for in stock.
Good collection of general machandise
Best store Best service   and delivery and lady manager good service if you got a mistake or problem.
Brock went above and beyond with Customer Service experience today. You cant get the friendly interaction online only in person. Will definitely be telling my friends and family to shop at this CT.

Every time Ive been there customer service is top notch. Unbeatable. Staff is super friendly and I wouldnt save a lot of staff but plenty. Every time you look for someone  it doesnt take long to find.

I always visit Canadian Tire to buys plants and  other household  items, every time my doctor send me for blood work coz Life Labs is within the compound of CT. There you can find varieties of house and garden plants.
Very clean and organized store, Mark in the automotive department parts is very helpful and knowledgeable,he makes sure you find what you are looking for.

Andrew, a mechanic in the shop was awesome. A surprise to me, my car wouldnt start up (with no prior warnings of issues). Although Andrew was the only mechanic working in shop, he stepped out for a minute to have a look and give my battery a boost. Great guy!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Danielle, we appreciate the 5-star review! Corporate Customer Experience Team

detailed_reviews.review_text: Got a flat tire.  Every placed is closed due to the long weekend.  I noticed Canadian Tire was open so I gave them a call.  Joe from the Automotive Service Department answered and told me to bring my vehicle in.  He said that it would probably take a few hours because they have quite a few vehicles in for servicing today.  He managed to somehow squeeze me in and had me back on the road in under an hour.  I cant thank Joe enough.  From the turnaround time to the service to the professionalism, I am extremely satisfied.  Joe and the Asian Mechanic with the blonde highlights (Sorry I didnt catch his name) was amazing.  Thank you once again :)
Clean and well kept and stocked Canadian Tire. Entrance off of upper parking. Bigger store, but is well marked and staff are friendly.
Its wonderful store, you can get many things there!!!
Overall I have been here multiple times and always had a good service. No major complaints, whatever you need they have and its overall a nice and clean store. Very convenient.

Great customer service at this location. Great attitude and willingness to help. I didnt catch the young mans name but helped me with obtaining 4 bags of fireplace pellets from the backroom. Thanks buddy
I always shop in canadian Tires friendly staff and prices.
Huge store, clean, organized and items in stock and a very friendly, efficient cashier (everything that the  Richmond stores dont offer!)......worth the drive over the bridge.
Shelves well stocked! Absolutely well stocked shelves for Spring. Clean Store. Fantastic Store Manager - Brock. Jam packed stacked up summer readiness for All.

Well where to begin, canadian tire has been a hugh part of my life , ever since i was young remember going there with my dad getting what we need for car and working on the car in parking lot . Now i have seen alot of repairs on my own vehicles over the years and spentalot of time wrenching my trucks in the parking lot just like my dad would do . And my favorite part as a kid was getting to keep the canadian tire money. Over the years its been growing into a great all round needs kinda store there house brand is become very compeditive with the big name power tools and at a price way below which is a good thing for the low budget people or if you are just a tight wad like my self . They have a great spray paint selection for those small paint jobs or brush on or larger sprayer paints as well as all your paint accessories.  The auto motive section is large and user friendly lay out for the self serve types or if you need help well good luck on fast service and when you get it its rare to find an employee wllling to solve your needs if they dont have what you need .that being said  i think over all this world would not be the same without canadian tire . Im glad its there for my needs . I highly recomend this store for someone who has not already experianced the good this store has .
Great selection. Wonderful and very hhlelpful staff. Bought a new toilet. Was ready for pick up in under 3 min. Loved it

I have had two exceptional customer service experiences at the Automotive department. The mechanics are very helpful and the service is very good! I always leave feeling good about the experience. I really appreciate the fact that they go above and beyond for their customers! Thank you :)
This CT branch is big & modern, up to date. Well stocked with well-trained staff.  Only thing, the automotive section is physically separate from main store. Minor inconvenience.
I love the service a lot and the staff/workers there are very nice, helpful and friendly. There is a lot of amazing things here and the store is clean, neat and great overall.

Canadian Tire stores around the Vancouver lower main land have been going through some renovations. This is a brilliant opportunity to find great deals on clearance sales as the store shifts its shelves they have lowered prices on items that have not been selling or the remainder of seasonal products. This is a wonderful store with great staff members who greet you when you arrive, help you find whatever you need while you are there and assist you when you are leaving. There are a couple of really amazing managers who treat the customers well and the staff seem content which probably means they are given the respect they deserve. All in all Canadian Tire is my favorite store and it is amazing that this fanchise has given their customers rewards since the begining. Canadian Tire money is the first reward system and that has changed our retail experience because now all stores have reward programs. This is a great sorce of pride for this corporation and a part of our culture which protrays a national identity which we all can be excited to be a part of. Support this store and you will not be dissapointed but rather fulfilled with quality and reasonably priced products.
Good price and service on the retail side. Got some bad experience with their tire department though in a different location in Richmond, although the name is Canadian tire

Great service, any time I need to find something they will go out of there way to find it.  I had to return something and didnt have a receipt and the lady made it happen for an exchange.  Great place great stuff!
Everything you need is here but some things are expensive. They have some clearance and offer
Can now pick up from locker, and always have weekly deals and triangle perks. Now I can even duplicate keys here self serve.

I normally dread going to any Canadian Tire. But this was a pleasant surprise. Even though there was an issue with the item I wanted, the manager went above and beyond to make eveything right and all the staff were super helpful. Thanks for handling a problem so well!
One of the best Canadian tire stores. Helpful staff and very nice environment. However, Canadian tire in general, is not always up to date and you cant find latest products.

name: Guu Original Thurlow
description: Bustling izakaya offering inventive Japanese small plates to go with sake, beer & unique cocktails.
address: Guu Original Thurlow, 838 Thurlow St, Vancouver, BC V6E 1W2

detailed_reviews.review_text: It is one of my favorite izakaya restaurants in Vancouver. Food is always good. The only con side for the restaurant is really small and its open kitchen, so your clothes will smell after eating here. Remember to make reservations, or expect to wait for a long time.

One of our favourite places to dine, the food is always too notch. The dishes are great for sharing and you try a lot of different ones as a group. Service is very fast and there s a vibrant atmosphere in the place.

Everything we tried was so delicious. The atmosphere is amazing and you feel so welcome immediately. The host was so nice to us, we had to ask,   Do I know you?    I guess we are not used to the hosts at restaurants being so sweet. Even the music and the cooks dancing while cooking were a whole vibe. Such a wonderful experience. I don t think we ve ever been treated so well in a restaurant. We will come back for more!
Cozy small place.  They have a large menu online as well as a separate menu of daily specials.  A nice variety of items.  The dishes I ordered were tasty.
Wonderful place and a must visit. The staff are so happy and make you feel at home. The atmosphere is so great and make you feel like you are in Japan. Yes, the food is fantastic.

Good service and the food was delicious. Chefs are cooking dishes in front of you if you seat in the bar also someone is very fun and happy. The Sapporo beer is so fresh. Woman s washroom is from Japan   you need to try it

My bf and I came here after searching google maps for a tasty Asian resto and we were very lucky to have stumbled upon this gem. We waited for about 25 mins but it was so worth it. The food was delicious, the service was amazing and the vibe was fun. We had a few of the specials: jellyfish on tofu, miso black cod (SO GOOD), udon shrimp carbonara and from the regular menu the sashimi salad and karaage. The only thing I d say is there was a bit too much dressing for our taste on the salad but honestly everything aaa so good. The waitress was attentive and kind. We finished off with a panna cotta with blueberry coulis. Highly recommend!

Tasty udon   and yummy takoyaki!    The whole restaurant feels like Japan!   But, unfortunately, the sashimi   isnt the freshest.  However, its still worth the price   and the best part is we didnt have to wait at all!

A reasonable priced restaurant. We had a bottle of sake, sliced tomato with tofu, pumpkin croquettes, Chirashi, and yaki udon, and mochi, red bean, green tea ice cream. All were great and delicious. The service was fine and staff friendly. A busy place, do make reservations in advance if you can, especially if it s a large group.
Was recommended by a friend, and was blown away by the great food and dining experience. Have only gone once, so Ill try and do more visits so we can provide a more complete review.

Probably the best restaurant experience Ive had in a while. Every dish we ordered was absolutely delicious but I particularly reccomend the kimchi udon, deep fried fish cakes, smoked salmon with onions, and unagi over rice. The atmosphere in the restaurant was on point and the service was very accommodating.

Love every Guu location. I enjoyed my meal so much I only took one photo which basically says all you need to know when an amateur food reviewer actually puts their phone down. So many different flavours and each dish is unique from the last, every dish executed so well.
Vibe was very good. I recommend ordering a large variety of appetizers and getting their hot sake for the chilly fall and winter Vancouver weathers.

Espectacular! The food was amazing, it taste so delicious and the presentation was expectacular. The service and the environment are the best too! I highly recommend it   We order the sake mojito, an appetizer, yaki udon ( I think that was the name) and a dessert!

I ordered various meals, beer, sake and also desserts, everything was tasty. Also atmosphere was great too.  Just one thing the service was,, just fine compare to their reputation in Robson area. Overall , All was satisfying
One of the OG and best ones in town. This one and Guu with garlic are our favourites. Small location so reso probably best unless you don t mind waiting.  Always great service and food!

If you are looking for an authentic Japanese experience, this is the place. Delicious, freshly prepared food and a real izakaya vibe. Friendly, attentive and efficient staff. We were there for lunch, place was not too busy.

The best yakisoba I ve ever had! It feels like I m back in Japan, but they have fused local ingredients to make out-of-this-world dishes!  Will definitely come back! Reservations are probably needed as this place is small and crowded.

Oh my gosh yum! We went for a later dinner, arrived around 8, and the restaurant was busy and lively. We were seated at the bar and got to watch the amazing ingredients transform into a magic and beautiful dish in front of our eyes. The service was fast and attentive. The atmosphere energetic and playful. The food was prepared quickly and was delicious, flavorful, and presented in a beautiful manner. We got the special 3/$14 tofu appetizer, shishito peppers, and the fish cake tempura. Shrimp black fried rice, okonomiyaki,  and the nametake meguro. It was all so delicious and a bit more than we could eat, but happy to take the leftovers home. The staff kept us smiling thought the meal and the chefs were fun to watch in action! I would definitely come here again and really loved the energy and vibe of the restaurant.

First time at this location, i believe this is one of the original locations. Busy for lunch i came here with friends from out of town and we really enjoyed it! Great tapas to share and amazing lunch entrees. I really liked the ebi mayo, such great tasting deep fried prawns! Delicious and plump! Actually i think everything on the menu is great, fresh quality ingredients. I do highly recommend you try out their teishhoku combos! Got the Sashi tray with assorted sashimi . One of the best Izakaya i ever been to for sure

This place is busy at lunch! And no wonder, it was amazing food at a great price. Being busy, it can take a while, but if you get there before the rush and order promptly youll be fine! Get the katsu-curry! Food : 5/5
Outstanding on almost all dishes, a great place to spend sometime with your friends. Dishes are small, but good ;)
Wow! Amazing small plates that we shared! From jellyfish to pig intestines to black cod all amazing!!! Pictured is some sort of poke style bowl all amazing!!

Friendly efficient service, everything was tasty and timely and good value. I enjoyed the agedashi tofu and brussel sprouts particularly. Dessert was good too! Yuzu cheesecake with green tea ice cream. Yum. Only slight is that the bathroom could benefit from some investment. Wheelchair accessibility: Not set up for accessibility but could be workable except for washroom.

A must visit if you are visiting Vancouver. There are plenty of restaurants in the area, but this Izakaya should be on top of your list. We came here 2 nights out of our short 4 night stay in the city. Now, lets start with the food. Highly recommend the Black Cod Miso, Sashimi Salad, Beef Takaki, 3 or 5 kind sashimi dish.
