The service was excellent, too. I will remember to get a double shot Japanese High Ball next time. These guys are very accommodating. We were coming back from skiing at Whistler and running late. They were happy to change our reservation to a later time, given that they are very busy. We will definitely come back here on our next trip, which is 2 weeks from today
Awesome place for a drink after work. Foods are fantastic
Got in for lunch at the last possible seating before they closed for the afternoon. The sashimi combo plate was the perfect size. Sho-chu hit the spot as well.

Excellent Japanese restaurant! We found it looking for late dinner and we did the best choice! Service was really kind with us, top! Food was really good and price is reasonable. We will be 4 days in the city but probably we will come back! 100% recommendable!

Great ambiance, delicious food, and amazing energy from the chefs. Every single dish we ordered was a delight, but do yourself a favour and get the kimchi fried rice. It s not as eye catching on the menu, we didn t order it until we saw the chef popping heaping plates of them out of the wok behind the bar, and man was it good. Who doesn t like smokey bacon and crispy rice?

Quality Japanese food at Guu! Restaurant is not posh and fancy or anything, a bit run down, but the food is fantastic. Good selection of izakaya. This is what I had this time around at GUU THURLOW. Love the Lychee Beer and Sake Mojito. We had the Beef Tataki, Beef Hanger steak with Chives, Ebi Mayo, Bean sprout gomaae, Salmon belly and Deep fried oysters. No complaints! Very satisfying dishes.
Had two awesome dinners with high quality food, great service and people. Totally worth checking out!

Guu Thurlow is one of those places that you can never go wrong with or have a poor experience at. I ve been to Guu locations for several years now, with Thurlow being my favorite; what makes this time special was trying two new specials that I just HAD to write a review for. Let s start off with overall ambience and experience. As always, walking into a Guu will give you the feeling of entering a izakaya in Japan. An exposed, homey, and intimate setting. Service is excellent as always with friendly front of house staff and knowledgeable bussing team along with energetic kitchen staff. Now let s move onto food, we had the assorted oden, Yaki udon, pork liver, and spicy salmon belly - the last two being the specials. They highlighted the entire meal and both were so tender and incredibly flavourful: the pork was paired with vegetables and was overall savoury whereas the salmon was crispy, sweet and spicy. Spectacular restaurant.

Awesome little original place serving up a Japanese plates. Really enjoyed everything we ordered off of their seasonal menu. Very reminiscent of drinking and eating at izakayas in Japan.. we came with two small children and they were really awesome at finding a place for our stroller and being friendly and welcoming to them. All in all excellent service, great food, and fun drinks. Definitely recommended!

It feels like youre back to Japan, both in terms of food quality and atmosphere. Everything was fresh and delicious, but my personal favorites are the sashimi and the hanger steak cubes. Theres a good selection of beers and sakes to accompany the great food. The vibe was really cosy and friendly. Will be back.
The food was surprisingly good! Good thing I made reservations there was a huge line while I was eating
Awesome authentic japanese izakaya. Only tried a few dishes, but definitely coming back to try more!!

Beyond the earthy and fun pub vibes (and sake/beer/cocktail menu), the outstanding seafood here may set it apart from other izakayas (in a city with no shortage of outstanding izakayas). The food is unbelievably fresh with a vast variety of options  sea urchin, mackerel aburi, yellowtail caraccio, monkfish liver, with a menu that literally changes every 2 days. Everything is made to order from scratch (we were sitting at the bar and saw them furiously at work in the open  kitchen). Please stay sober for the food

Were in downtown for the Anime Convention. My son has been watching an anime thats about an Izakaya that serves amazing food. He said he wanted to try it. We looked for a restaurant close to our hotel, and we picked Guu Original as it was walking distance. What a great vibe. The atmosphere was very welcoming and friendly. The servers were all so polite and served us with a smile. The food came quickly. We had 3 appetizers for $14. We ordered the Smoked Sausage with Carrot Sauce, Grilled Capelin and Fish Cake Tempura. They all definitely paired well with the Japanese IPA that I tried. It was very refreshing. For our mains, we ordered the the Assorted Sashimi on Sushi Rice and the Grilled Pork Belly. They were all so fresh and delicious. The pork belly had no gaminess at all. Ill definitely go back to try the rest of the menu. My son really enjoyed his first Izakaya experience.

Visiting from Montreal and wanted to try an authentic Japanese pub. This place was above and beyond my expectations. Sat at the bar and watched the friendly cook make excellent food all night. We tried the sashimi plate, the udon noodles with beef and the Korean fried chicken. All very fresh and tasty. The service was impeccable.

What a truly exceptional experience. There are a multitude of authentic dishes here, my favorite being the udon and beef tataki. I additionally enjoyed the taiyaki pancake dessert. All the inside is standard fare that may remind you of genuine Japanese diners, it was the service that made this it truly special experience. All the staff welcome and say bye as customers head in and out of Guu, which is unlike anything Ive seen before.

Really packed space and always lots of customers. Good value for your money as it s quite cheap and has good portion. I feel like this restaurant gives me Asian street food kind of vibes, you know, the noise, the grease, the mess, the yummy food, the smoke from open kitchen; it was a good dining experience. My 2 y/o daughter enjoyed it very much as the servers were very nice to her.

Fantastic place to eat, would definitely go back and highly recommend. Food quality - Amazing Service quality - Amazing Presentation - Great Restaurant cleanliness - Clean Washroom - Yes, separate men s and women s washroom, kind of dirty. Accessibility - No

I have visited here four times. Every time I come, I am satisfied with the delicious food and the friendly service of the staff. And sometimes they play hip hop music here. Tupac, Biggie, TLC, Ja Rule.. I really like this place.

It has been one of the most best experiences ever for my palate. The portions are fantastic, the service is spectacular. We had the Kimchi rice, the Yakisoba and the Okonomiyaki... I am definitely coming back often. I cant recommend it enough!
Amazing place to snack and drink. Quality food and service. The Guu family of restaurants are one of the most authentic experiences in Vancouver. Ill visit again and again.

Delicious, fast, great service and the best environment. All the staff has great energy and its contagious. We had dinner around midnight on a Sunday. Chefs cook right in front of you if you are sitting on the bar. Definitely a great restaurant!

A great way to start celebrating New Year s eve. We shared 6 dishes & sake & Sapporo on tap. What I love about Guu is that the menu changes & is different at other locations. Incredibly friendly service & staff!! Each time you go there it s an eating adventure to try new dishes. Well done!!

Came here on Christmas Day around 6pm and easily got in without reservation. The food and service was great. Everything was fresh and came out very promptly. The staff was friendly and even wore Santa hats, nice touch. Overall a great experience with great energy and really yummy food. Portions are also pretty generous!

Such a fantastic experience! The staff was super friendly, the food was great, and I love the daily features menu. I would also highly recommend sitting at the bar if you can, we got to see a ton of beautiful dishes going out that we can try next time!

This is a great little authentic Japanese restaurant located just off of Robson Street. They location is small and cozy and can get very busy. The food has some very unique items such as pickled okra. The menu was in Japanese and the server definitely helped me to select my meal choices. Everything was great, including the sake selection. I definitely recommend this place.

My absolute favorite Japanese small plate location in town. The food is delicious! We order the chicken karage and grilled halibut cheeks everytime and its never let us down. Service is also friendly, unique and efficient. Try to avoid the peak times since there can be a long wait.

This place has been consistently good over the years. The food is yummy, prices are reasonable, and service is efficient. They greet you when you are seated and thank you when you leave. When I go, its usually for lunch. I usually order their grilled fish meals like the saba, but there are many great options on the menu.
Love the food and the authenticity!! The chef was also very hot
Great food and atmosphere. Love the yaki udon! The assorted sashimi, beef carpaccio, and desserts are also great! Sad that they ran out of beef tongue even around 6 pm...

We stopped in because we love the Toronto locations so much we wanted to see where it all started. We were not disappointed. The food is creative and delicious, it is reasonably priced and the atmosphere is unlike anything weve encountered before (aside from the Toronto locations). Cant recommend it enough.

1. Wonderful place to spend an evening 2. Varieties of Japanese cuisine 3. We had octopus, fish items, beer etc 4. Hot and happening place 5. Recommended for Japanese cuisine (dont expect Sushi, they dont have any)

Wow, just wow. This place looks just like any other regular izakaya but dont let that fool you. Food here is top notch, and so are the staff. Id say that everyone was very friendly, energetic and inviting. We ordered from the regular menu and the daily special menu. From the special menu we got the aburi salmon on rice and the BBQ eel rice. The rest of the dishes were from the regular menu. These include: smoked monkfish liver, Takowasabi, karaage, takoyaki, and ikamaru (grilled squid). For dessert we ordered the mochi ice cream. The aburi salmon was fantastic. It was plated beautifully. The salmon looked overdone but in fact, it was lightly torched. This in combination with the vinegary sushi rice was delicious. You have to drizzle some of the soy based sauce that they provide. It was an umami rich experience. The BBQ eel rice was hands down the best I had ever eaten. They serve it on a bed of rice along with some fluffy scrambled eggs. This dish is super rich. Im glad they added the pickled ginger to garnish. You will savor every bite with how buttery the eel and egg are.
This restaurant is a MUST in Vancouver. The meal was superb in every way: staff were friendly and quick; chefs were vibrant, social, and culinary masters; and the food can only speak for itself.

Good atmosphere, friendly service, consistently good food, nice variety. I like trying their specials. We had deep fried brie and a refreshing cold dish. I highly recommend their lychee beer on a hot summer day.
Had dinner here, the food was excellent. Will definitely try to come back for those udon noodles and melt in your mouth sashimi!!

Our go to place every time we visit this city. Love how theyre open late so we can just hop over and feed our cravings whenever! Price is reasonable. Served and cooked by friendly Japanese speaking staff. I highly recommend this place.
we had the broccoli tempura, agedashi tofu, BBQ eel rice, and okonomiyaki with yakisoba. everything was delicious and the sake mojito was very very yummy!

The original guu!! Extra Energetic japanese experience today with the greetings as you enter /exit. Some really well priced dishes here for a sit down restaurant.. service is excellent when they are not super packed. The staff refilled our tea even after we paid our bill.
Really enjoyed the food and service. It gets very busy so making a reservation is a good idea.

This was the BEST meal I ve ever had. I ordered the beef tataki, yaki udon, and yuzu cheesecake and they were nothing short of divine! The service here literally felt like FAMILY they are the sweetest people I ve ever met   new favorite restaurant!! 10/10 recommend!

Ambiance is amazing Food is amazing Chefs are amazing, loved their energy preparing food while shouting          at the top of their lungs. The best Izakaya experience. (Well the menu is crammed, might be a bit hard to understand without some Japanese reading involved, maybe put the English translations in a separate menu :)

Authentic Japanese izakaya food and experience. Saba Mackerel was grilled to perfection, crispy skin and juicy inside. Staff are warm and welcoming. Love the vibe here and aroma of grilled food. Fabulous place.

This is a very unique Japanese Izakaya experience.  Food is very good and packed with Japanese customers (always a great sign of good quality).  We were delighted by the Sashimi salad, the karaage (yummy fried chicken), the Ikamaru (fried garlic spicy squid), the takoyaki octopus croquets), the eel fried rice, the negitoro (chopped tuna sashimi with green onion) and the yellow tail sashimi. The place is small, busy and hectic, but you literally feel the Japanese street culture and the staff s personality through the loud yelling and fast serving.  Perfect for late dinners. Closes 11 pm on weekdays and midnight on weekends!  Highly recommended as a memorable, fun and yummy experience!!

Can t say enough good things about this Guu location. It s one of my favourite places to eat in Vancouver - with friends, for a casual date or whatever! It s the perfect combination of quality, atmosphere, and casual dining. I get a pitcher of Sapporo and karaage plus whatever catches my eye on their specials list. This is a place where I like to try new things. The vibe is awesome. It s a little lively, with the kitchen staff shouting greetings often, but that s why I like it. The cost matches the quality of food for sure.
Yummy Katsu Don and BBQ beef.

Takoyaki= deep fried octopus. Delicious. Steamed mussels. Very good. Negitoro. We though it was like sushi maki but it was just a ball of tuna. We prefer the maki negitoro. Yaki udon with mushrooms. Very good although it has lost the taste it used to have. It tasted like it needed a bit of salt. Very good in general.
Great Japanese food. Prices are quite good and the place is open till late. I would highly recommend checking this place out.

Authentic Japanese restaurant with many BBQ options.  Price is decent and good food.  They were so good that we forgot to take photos.  The restaurant is small, better to reserve a table before you head over to avoid the wait.  There were 6 of us and we got a large table in the back which is quite cozy.
At this place you can order small dishes to share. A lot of different varieties of food you can order.  Great restaurant!
Our first meal in Vancouver and what a great start for the trip.  Everything tastes excellent!!  See photos for review (pictures speak a thousand words)

This is by far one of the best izakayas in Vancouver. Absolutely lovely Japanese atmosphere with amazing beer, and Japanese tapas style food. They have a daily menu which changes based on the season and what they can find at the market, plus a Regular menu which consists of deep fried food, sashimi, rice and noodle dishes. They have their own house beer, wine and sake, and their beer, the guuud ale is absolutely amazing.
Very delicious food, staff is amazing with the customers and they so friendly..love the environment and the presentation on the food

Subjectively, I prefer guu with garlic. At Guu original, a lot of the dishes are high quality sashimi. While this is not a terrible thing by any stretch of the imagination, it doesnt really lend itself to be shared amongst many people. Guu with garlic on the other hand has tons of shareable dishes that isnt just raw fish.
Love this place! Ive been their loyal customer over 20 yrs i think! The wait to get a table is well worth it! Just love their food! The Yaki Udon is to die for! Food

The atmosphere here is amazing. It feels like youre eating in someones damily home because all of the staff seem so friendly with eachother. It probably helps that I dont speak Japanese, so I had no idea what they were saying. The food was good as well, but I had a lot of hype coming here since it had been recommended by many. The food was delicious, but I wouldnt go to exceptional. None the less, I would definitely recommend this place for a small group of people (the shop isnt big, so sitting 6+ groups may be hard).
Best experience at this restaurant. loved how the servers were attentive. The food was delicious and great. Make sure to try there mango and lychee beer they simply delicious. Well done!!!
Guu knocked dinner service out of the park this evening! Friendly service, absolutely amazing dishes and a must try. Well done to the staff and kitchen! Amazing experience and great energy!!
Always love my meals here   been coming here for more than 10 yrs, food is alway
I loved it, Ill come back during lunchtime to try the Katsudon.

SO GOOD! There were so many delicious options to choose from and I was very surprised at how great the prices were considering the quality and size of the plated items. Long wait time so it s worth making reservations, and it is very hot and humid inside the restaurant in the summer so dress accordingly! Some of the items tried and would highly recommend were the Kimchi Udon, Karaage, and beef tataki.
this place has great food and drinks for a good price! Staff was so fast and friendly and the ambience is cozy and nice:) would definitely come back and try out more!
Im a royal customer. Its been 15 years since I first visited here. I love this place. But the food quality to be honest was better back in the days. But its still good.
Happy service staff greets all guests and bid them farewell VERY LOUDLY :) Fun cool atmosphere for great sashimi and beer. Definitely a unique dining experience but we love it!

Fav Japanese pub-style restaurant in Vancouver! A MUST try. My Partner and I were just out for a walk a few weeks ago and accidentally stumbled upon this place. I am so happy we did because they are amazing, all around. Ive been three times since! Atmosphere 5/5 Food Quality 5/5 Food Quantity 3/5 Atmosphere is so friendly and up beat. I wasnt expecting to feel so welcomed, but as soon as you walk in the whole staff greets you! They also say goodbye when you leave. - I thought that was the sweetest thing. The staff in overall is super nice. Everyone here was laughing and having a great time (socially distanced of course.) Not too loud too, I can still have a conversation at my table and not feel like Im yelling. That is SO important to me. Food quality is amazing. Ive been to some great restaurants before and I have to say, not that I love paying lots of money for food, but Guu could charge 2x as much as they do for some of the items on their menu. AMAZING dishes. GREAT for sharing. The chefs here know what they are doing. I would recommend off the dinner menu: - Sashimi Salad - Salmon Yukke - Negitoro - Tuna & Salmon Tataki (fav on the menu) - Beef Tataki - Kimchi Fried Rice (my partners fav on the menu) Food quantity is not as much for some items, like the Tataki and the Yukke. You are paying for the quality, so dont expect a feast! Some other items though, like the Kimichi fried rice, is almost TOO much food. I always go home with left overs! **Overall Im so happy I stumbled into this place because its a great time! Never should you be opposed to going off the main street (like Robson) to find a hidden gem restaurant. Guu is my fav! MUST have.
Great energy and quick service. Great to grab a bite and drinks with friends. Casual and inviting.
Let us sit down early. Good service. Good food.
The food was delicious and the presentation was impeccable. Definitely a good place for dates or parties. Wheelchair accessibility: Theres a ramp at the entrance and open seating near the window.
I felt like I am in Japan during my lunch at Guu Thurlow. Love the atomsphere and the authenticity - the food is definitely oishi!

I ve been here around 7 times over the past 2 years and I ve never once been disappointed, the vibe is always perfect, the food is consistently good, and the staff is always happy and positive. I always recommend this place to family and friends!

Here with my wife for date night. We booked a table through OpenTable and we were seated promptly when we arrived. This place was pretty busy, so glad that we booked ahead of time. We left the service. Everyone was friendly, attentive and helpful. Of all the dishes we had, the grilled squid and the sashimi were our favorites.  Wanted to try the lamb leg but it was not available and replace it with a beef tongue, however, we found the beef tongue to be just a little bit on the tougher side. They have a 28th anniversary special on right now with a picture of Sapporo and an app for 14 bucks - thats well worth it! Too bad I wasnt able to take advantage of that as my wife doesnt drink beer.
Incredible. Rotating daily specials that cant be beat. Insanely good pricing considering how good the food is. Im super excited to bring people here for a fantastic time.

Always a good time here. Been coming here since they started maybe over a decade ago. And they still here, so you know that means they are doing something right. Good food, good service, good drinks, good ambience. How can you say no. Always a good time here whether youre here on a date, with the homies or professionally. A good setting, is a good setting. Highly recommend. Cant wait to be back
Delicious and decent Izakaya style. Please always make reservation because of limited space and seating area
BIG PORTION - I honestly didnt expect this from izakaya. Ive been to different guu places in other provinces as well, and this place is easily within the top 3. Try there donkatsu, Yaki udon.
Staff were welcoming and kind. Ordered the takowasa and karaage donburi. Takowasa was addictive and good. Donburi was hot,juicy, and delicious. The doburi was a lot more filling than I expected.

name: Guu with Garlic
description: Bustling izakaya offering inventive Japanese small plates to go with sake, beer & unique cocktails.
address: Guu with Garlic, 1698 Robson St, Vancouver, BC V6G 1C7

detailed_reviews.review_text: At this point Ive been to Guu at four separate locations. Im impressed by how consistently good the food is and the charisma of the staff. This particular location is small but I cant think of a single negative. It has a friendly atmosphere and phenomenal food. It doesnt get much better than this.

Went here for an early dinner during the weekend. Not too busy at all. Enjoyed several dishes. The Tontoro, pan-fried pork cheek with ponzu sauce was really good. The salmon and tuna taraki s were both good. Potato mochi was good as well.

Went here on a Tuesday night. And everything we tried was delicious. Would really recommend the deep fried Brie cheese. All the peach cocktails were amazing too. The service was fantastic and our waitress was very sweet. We sat at the bar counter where you can watch them work In the kitchen which is neat. They also played only linkin park songs which I find hilarious. The overall amount of seating area is a bit on the smaller side so be careful if you try to come during peak hours.

Always an amazing time here. Been coming here for over a decade. Super to see them survive this long and still going strong. Great good, staff, service, food and drinks. What more do you want. Always fun and energetic ambience. Always busy too. Like I said, been coming here for a long time and I plan to keep coming back. Highly recommend

An authentic slice of the Rising Sun in British Columbia, Guu with Garlic is located in downtown Vancouver B.C. at the north end of trendy Robson Street. Walk inside and immediately feel like youre in a Tokyo neighborhood restaurant. Hungry for sushi? Look elsewhere. This place serves authentic Izakaya style small plate cooked delights like Takoyaki, Yaki-Udon, Kara-age chicken, Tuna Tataki, etc. High quality ingredients, friendly, patient, professional & helpful service; highly recommended! Support your local small businesses & restaurants

Really nice honest and authentic restaurant. Food was delicious and inexpensive, the space was small but cosy and authentic, and the service was very good. All staff were kind and polite as most Japanese people are.

I ve never felt the need to leave a review at restaurant until dining at this one. Nice place tucked into the corner far end of Robson, service was great and our server was lovely as well. Food/drinks came out quickly and tasted fantastic as well. Highly recommend!

We arrived quite early around 5:20 pm as we knew we wouldn t get a table later. We got two bar seats which we enjoyed. Didn t realize that there would be a fresh sheet at 5:30 pm. What a sweet surprise! Great food. Sashimi was really fresh!
Fantastic drinks and food here. Slightly pricey side but well worth a visit in the downtown area. Great service and super amazing staff.

Our go to place for authentic grilled mackerel combo. Mackerel is cooked to perfection, grated daikon is plentiful, rice is beautiful, and pickles are just  perfect. Yum! Haven t really tried any other items as we crave this mackerel meal, but I watched the cook/s make chicken karaage and it was done the proper way (double-fried). Would definitely try it sometimes!

Guu is one of my favourite places in Vancouver, it has a rotating menu and this time I tried their gyudon, kakuni, and deep-fried cauliflower. The gyudon was pretty standard, with complex flavours and contrast but I thought it could have used more sauce. The kakuni  exterior was a bit dry, but the flavours in the dish were light and relaxing. The deep-fried cauliflower was good, but obviously it doesnt compare to actual meat.

I love Guu! They have such unique and tasty dishes. I definitely recommend the takowasabi if you like the taste of wasabi, its not too spicy! The sashimi salad is also very good. So many dishes to try you have to come again and again! They also have floor seating which is so comfy.

Nice place for casual outings with friends or colleagues! I recommend getting the yaki udon, pizza, and kabocha croquette! their cod head special and una meshi bowl are ok. chicken wings fire, and only available after 5:30!

Havent been here for a while, it is still very good. You have to try the house special menu which isnt available until 5:30pm. The stewed pork with daikon and running egg is really good, we also liked ebi mayo and qrilled squid

Not a japanese food expert so take this review with a grain of salt. Came here on a Friday evening. Place was somewhat crowded. We tried several items and all of them were good. Great service! They patiently explained all the dishes and even gave some good recommendations. We sat at the end of the bar somewhat secluded and could see the entire kitchen from our seats. It was great watching folks work at breakneck pace yet make those meticulous actions. Staff all speak Japanese to each other in the stereotypical sing song way and while I dont know what exactly they were saying, seemed like positive messages every few minutes. Food was fresh and delicious. Had a cold wasabi & octopus dip with sea weed wafers and the dip was very fresh and somewhat intense (which I loved as a palette cleanser) Also had their fried chicken with dip, small Japanese hotpot, scallops pizza, and beef in sauce. The portions are small so you can try multiple dishes. Overall, good

This place is an absolute hidden gem in Vancouver!!! Their sashimi lunch special is so beyond worth it, it s a mustttt when in Downtown Vancouver Ordered: 1. Sashimi lunch combo ft. yellowtail, albacore, wild caught salmon, mackerel, scallop, & poke 2. Chicken kaarage w/ garlic mayo The sashimi was super fresh and the restaurant was rly generous with the slices! I love thick slices of fish & each of the ones were amazing*_* The mackerel here was one of my favorites which is surprising considering I typically don t like it. Price: $19 CAD for sashimi/$11 CAD for chicken The price is beyond reasonable and such a steal for ALL the fresh fish that comes with the combo. It s still insane to me that the sashimi was only $15 USD!! Searching up how to obtain Canadian citizenship now
Love the atmosphere, service and food! Great options and always super fresh.

Every single thing we ve tried in the menu has been exceptionally delicious. The combination of flavors is fantastic, the service is exemplary and the place gives you a Japanese experience. Highly recommended.

Food 4.5; Ambiance 4.75; Service 4.75; Flavors were strong and tasty. Miso Cod is one of the best Ive ever had. Plenty of fried options including crisp green beans and tasty mochi filled with cheese. Great vibe and energy. 4 people; C$100

Excellent food! Weve been back twice after our first visit around mid-August. Theres always new menu items to try, and weve enjoyed every dish! This is one of our favorite spots for sure. Highly recommended for the food, service, and the lively ambiance! Parking: Weve only been late night because of my kids sports activities. So parking was plenty. Cant say how it would be during the day.

Amazing food! The atmosphere was really great and everything had so much flavor to it. They even give you complimentary green tea with your meal which is a super lovely touch. One of my favourite places in Vancouver!!

This restaurant part of the Guu izakaya chai. It s really good! Highly recommend going in a group of 2+ and ordering family style. Service is excellent and food tastes top notch. We ordered a wide variety of dishes. The chicken kaarage is a must. The steak was delicious and so was the Yaki Udon.

Very nice Izakaya with plenty of drink options. The menu offers plenty of options, which is actually also supplemented by a daily specials menu. The grilled fish took a bit of time, but IMO was worth it. The Pumpkin Egg was also excellent. Funny enough, the beef udon was my favourite! You will see options like Japanese Curry, Katsu don and Oden alongside various plates of sashimi. Quite good. They do sell out of things quite quick so I would recommend being there early in the night if possible!

We had a big dinner planned so we only had curry with pork cutlet and bbq eel rice. Both were really good! Pork was tender, moist and crispy and curry was rich and flavourful, lots lots rice to go with it too lol. The bbq eel rice was great too, that crispy bottom at the end was yummmm. Definitely hit the spot.
We had the Tofu & Seaweed Salad, Takowasabi, Chicken Nanban, Spicy Poki Don and Yaki-Udon. All were very good.

Very fairly priced Japanese food, it s like Japanese pub food. You can always order from lunch menu, their hanger steak is totally worth it. Their sea bass was very mild and rest of the service is way better than other Japanese restaurants where they take customers for granted

Delicious food, lively environment. We tried many dishes including assorted soups, Takoyaki, kimchi noodles, steak, pineapple poke... just to name few. loved each and every dish. Warm sake was super delicious as well. Loved the entire experience.

We came at 5:40 and it still had a lot of spaces which was filled quickly soon. Maybe because we are hungry, this little restaurant feels great in every way. Friendly and fast service. The food looks good and tastes even better. The price is very reasonable too. Definitely will go back in next Vancouver trip.

Phenomenal comfort food! Great ambience! Always a great pick me up after a long day. Stopped by for some hearty Izakaya food. Did not disappoint. Great selection of appetizers and drinks. Dont forget to try their Scallop pizza.. Very unique!

Everything I ordered was delicious. Seated at the bar with a great view of the process, food was served quickly and fresh. Staff checked in frequently and I was very satisfied from start to finish. I ordered the calamari, okonomiyaki, salmon salad, seared tuna salad. Would come back in a heartbeat.
What an awesome restaurant! The servers and chefs were personable and made the whole experience better. I d definitely come back and try the whole menu. EVERYTHING we ordered was delicious :)
Their food quality never changes from the first time I ve been there. Highly recommended!

Delicious food and great service! Guu is a classic when you re craving Japanese cuisine at a good price. Everything was so delicious and cooked perfectly. Their sashimi is very fresh as well. It does get very busy during peak hours so expect a wait.
Nice izakaya with a warm atmosphere! Delicious food - simple and very well cooked. Enough choice to please everyone. Prices are correct. A very nice time with friends!!

Wow just wow! The Beef was in sauteed in this magical sauce, the salmon was fatty and juicy, the Taitake was great too. The place has an authentic Japanese restaurant vibe to it with floor seating and low benches.

This is my favourite restaurant in Vancouver. Food here has been consistently great every time Ive been here. Especially recommend getting the chicken kaarage, it is always juicy and very tasty. They regularly change their specials which is great.

Really enjoyed my dinning experience here! This place has a great vibe, service is fast, waiters are friendly, food is good value and taste great! Highly recommend their sashimi salad, beef carpaccio (not pictured) and tuna tartare!! Wonderful hangout place to eat and drink with friends as they have a large selection of drinks and tapas to share!
Great Sashimi, ramen, and potato mochi. Good service and nice atmosphere - would highly recommend

Great Japanese restaurant with a lot of the usuals and a lot of daily specials. I ordered the Miso cod which was light and had a very good balance of miso marinate to fish portion. The fried chicken wings were decent but nothing fabulous and my friend said the fried squid balls were very good. We sat outside but the traditional seating on the floor was very unique.
I love this place soo much!!! Definitely will come back to try more items on mean!
My friend invited us there and we had a memorable experience of authentic Jappanese food there. And we fell in love with saake. Lol
Loved the pork miso lettuce wraps! Enjoyed it so much I ordered it twice in the same sitting! The adult melon drink and the eel bbq bowl were also superb. Fantastic!
Its a cute and authentic Japanese izakaya. Food was fresh and delicious with lots of options.
Everything was extremely fresh and delicious, we stumbled upon this place and will make a point to come back. Great food and very cozy.
We didnt try their garlic prawns but other menu items were good. Service was good. They gave us six free small pickled appetizers.

My friend and I ordered 3 things and shared them! Our total was $13 each and I was full! The Takoyaki was my favorite I didn t have a picture because it was already eaten! Best Takoyaki I ve ever had honestly. The scallop mayo pizza was to die for. Definitely worth checking out.
It is a truly right Japan atmosphere in the heart of Vancouver. Do not await trendy interior, but it is just cozy Japanese izakaya as is, as I saw it when visited Tokyo or Osaka.

Delicious tapas style food. This is a japanese pub, loud and full of excitement. They rotate lunch and dinner menus daily on top of their core menu, so you can get something new each time you come. Like others suggested portion sizes are small but they are designed so you can try lots of dishes and share with your friends. I suggest going next door to marutama or santuka for ramen first before finishing your day off with some beer. A heated patio is also available here but sitting at the bar table is the best.

To start off, the restaurant can get pretty busy so reservations would be recommended; keep in mind they only accept reservations for 3 people or more. The drinks are great but the food was amazing. We had the yellowtail sashimi which we highly recommend although the it might be on the pricier side for sushi. Also recommended is the pork cheeks with radish. As for atmosphere, this would be the type of place youd want to bring your kids to or have a quiet meal at. The restaurant resembles the classic izakaya bar/restaurant  youd normally find in Tokyo; filled with students and adults that just want a place to unwind after a long day.
Awesome Japanese tapas. Always enjoy their food for many years! Good service and environment. The food look average but taste great! Highly recommended!
Fast service and great food. Being open after 9pm is a plus!
Delicious japanese food! Loved the seafood. My favourite was the garlic noodles as well as the pizza with muscles. Loved our time here.
Great friendly service, food, and Covid-safe protocols. Thank you for a lovely New Years Day dinner. The Grilled Mackerel and Garlic Soy Eggplant were especially yummy!

The closest you ll get to a authentic izakaya in town, serving fresh seafood tapas and other delicious Japanese dishes! Has a unique atmosphere that s perfect for weekends drinking and dining with friends!
Amazing food! The staff wasn t super talkative but hey were extremely efficient in a rush! We like everything we tried and would definitely recommend this as a must eat in Vancouver!

On a whim we decided to check this place out, as I love trying Japanese restaurants every where. But in particular was one of my favorite places in Vancouver to eat. The menu had a lot to choose from and we had a hard time figuring out what to eat. I cant turn down a plate of hamachi sashimi so we ordered that, some oden, garlic soy sauce salmon and garlic shrimp.
Super friendly service. They even accepted that I bring my small-medium dog on their patio. The food & drinks were great. Thank you for the nice experience!
Very friendly staff with a good variety of dishes. Everything tasted really good and the decor is done up really well. Im always on the hunt for good Japanese restaurants and this one delivered.

delicious authentic Japanese foods  highly highly recommended if you are looking for affordable and authentic Japanese restaurants with great customer service in downtown Vancouver!! I would recommended you to order anything from Teishoku (combo) if you don t know what to get!!
We felt in love with the food and the staff. Everything was perfect and beyond our expectations. If we lived in Vancouver, itll be definitely our place

Great drinks and food! A little pricey but worth the experience! Actually every guu location in vancouver is great :) I think they also offer monthly specials and the servers are really friendly!Definitely recommend this place and would come back again!
Atmosphere is fun and lively. The servers were extremely friendly and the food was delicious! Great spot for a date night

It was our first izakaya experience and it was wonderful! Its so refreshing to try authentic Japanese food with high quality drinks in traditional setting. Food was great and reasonably priced, service fast and attentive! Highly recommend to try out. Enjoy!
Great atmosphere and great food. I really like the udon and mapo tofu. It goes really well with rice. Will definitely come visit again!

Everything we ordered was SO GOOD. Prices and service is excellent. Will be returning! P.S. the apple mojito is the best. Really easy to drink if you aren t used to alcohol. It tastes better than the Aloe mojito!

Tontoro (pork cheek) melts in your mouth. And stays in your taste memory!  Sashimi fresh, especially creamy hotate (scallop). Mackerel on hot grilled plate, with garlic, great quality and value. Home made cheese cake. Plus, creative cocktails and sake.
Fresh delicious Japanese dishes, very friendly service staff .will dine again .

The food was super delicious with reasonable price. Staffs were friendly. They don t take reservations online so we usually need to wait 15-20 minutes before getting our table. However, it s always a good choice to spend our date night at Guu

The servers were so friendly and passionate, we came here to celebrate a birthday, so we brought a cake, and they not only helped us hide the cake but lighted candles and sang a birthday song for us! Btw, all foods were so tasty, seriously! Would definitely like to come back again!
Really great restaurant! Is it just me or does the food come SO fast! Really enjoyed all the dishes and really great service.
Fabulous food service and atmosphere. Great place to sit at the bar and observe the team creating your food
Very kind staff and nice good. Just feel like in Tokyo.

Wonderful first experience at a Guu location. Tried most of the dishes on the daily menu and all were great. Dishes are on the smaller size. We ordered approximately 10+ dishes to split amongst 4 people for dinner - I would say we were content but still had enough room for dessert elsewhere.

OMG! The food looks, smells, tastes so delicious! This place is adorable.. great vibe, helpful staff, and great service. I had enough vegie options and thats never easy! The cold Tofu was spectacular...
Loved the octopus balls, tataki and udon. Staff were attentive and price very reasonable.
It was Friday night and we must look for a place with patio. This small restaurant surprised us with special tastes. Heaven!!

Came here after an exam for some snacks with some friends. We ordered a bunch of dishes and they were all very good. This place is definitely for those who are more adventurous with their tastes in food and are there for socializing/sharing or drinking, because the portion sizes are small and ~$10 each, so sharing is more worth it. We ordered: 2 orders of wings with sweet soy sauce, 2 orders of takoyaki, sashimi salad, grilled squid, marinated enoki mushrooms with red tuna, Saba (mackerel), and grilled grouper head, and grilled beef tongue. The picture is after we wolfed everything down
Their miso garlic is seriously good, worth being a signature flavour at the restaurant. I had the eggplant and block cod and I d get it again for certain.

Made a reservation for 4 people, and we were let in a few minutes late. Literally everything we ordered exceeded my expectations. I stayed in Vancouver for over 2 weeks, but this was my favorite meal.
DELICIOUS and affordable. Great food and atmosphere. Great service. Highly recommend this restaurant.
Cheap and good. A very nice izakaya. Sometimes crowded, but the food worth the wait. Staff is nice. The Waffle is the best desert around

one of the best food in town for sure. and the  quality of the food and the reasonable price is amamzing.  should not miss this place. but i do recommend you to reserve your table before you go as the line up could be crazy.
This was my first time getting izakaya. I loved all the choices on the menu and I will definitely come back to try more things.

Appreciate Japanese cuisine that isnt the standard sushi/ramen. Staff very considerate with dine in accommodations. Not that it matters, but also enjoyed the staff speaking/writing in Japanese: adding a layer of authenticity.
Incredible food, great varied drink selection and the best service at a isekaya Ive ever had. Sho the server was incredible, always knew what we needed and when. Amazing vibes.
The atmosphere is good and I love all the bizarre and plentiful menu items.
Great Japanese experience! Little comfy place with some new japanese dishes. Everything looks super fresh and made at the moment. Staff super friendly.
Nice place! Yummy foods and good atmosphere.
Love this place. We ordered salmon tataki, sashimi combo and beef donbri, which are all great!
Awesome Japanese izakaya! Authentic food served by very nice, friendly and attentive Japanese staff.
Best quality price restaurant. The service is excelent the ingredients are ssoo fresh love it !
Its one of those restaurants where you have to dine in to really get the best experience out of it.
arrive early for big partys or small be prepared to wait. good food avarage prices be prepared to order multiple dishes. small portions but goos quality.
Great place.  The Garlic is my favorite Guu.  Always a hit overall with delicious stuff.  Some things can be different and not the best.  But overall great.
One of the most amazing dining experiences youll ever have. Food is amazing, staff is attentive, very comforting atmosphere. Overall very good! Sake is also very good. Cant wait to go there soon.
I really love beef udon, the soup was tasty ! and the staff was awesome!

This restaurant exceeding our expectations. We arrived earlier than planned and it was packed full - a good sign. When we got a bar seat, after a quick neighbourhood stroll, we filled our bellies with some of the most delicious food I have had in ages. Cant wait to go back!
Place was fantastic extremely hospitable good food nice interior very homey
Pretty much one of my favorite go to s in Vancouver. They have a super fun atmosphere, an awesome and always changing menu. I would definelty recommend their own Guu Ale.
Food was sooooo good!!! A little bit pricy but you wont regret it!

name: Jang Mo Jib Korean Restaurant
description: Mini-chain serving Korean BBQ, rice, noodles & other staples in a low-key, wood-lined environment.
address: Jang Mo Jib Korean Restaurant, 808 Bute St, Vancouver, BC V6E 1Y4

detailed_reviews.review_text: Very delicious Korean food. I got the BBQ Chicken in medium spice level & highly recommend it! The kimchi was also really good in comparison to others that I ve tired. Staff was warm, welcoming, and attentive. I also like that the restaurant is on the 2nd level because you can see the city life happening outside if you re placed by the window!
Beautiful ambience and delicious food. It ticked all the boxes for our authentic experience. Will definitely be back. Prices were fair, portions were good and food overshone my expectations.

Came here just two weeks ago and WoW! The food here is absolutely delicious as always! I m hungry just thinking about it.  My family visiting from out of town came with us and was absolutely impressed with how the food was very delicious! We were stuffed at the end and had some left overs to take home! I have been coming to this place for over a decade before they moved to this location and the food has not changed- it just too good! When im craving Korean food, this place comes to mind. Nothing can beat it! Their pork soup is to die for! The seafood pancake, bbq beef and gayoza fried and steamed are mouthwateringly yummy!!! Can t recommend this place enough to anyone I know who dig Korean food. It s a family restaurant and I find it is rare to have something delicious and family run at the same time these days. Will always come back here any season of the year! Thank you for a delicious meal each time!
Foods are just ok to be honest but the service I got from here was awesome especially from Jay I guess he is a manager of this restaurant. Thanks for great service.
This is our go-to place for Korean food. They have very homey and wide selections of Korean food that can satisfy your entire family.
we (2) had awesome experience - great food, friendly service. Iron wok chicken bbq was satisfyingly filling (bit spicy) and short ribs were perfect. we will go again for sure.

If I were to choose one word, Id say phenomenal! Went to visit this place with my family this summer for quality dinner and the food did not disappoint. I believe they have the best beef BBQ short ribs, their unique sauce definitely separates from regular BBQ . The cooked sliced pork wrapped in Chinese cabbage is absolutely splendid and the honey garlic chicken wings are unforgettably delish. I would recommend this place to anyone because you get great food for affordable price!!! Thanks Jang Mo Jib for the awesome and amazing Korean Food experience.
Decent food and service, they have a water leak so a bit messy when we were there.  All in all we liked it and pricing was good.

We were very enticed by the Iron Wok Chicken BBQ picture that was out on the sidewalk. Dunno why their rating is so low - I glanced through and most of the recent reviews were 4 and 5 stars so we gave it a shot. The restaurant is located on the upper level and is super spacious. I liked that they played Kpop - but softly so that talking wasnt an issue. Service was great, our server came quickly when we pressed the call button. Maybe previous reviewers arent aware youre supposed to call? Food was good, perfect portion size for 2 people to feel very full. The egg souffle was phenomenal, and the cheese enhanced the flavors of the chicken very well. The chicken itself wasnt the best Ive had, but thats me being nitpicky. The meal was delicious overall, and very very well priced (by my NYC standards!) - came out to about $50 total after tax and tip.

Great Korean restaurant! Shoutout to the servers - there was a young lady who served us who was very warm and friendly and happily offered us extra side dishes. We ordered the Korean hot pot as our main - it was fantastic and just enough for the two of us, making it a great value! Also enjoyed the homely atmosphere in the restaurant.

I was really hungry and just randomly popped in to eat here at Jang Mo Jib Korean Restaurant. We really enjoyed our meal  . I chose spicy and my friend had an extra spicy meal  . Ill post some photos I was able to take.

Best tasting Korean BBQ Pork I had in a long time. Warning, it is spicy   hot. You will need to request a fork as chopsticks are provided first. Cant remember what the drink was called. I believe it was a peach wine. Sweet tasting. Like Sake

The food is so flavourful! I am a vegetarian and loved this place. Veggie Bibimbap and Tofu stew were great. Chef confirmed and prepared the stew in veggie broth!! The service is excellent and everyone is so friendly. The ambiance is really nice and I love the Korean music that was played. Absolutely must visit! Highly recommended!

Very nice, BIG restaurant (probably dont have to wait to be seated) the staff were nice, portions quite big, price not bad. Really better atmosphere then some other smaller, super crowded korean restaurants near by. Will be back.

We had the Kimchi Gam Ja stew and Haemul Pajeon, which stayed crispy until the end of the meal. Everything came out piping hot and was SUPER delicious. I read others complaints about the service and I can attest that service was on point... even anticipating our needs before we knew it ourselves. We left sated!

was delicious.  The recommendation was said to be chijimi, but it was really delicious.  The fried shredded carrots were fragrant and made the chijimi different.  Both the pure tofu and the stone-baked bibimbap were delicious.  There is also a bar corner, so it may change completely at night, but lunch time was bleak.  Correspondence was very friendly and helpful.
Good food, friendly staff. Open til late, perfect for a night out with friends.

I love the soup! The taste is awesome and the price is reasonable. My dish is Bibibab which is 9$ and get a lot of side dishes. The bowl is so huge and it also has rice inside. Last February I went to karaoke of this restaurant too but it s quite pricy for me around 60$ per hour but there are many kind of music around the world. It has Thai, Philippine, Maxican, Korean, American music.
Food was okay. I wouldnt recommend coming for their feature item. Too much chicken, a bit dry and and too little corn, cheese and egg. Looks fancy but the proportions were off

This is a great place to come with friends and family. One of the very authentic Korean food you can find in the city. One of the best pork bone hot pot soup you can find in town.  The food is great and the service is always good
I had a worst experience 5 years ago, the reason I came back because I heard that they have changed ownership. Tried their gamja tang and japchae, it was excellent. I would come back!
Amazing Korean food in a new location at 808 Bute street.  Improved service and more casual fine dining now. Great service.  Great food.   Must try!

Came here for Gamjatang. The gamjatang was bomb and all the banchans were great. Korean trick: broth is refillable hehe. We actually loved the banchan so much and refilled it so many times and the servers never complained. The servers are so nice and honestly really good customer service overall. The two of us actually couldn t finish so we actually got 2 containers of leftover to go. So worth it.
Food is really good quality.  Service only lacks when they are really busy.  Other than that this is a regular go to.

I had sundubu and beef galbi at this amazing Korean restaurant. I went there twice in three days on a business trip, and it was really amazing. In my opinion, its honestly the best Korean restaurant in Vancouver.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your visits and your beaming review! We have shared your review with our staff! We pride ourselves on quality as we have for near 30 years and continue to stick to our values however challenging they may be in light of ever changing field of cuisines. We look forward to your next visit to Vancouver!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Its a nice place to have lunch. The prices arent too expensive and there are a variety of options for everyone.
Was looking for Korean restaurant in Vancouver. The food is pretty good unfortunately the shop is shortstaffed as we went for dinner slightly before dinner time.
Really amazing food! We ordered the iron wok chicken BBQ and the beef B.B.Q. Highly recommend both. Service and ambience were highly energetic and fun.

They serve the most authentic Korean dishes than any other places where Ive been so far downtown Vancouver. Their fresh kimchi, cold noodles were really tasty. Please dont use too much sugar which can cause cancer.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your stellar review!! We look forward to your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: First time i walked into this restaurant and i am very impressed by the servers and bartenders especially Ryan. I would like to thank you for taking care of us youre the best. Highly recommend

We booked Jang Mo Jib to throw a surprise dinner for over a dozen people. The staff were amazingly flexible with our large group. They left us alone and let us order when we were ready and gave us a free dish as well. They accommodated our requests to split bills various ways which is so appreciated. Food was solid. I wouldnt hesitate to return to this restaurant in the future. Thank you, Jang Mo Jib.
Good place for Korean food. Even my husband who is not a fan of Korean food likes it. Good food and service so far.
Delicious Korean food   and kindly staffs.

This restaurant represents what it means to truly value customer service and customer experiences. Every staff member at this location is so kind, thoughtful, and professional. You truly feel like you are being taken care of when you eat here. Well done to everyone who works here, especially the servers and manager who has obviously prioritized the experiences of guests. The food is delicious and super filling. Food also arrived very quickly even though the restaurant was packed. Very well-run place.

My brother and sister-in-law suggested this place for dinner while my husband and I were in town for our honeymoon. The four of us went for dinner and everything was top notch. The service was fantastic, the food of course was incredibly delicious and the atmosphere very enjoyable. We were there a few hours and left full, happy and excited to go back again to try more of the fantastic food! Would definitely recommend to anyone living in or visiting Vancouver! Thank you for a great dining experience!
The sundobu was sooo good. The pork thing was so so. It s always crowded! But they don t take reservations for less than 10 ppl groups.

We walked into this restaurant by chance, we wanted Korean BBQ at 11:30pm and we were going to get it. They were open til 1am and it was fate. As we walked in, we noticed the vibe was chill, yet lively. The servers were very nice and the food was fantastic. There are a lot of great Korean BBQ places in Vancouver, and this one is a great one to visit! Especially at 11:30pm on a weekend! Thank you! PS, all their sides were AMAZING
Good Korean food. Very consistent in quality.  Social distancing measures in place.

I do not know what the negative reviews are about. The kpop music playing in the background was a mix of old and new, and it certainly was not loud This restaurant is quite big, the staff are pretty, kind, and attentive. The food we had was the chicken bulgogi, and the soondae soup. The food was alright, its a different style from what I was used to. The banchan (side dishes) were abundant, and made well. We will visit here when were in the area.
I really love eat Korean food, I think Jang Mo Jib restaurant is the best way u choose

Went here for a birthday dinner for my boyfriend. Nathan was very attentive and ensured all went smoothly. Jay was our server and he super fun, matched our energy and get every order right! A no brainer to go here for celebration

This is the somewhat new location still on Robson! Probably the most authentic Korean spot in downtown. Stews/soups are great, the side dishes are all very fresh and taste like my own family side dishes at home. Big fan of the bossam + galbi tang! Very reasonable price + super clean inside as well.

Their owner and his wife were super kind and friendly. Their customer service was beyond and above. Server not so much, but owner couple made our day by providing their sweetest care for our table. Thank you we really were touched and felt cared whole time. Will visit again because of them!
We ordered hotpot + pan fried dumplings. It was very good and everyone left satisfied!

Excellent food and service, we had Nathan. Most bad reviews here are old and for silly reasons like a past temporary menu or the bathroom. Don t be fooled: good quality Korean food and good service for still not crazy prices.
Good bibimbap, fairly priced. Tasty squid barbecue. Food came in very fast, servers very polite. Cool seating with a view.
A bit pricey but great if you are eating with a group of friends
Food is delicious. The chicken BBQ iron wok is amazing.
The food and service exceptional, love the side dishes too.  Nathan was very attentative and a delight.  Nice new spacious location.  Prices are fair for downtown.
Been here many times and they never disappoint! Staff are so attentive, efficient, and friendly! Food and drinks are unforgettable! Sweet and spicy chicken wings are our favourite every time! :)

Had a great time! Food was delicious and well priced, and the portion size was perfect. I reallh enjoyed the vibe and asthetic of the restaurant as well. The music was good and the decor was modern and interesting. Ill definitely be back.
We went for lunch and the good was excellent. The dumplings were well cooked and delicious, the BBQ chicken was also delicious and the spice level was exactly what we discussed with our waitress.
This is a very traditional Korea restaurant Every dishes are very delicious
One of the few Korean restaurants that has a bar attached while maintaining an authentic Korean taste and menu. The food was great and the servers kind. Will definitely be coming back, 10/10.
I personally enjoyed it here. Loved the snow chicken and the side dishes! There were 9 of us that came in at 11:30 p.m. and the servers were sooooo patient and friendly. Thank you for being so kind!
So so good! Highly recommend!

After 2019 new year fireworks, we ordered food at 12:30 A.M and the restaurant was super busy. The menu is so looooong! So, youd better ask the server to help you on choosing the right food. At the end, you will not regret ordering its Gyoza. All the food is high-quality and youll enjoy the unique atmosphere as well!
I just so love this restaurant.  Spacious, good to go with friends. If lucky, you can sit by the window and get a good view of the city .
Went there 2 times, Japchae is to die for

This is our go to restaurant in Robson! At first I thought it was dark so I was hesitant to dine in but it turned out really spacious and well-maintained. Especially now with COVID, they see to it that all the protocols are followed and not to mention they have GREAT FOOD and GREAT CUSTOMER SERVICE!!! They also have the best cold noodles!! All our orders are really good though!

Have been here a couple of times; even though the service isnt very attentive but its not a total deal breaker. The food always taste great and the portion is enough to share among a few friends. It is sometimes fun to yell and shout at your friends while talking to each other because it is always so loud in there. Very interesting dining experience! LOL

My boyfriend and I come here every Sat night after my show. I love their BBQ skillets and the mandoos are delicious. My boyfriend loves the radish soup. The service is great but you have to really flag them down because theyre always so busy with quick turnover. Once you learn how to deal with the busy staff, its actually a really great experience. The night manager treats us like VIPs because we go often, and we appreciate the touch.
I love the new location ! The decor inside is so pretty :) my go to place whenever I crave Korean food. Bugaechigae and soondubu are my favourites

Awesome Korean food with authentic flavor and style. I love their grilled short rib beef. Compared to the branch near Metrotown, this one doesnt have those combos. Staff are nice. Definitely come back soon.

Great place, friendly servers and the food is fresh. I like the rice wrap, if you want less noodles than you can swap out for more veggies. I usually just get the half order as it is pretty satisfying.

Out of 5 Korean Restaurants in Vancouver, this one was the best in terms of quality of the food, service and price. I visited Vancouver for a cruise trip and stay there for 4 days. Ive eaten at Bibiko, Dae Jang Gum, Daebakbonga and one other. This one is the best
Pretty good food for a not so well rated restaurant :) Korean food, 1 - Raphael, 0
Good service and environments. Reasonable price

Im usually picky with the Korean I go for in Vancouver but everything is super well made here. Food is very comforting and the sides are extremely fresh. I recommend the Haemul Pajeon, Bi Bim Bop on the stone, and their tofu soup.
The food here was amazing.
The food and prices are really good! And portions are big. Love the seafood pancake, so crispy. Perfect every time we do big group dinners and they have karaoke and bar upstairs now. Yay

Love the food, environment & service here!! The food is incredibly authentic & delicious, and it s so convenient to have a bar at the top level with karaoke as well! Highly recommended & well worth it!! Great prices too   my go to for Korean food!
Everything was delicious. The ribs, the spicy chicken was very spicy and very tasty. They are open late. The k-pop was a bit loud but worth enduring for the quality of food.
Great food, very authentic Korean dishes. Went for friend birthday, friendly service and they give us extra side dishes.
Food is actually AMAZING! The staff is quick, friendly and the vibe is so good.
Great food specially the seafood pancake and awesome staff. Kudos to nathan for the impeccable service. Highly recommended.
Very good food and servers are so thoughtful! I will come back again!
Loved their spicy pork, seafood pancake, and the pork bone soup portion is massive.
Delightfully delicious. Kept table sides going endlessly. Amazing host. Highly recommended. Fun place and Karioke
Wow! Korean food galore! Soups and noodles and various meats. Great service . Some of the best service in town. Big booths for groups, tables too! Very fine place. Large portions great food.
Delicious and very authentic Korean   we loved everything we ordered; ribs, pancake, chicken fondue, mandu. Kimchi was also very yummy. Will be back!
Excellent food! Ya it was packed and the servers were busy, but if you dont mind raising your hand, service is good.
The main dish was amazing and so were the free side dishes. The service was great.
Loved the food here and the service was great!

Nice option for Korean food on Robson. We particularly like their different kimchi pairings.. You get the classic radish kimchi with bone broths.. These are unseasoned in typical Korean fashion to allow you to season to you preference.. And they also serve fresh cabbage Kimchi..we always get refills..
Fantastic Korean food, staff were very kind, atmosphere was pleasant (music a little loud at first but they turned it down). Would definitely come here again
Love the vegetarian options they have. Great service and amazing food. Loved it!! Definitely recommend
Had bibimbap with side dishes. They all tasted fresh and high quality. Will come back and try some more.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your stellar review!! We look forward to your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Been Many times. Love the service and atmosphere - Thanks Elliott!! When are we playing poker again?
Ive been to a few Korean restaurants but this place is a cut above, even the potatoes on the side were amazing! The broth for the soup was absolutely perfect.

Dont know why people are giving such bad ratings. Only bad part is that it is slightly more expensive than their location in Burnaby, which is understandable since its in Downtown and still affordable. Other than that they have great food and enviroment!

It has some expensive selections, but its soups (which are very good) are very affordable (~like ~8-9$). In addition, the restaurant has nice and aesthetic decor so overall it was a very satisfying experience dining there.
Awesome place. Faith is very attentive and friendly. The manager and supervisor are friendly too. Nice spot.
Delicious food and service, a staple of Korean food since ive been young. I recommend the mandu and cold noodles!
Went at lunch hour. Great food and service
Good atmosphere, kind service. Food was good. Id go back and check out a bit more of the menu. I just might...
Very tasty and delightful experience. Must visit this Korean restaurant and try their hot stone bowls
excellent service from nathan and the food was good. we love the new location
Amazing food and super friendly staff. The pan fried dumplings and beef short ribs were amazing.
The food was super delicious, highly recommend R2. HOWEVER, service need improved.

name: Eat Bar & Patio Haraheri
description: Bustling izakaya offering inventive Japanese small plates to go with sake, beer & unique cocktails.
address: Eat Bar & Patio Haraheri, 888 Nelson St m101, Vancouver, BC V6Z 2H2

detailed_reviews.review_text: The food were very delicious.  We got 2 Royal bento boxes, vegetarian udon soup, and a kids meal.  They were all very yummy.  Very great vibes .  Roof top patio and friendly staff.  Next time I do want to try the different items on the menu as they looked so good for the other tables.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and great review!! We look forward to serving you soon!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: This restaurant is a hidden gem! It took us a while to find the entry. They have a sign on ground floor says it s opened, however, there s no sign on second floor, so we kind of feel lost and don t know where it is. Once we went up to third floor, we found the restaurant and everything is so amazing! They have a really Japanese style interior decoration which is cute and aesthetic. We ordered 3 combos and every food is tasty! Really recommend the royal bento, it s $30 but you got to try so many dishes! Will definitely recommend to others and come back!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for your visit. We are glad you found us!! We are looking forward to seeing you soon!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Had a wonderful lunch at Haraheri Customer service: The staff is welcoming and provided excellent service. Food: Haraheri Bento Box: this was super tasty! Everything in this Bento box had good flavour and textures. Items incuded: chicken nanban, cauliflower karaage, wagyu hamburg steak, ingen fries, ebi fries, bang bang g salad, vegetable pickles & kobachi Setting: Tranquil rooftop patio seating was perfect on a sunny day. Definitely would return to try out the other menu items.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for the great review. Please come again!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Good food especially the karage chicken omg I dream about this fried chicken with the mayo dip. The hand roll was meh but I tried a few bites of steak from my friends and cocktails are bombbbbbb. Will definitely come back again. My heart goes out to the servers tryna serve our table of 11 tho but we all got chicken and beers so we re g.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your feedback. We apologize for our service and we will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: I came around 2 pm on Wednesday the service a and the attendant was amazing no complains but the best part was the food totally Japanese; recommended from a Japanese person. I try the curry with noodles and was nice till the moment of the oden 5 kinds arrive a perfect combination of flavours and textures I like to call it the sea earth dish
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your compliments!! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit. Please come again~

detailed_reviews.review_text: Delicious food, especially the karaage. Mocktails, cocktails, and beer were good. Patio seating is lovely with the lights. Floor seating is also an option. Great for both casual dinners and special occasions. A busy place in a not-so-busy area. Chatter is not too loud.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for sharing!! We will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Our local friends told us this place is sister restaurant to Guu with Garlic and that they actually like this place better. So we tried it out, and my goodness, it was so worth it. Granted, you have to order a bunch of dishes because they re kind of small, but that s izakaya for you. We loved everything, esp the sukiyaki and salmon ikura bowl. Spent about $127 pre tax for 9 dishes and sake which is very decent.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for your visit and feedback! We will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Nice spot for some social bites and drinks. The food was great and the service was excellent. I was quite surprised how reasonable the bill turned out considering how much we ate and drank. Worth checking out.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and feedback! We will try our best to serve you better on you next visit.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Love visiting here whenever Im in the mood for some Japanese food downtown. It used to be a Guu, but has now changed its name. I love the food, the atmosphere and the staff are attentive but not overbearing. Highly recommended the Brussels sprouts and the karaage both the chicken and cauliflower styles. For the special when I was there they were offering black cod collar which was delicious. Me and my dining partner throughly enjoyed each dish. I will return.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your great comments! We are looking forward to serving you soon!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: A neat little eatery on a roof with a wide selection of izakaya treats. You can order and pay on your phone at your seat, some dishes even come with a discount if you do. All the dishes are reasonably priced and even on the cheaper end. I really loved the blend of flavors in the cool eggplant and the black cod was so fatty and tender and generously portioned! I also really enjoyed my melon drink and ice cream, very creamy and refreshing. Service was nice and very fast, we couldve been in and out in 45 minutes with how fast the kitchen was, although we ate a bit earlier during dinner when it wasnt as busy, the speed was still rather impressive.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for a great comment! We apologize that we couldnt  reply for long time. We are looking forward to serving you soon!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: I visited the restaurant on a Thursday night. The place wasnt too crowded and we got a seat by the bar immediately. This was my second time visiting and they rebrand the restaurant from Guu to the current one. The ambience is still nice like previously. You order from your phone and they bring it to your table. Not a huge fan of needing to pay and tip before eating tho. The food itself was unique and flavorful. You cant find some of their dishes from other sushi store/Izakaya. We ordered pork neck, fish collar bone, roasted cauliflower, karage and mackerel pressed sushi. The pork neck and beer tonge were amazing. The karage had crunchy skin and the inside was tender and juicy. Definitely recommend checking this place out.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comment for our food!! It alsways encourage us to make our restaurant better! We are working on our order-to-table system to let you pay after the dinner. Hopefully, it will be available on your next visit. We are looking forward to serving you soon!! Arigatou Gozaimasu!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Tasty Japanese food and warm service. Really a cozy place to have meal and hang out with friends. A little situation we encountered was that we left a pair of sunglasses at the restaurant after dinner. The owner patiently helped mail them to our place in another city. Highly appreciated!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your visit. We appreciate your comments. Please come again!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Rebrand from Guu Garden so the menu is completely different from before. Still a great place for snacks and drinks with friends or dates. Huge outdoor space with patio seatings on the top floor of the complex. Stairways on the sides for entry to reach to the upper floors. The restaurant has an online ordering system, it is also a great way to list out the items you want to order in person without needing to repeat it to the staff. The foods were great aside from one of the dishes of chicken, thou it was deep fried but the sauce and such made it soggy.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your supportive comment! We also appreciate your honest opinion about the chicken dish. We will try to fix the problem and serve you better on your next visit. Arigato!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Amazing experience at Haraheri last night! We went on a Friday and we were helped immediately. The restaurant has a cute rooftop vibe and the inside is quite cozy. What I was impressed by, however, was their great level of service and AMAZING, authentic japanese food. The tuna tataki was divine - garlic chips added a nice twist. Chicken karaage was yummy too. The best part of my night was the cajun salmon aburi/oshi - it literally melted in your mouth and the flavours worked perfectly. Absolutely loved it. Staff was extremely friendly & prices were reasonable considering Covid! I will definitely be returning. :)
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your compliments!! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Come on by for rooftop patio dining @guuharden.  The tables are socially distanced and the weather was perfect for dining outside in May 2021.  I really liked the garden around the patio which reminds me of Japan. Its the 2nd time Ive seen this system at a restaurant, ordering from your smartphone.  Such a great system to use to minimize contact as well, I am sure it helps the staff with orders going. straight to the kitchen. We both order the lunch Royal bento box and was delighted my it arrived.  Everything looked appetizing with bright colours and organized placement in the bento box with attention to detail. The Royal bento box includes: - 3 kinds of sashimi - ebi mayo - chicken and cauliflower karaage - ingren fries - bang bang e salad - saba shima sushi - grilled fish - vegetable kobachi - miso soup. My favourite were the fresh sashimi, specifically salmon and scallops.  They both melted in the mouth and you knew they were fresh.  The rest of of the items, honestly was also delicious.  The shrimp was super big and juicy in the ebi mayo.  The chicken was boneless and super moist and crunchy on the outside.  I enjoy vegetables with the bang bang e salad, cauliflower karaage and vegetable kobachi.  I was wasnt able to finish as I was quite full.  My husband gladly finished the rest of mine. If you havent tried Guu Garden, you must!  Support local by dining in (patio) or pickup/delivery.

This is one of my favourite Japanese restaurants in downtown! Their service is great! The food is very intricate and flavourful. During covid time, they have QR code on their table that allows you to order and pay through your phone. I love the thought they put in designing their outdoor dining experience. They have heater, pretty lighting and a nice view.

It was my first time dinned at this place. All the dishes were delicious but maybe because this restaurant business was very good on that particular Sunday night. I hardly can hear my friends talking across the table  I will return other days to try the food again.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your compliment on our food and apologize for any inconveniences during your visit. We will try our best to manage it and serve you better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: The thing I loved the most about Eat Bar & Patio Haraheri is the way the space itself is setup. The entire restaurant feels like a rooftop patio (half of which is actually a rooftop patio). Even when youre inside, it almost feels like youre outside because of the wall to ceiling sliding glass doors. The staff were also super friendly. They had a great big smile as they welcomed us into/ushered us out of the restaurant. The food was delicious and prompt. I can recommend the Chicken Karage, the duck breast, Nasu Agebitashi, Bang Bang G Salad, and the Sake Sangria. Great spot to enjoy a nice summer day with friends and good eats.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your feedback!! Please come again!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: We re a fan of the Guu family for 2 decades now and we ve had consistently fantastic izakaya experience at Guu Garden. Our go-to dishes every time are their agedashi mozzarella , tuna tataki, duck, pork cheek, and yaki udon. Never had a mediocre dish and service has always been on point. These guys switched to takeouts seamlessly during covid and we were so grateful we had this as an option! So glad we were able to dine at Guu Garden before they shutdown for reno/rebranding.
