Looking forward to their re-opening.

Amazing 3rd floor large secluded patio and food was deliciois. Nice variety, lots of vegetarian and carnivore options, and easy to share. Service was friendly and really efficient. They also had some larger tables that could easily accommodate a larger group of 8-10 people. Perfect summer time spot.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for sharing!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Out of all the Guus in Vancouver I think this one is the best. I love that their situated above street level. It s got a bit of drama when you walk up the steps to their entrance. I ve come here for both dinner and lunch but come here more often for lunch. Their lunch menu is sooooo good. I ve had all their lunch specials and my favorite is the steak one. You can add the egg to it as well as a slightly larger portion of steak, if you re feeling super hungry. The normal one is pretty generous and comes w rice, soup, pickled veggie, and salad. their izakaya one is also really good and my second favorite, as that one offers nice variety. Price is not bad for downtown sushi set lunches. they do have $10 rice bowls as well. So a good range of items depending how much you want to spend.

One of the finest Japanese restaurant in Vancouver. I love the lunch menu, especially the sukiyaki, taste and portion are perfect for me. Several choice of cocktails and sake. Warm sake is also another favorite one for myself. The location is alright. Some chairs are not that comfortable but still acceptable. Definitely need to make reservations for dinner, it s usually full.

Came here fairly late at night in the rain with my family, so there wasnt too many other people there when I was here. That being said, service was fairly attentive and very polite with us. Well now that we got that part out the way.. The food was pretty damn good. We got six regular size plates and whew, they really hit all the right notes. I have a particular fondness for all things uni, so the baby scallop and uni cream croquette was just icing all over a very moist cake. We also ordered pork cheek, miso calamari, nankotsu, agedashi tofu and black cod kama. Presentation of each dish is pleasing, considering theyre mostly small fried plates, and they came out at a decent speed. Gotta say, nothing I didnt like at this place. Its not mind blowingly good, but they do everything so solidly its hard not to give them a 5.

Very nice izakaya, good interior design and tasty dishes. The beef tongue is definitely recommend. Portion sizes were a bit small but is expected regarding the price. However, the online ordering system could be adjusted; paying the tips after receiving service would be better.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for you supportive comment and your opinion about our online system. Our tech team is working hard to make that happen. We are hoping the feature would be available soon. We will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!! Arigato!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ive been coming to Guu Garden for many years now, and am amazed at their ability to change their menu regularly to incorporate seasonal fare, while maintaining a few delicious staples. This location in particular does an amazing New Years lunch set that they have also changed nearly every year (this year it featured a huge lobster tail as the highlight). The location is also wonderful, especially in the summertime when the rooftop patio seating is available. Due to the size of the surrounding buildings, and the less than obvious route to get there, it always feels like a bit of a secret location.

Always love Guu restaurant no matter which one it is. This one is unique, it has a massive patio however it s a shame that it is not well utilized and decorated. They could have an amazing rooftop patio vibe but I guess they didn t put any efforts into that. Anyway, food is not bad. It is a bit weird to that you have to pre-pay your order when ordering thru the their online menu. It is hard to split between friends and hard to determine the tip because I hardly even got any food or service yet.
Hidden little gem Downtown. I would totally gatekeep but I wont!  Delicious food and a great atmosphere.  Sashimi super fresh!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for finding us! We are looking forward to serving you soon!

detailed_reviews.review_text: A wonderful gem, tucked away. Tanaka-San curated a fantastic menu for our group of 16; delicious food, great wine and impeccable service.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for stars!! We look forward to serving again!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Everything I visit Guu Garden, I am always amazed by how they are always consistent in their ability to excite me. The food offers a good variety of Izakaya classics as well as delicious creative takes on classic tapas as well. This is a place meant to go in groups to order as large a variety as possible. Already wanting to go back!
Best karaage Ive had in years. The salmon oishi was really good too! Will definitely be back. Thank you so much for the amazing service and hospitality!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and a great feedback. We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: We preordered bento boxes which was good idea! But I wish there were less deep fried dishes.   Good atmosphere and friendly staff.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and feedback. We will keep trying our best to serve you better on your visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Went here for lunch on Sunday. Loved it. I ordered the chirashi with marinated sashimi and raw shrimp.  Came with a chawanmushi and miso soup. My wife had the special work the spaghetti and fresh mussels.  Great food at great value.

Excellent izakaya restaurant! The dishes are all delicious, packed with flavour and well presented. Prices are excellent! Service is great, very helpful. The salmon oshi was one of my favorite dishes, the brown rice was a nice twist! The ebi mayo was my second favorite, perfectly cooked and lightly battered!

I booked a party for 16 people for a birthday party. I even checked ahead of time if the bills can be split and it wasnt any issue. At the end of the night, we just put it on one bill, but I appreciated the owners patience for all the multiple questions I had. When we got there, I realized I forgot to mention that we wanted to sit outside, but since there were open tables, they gladly accommodated us. The outdoor space was beautiful and didnt feel like we were downtown, but on a rooftop little oasis. The food and drinks came out at a wonderful pace, without over crowding the table but not too slow where we were waiting too long either. There were too many dishes to name, but the stand outs were the tuna tataki, salmon oishii, beef tongue in broth with rice, grilled beef tongue, mentaiko pasta, tako wasa and salmon sashimi. We were having such a good time I forgot to take pictures. The staff here are amazing, so nice and we never felt rushed.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your visit and give great comments! We will try our best to serve best on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ate here our first evening in Vancouver. The restaurant was crowded, but the servers work hard to provide us with great services. Many great option on the menu. The food were excellent.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for sharing!! Please come again!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: great service, great attitude, serviced me the wrong food and the manager, the waitress came out and showed deep and sincere apology with good attitude. They treat their customers very well.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for sharing your experience and gave us another chance! We look forward to serving you soon!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Everyone must have their lunch! Preorder and they give %10 off! I saved $5.5 therefore lol
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit! We are looking forward to serving you again!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: This is a great Japanese fusion restaurant that is part of the Guu Family of restaurants in Vancouver. They have great cocktails like the Frozen Sake Bellini. The service is very good and arrives quickly. The restaurant is usually very busy, so you may want to get a reservation.
Great izakaya. Would recommend the duck breast, takara plum wine, salmon oshi sushi, cauliflower, creamy udon
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for great pictures!! We are looking forward to serving you again!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Guu Garden is a unique and memorable experience every time I eat there. The usual dishes I order include: Nasu (ginger-soy marinated eggplant), Mekyabetsu (deep-fried brussel sprouts), and Gin Kama Grill (cod cheek), all equally delicious in their own right. However, I recommend not limiting yourself to just these three dishes, as they have many to offer, which you should check out. This place is a must for food lovers who are visiting Vancouver!
This place was missing only one thing customers. It is a shame it wasn t full. It should be everyday. Ridiculously inexpensive, great tasting, awesome location
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your feedback! It encourages us to keep what we are doing and we appreciate that. Please come again!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great lunch options. The Bento boxes were delicious. Oden, chicken bang bang salad, yaki udon were amazing. During the patio dining only, the servers were very good. They have a great online ordering system so you dont have to go though any payment machine but rather on your own phone. That is very amazing now a days. Staff and food A+++
Great food and comfy rooftop spot.  Left my jacket and waitress found me about to cross the street to return it - a 5 Star in my books
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit. We are looking forward to serving you soon!

detailed_reviews.review_text: So delicious! All their plates are top notch and they even have their own ale! They have a lot of daily specials to try. Try the chicken knee! I thought their desserts were only so so.
Great food and atmosphere. Service is top notch. Perfect spot to enjoy patio weather!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and a great review! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: The dishes here are consistently delicious. We really enjoy the pork cheek every time. We tried two new dishes which were the ribs and the yuzu cod which were both amazing. Service was really nice too as they give you a hot towel when you arrive just like in Japan. Remains our go to for izakaya.
I m literally satisfied!!!! The food the service the ambiance just can t be better!!! I love everything they serve and I didn t leave any food in any plate. This place is amazing!!!

Recently came here again and was thoroughly impressed, especially with their lunch menu options. I had the Royal Bento Box, which came with three kinds of sashimi (scallop, shrimp, salmon), ebi mayo, chicken karaage, cauliflower tempura, saba shima sushi, grilled fish, and a few Japanese appetizer bites. It was a great portion for a wholesome lunch, beautifully prepared!
Great cozy patio and interior. We ordered tuna tataki and it was fantastic and also the cheesecake was mind blowing.

My fd took me here for lunch, if u call 30mins before, u will get discount. When u get there, the food is prepared. So if u dont want to wait, and just call in and get discounts!!! The staffs are friendly and nice. The food is very good!! The sashimi is fresh. The royal bento box I got, the tempera is amazing, I really love it! Enjoy our lunch!
The cocktails are SO GOOD! And their vegan creamy udon pasta is soooo delicious. Love it here.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comment!! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!! Arigato!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Food was beautiful and delicious.  Staff were friendly and unassuming.  A gem for sure.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Good place for japanese. A lot of not as popular food like squid pasta or wasabi octopus. The rice a little bit overcooked but everything else is perfect
A hidden Japanese gem with a lovely rooftop patio. Excellent food, wonderful atmosphere, and polite, friendly and efficient staff.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for your visit! We will try our best to serve you best on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Come here for the 24oz Mega Sapporos and amazing small plates. Sashimi here is expensive. However, the quality reflects the price. If you do get shrimp sashimi, you can ask them to deep fry the shrimp heads after you eat the shrimp body. Their oden was particularly good.

This my second time visiting Guu Garden. The food here punch above its price point. It is not flashy compare to new comers like Raisu, but it delivers great taste and value. If you are ever unsure of what to order, I recommend the Izakaya Lunch Box, and get a beer while you are at

Excellent food. Very popular. Noisy. Accessibility is a bit confusing. Elevator access via an adjacent building is available but no signage to indicate that. Many steps to climb, which is difficult for some would be patrons. Staff are very attentive. Note... Two-hour seating limit for busy times. These details could easily be included in their website.
Dine out 2020 was great. Good food seletions and decent price ($25). One of the few restaurants that is worth of going during Dine out.

Delicious food, very reasonable prices, attentive service, classy big band jazz music, authentic Japanese dining experience, what more could you ask for? For value, go for the lunch menu and call in  a preorder 30 minutes ahead of time for 10% off.
Food is good, sashimi is fresh , place is not busy .
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your compliments!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ive been here twice for dinner and twice for lunch, and was delighted with the food and service each time. Staff are polite, friendly, and attentive. The cream udon was perfectly done - very umami - and my personal favourite is the tamagoyaki oden, which I think is only available during lunch. It melts in your mouth and is perfect on a cold, winter day. I also love that there is plenty of patio space, which can accommodate large groups. I highly recommend this place. Parking: Paid underground parking available.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for a great review! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: I had a great experience here. The staff are welcoming and really know the menu. The food was excellent as well. The feet warmers under the table are a very nice perk as well. I would go back just for that. Dietary restrictions: I am gluten free and the staff took it very seriously. I found I had lots of options as well.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato gozaimasu for your great feedback!! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Good amount of food,creative dishes,competitive price with great quality of food:)I love this Izakaya.
The food compliment the drinks so well my asian glow was on FIREEEE
Best Japanese food in town Its real Japanese restaurant, not  Korean  Japanese restaurant. They also have great price for the beer.
Another hidden gem in Vancouver! Would definitely come back. Roof deck view Classy place
Really enjoy the whole lunch, excellent customer service, food is very very good.
I loved everything they served here, I truly recommend this spot! I d like to come back for the takoyaki and mackerel oshizushi! The atmosphere is super nice! Loved the Zashiki style tables.

I hosted my 32nd birthday here.  Weeks before my event, they were prompt to reply and were communicative throughout the whole procedure. During the night, they on-the-fly accommodated my extra seats.  The service was excellent, and the food was good.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your visit on your 32nd birthday and sharing your experience. We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Best prawns Ive ever had. Have to get them in season (May) but the food and atmosphere is wonderful.
Tasty, tasty food here!! Service was quick and attentive! Will be back again! The smoked mackerel was flavourful and fresh!
This place is a hidden gem. Bartender is so cool. Love the food. Wish I had known this spot earlier. You should visit if you are staying at Sheraton.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato you very much for finding us and give us a chance to serve you. We are looking forward to seeing you soon!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great spot for lunch and huge patio for the summer. Mega 1L bzzrs....Basically 3 bzzrs for $9. Service always with a smile. *Tip* phone in your lunch order ahead of time and receive a few bucks off per entree.

Best chicken karaage ever. All the dishes were delicious, service was great. Tako wasabi was good, but I think octopus could be marinated a bit longer to make it a bit more tender. Cool location, would come again.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and compliment!! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Really nice patio for summer. One of the best Izakaya I try in Vancouver.

I m glad we stumbled into this restaurant a few nights ago! The food was wonderful and served quickly by attentive staff. We are already planning to go back for the oden, mushroom udon and G Bang salad!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit and planning for another! We will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Nice place. They need better management of the items still available from the menu
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your advice. We will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: One of the few places I was able to make a reservation for 13 people on Christmas day in Vancouver. That already says something about how accommodating they are. As soon as we entered, we were greeted with loud welcomes from all the staff and seated prompt. The seating where you had to take off your shoes had foot warmers there to keep you warm in the colder winter days. Super nice. The staff would shout orders from right next to you to the bar if needed, so expect that when coming. :) There were a lot of Winter specials when we came and the prices were really fair for the portion. Beef tartar was one of our specials (amazing flavor, nice tender cuts that werent chewy at all). The uni and scallop croquette was nicely fried with such a rich filling. I was looking forward to finally having aburi, so I ordered the salmon off of the original menu. Nice sear on the salmon that complemented the seasoned rice, topped with warm, earthy, slightly spicy spices. So, so good. The mackerel was also really tasty, with a nicely salted fish and seasoned rice. Overall, all of the other dishes were really tasty and I enjoyed everything. The fried cheesecake ice cream was also very tasty, nothing much else like it that I ever had. Highly recommend!
Incredible food for great value!! Super tasty and cosy spot.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for a great comment!! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Everything we ordered was fantastic.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your compliments! We are looking forward to serving you soon!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: The best sushi Ive eaten. The view is wonderful.

This place is amazing. Definitely on the pricier side of things, but I think the overall experience was worth it. There wasnt a single dish I disliked, out of the 10s of different dishes my party ordered. My only complaint is regarding the propane fireplace placed on the benches for outdoor seating. It got way too hot, and the poor lighting without it may be an issue for those who like taking pictures of their food.
Super friendly staff and good food!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your visit & compliments! Please come again!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: We used to go here when it was Guu Garden, and it actually got way better now that the owner took into their own hands and branding. Great atmosphere, great service from the amazing staff and continues to offer delicious Japanese food with lots of variety on the menu for both meat eaters and vegetarians. Will be back for sure.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your continuous support! We are looking forward to serving you soon!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Really good food and very friendly customer services. Highly recommend!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your feedback! Please come again!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Prices were good considering the quality, I really loved the Ebi Mayo and Karaage but I thought the Katsu Curry was okay.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for you feedback! We will try our best to serve you better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Love the ambiance, the food and the Last Samurai cocktail <3 make sure to book on a weekend night as its always packed. Awesome for a casual date night as you can share and try all different kinds of food which usually come in small portions. Some vegetarian options available too. Be prepared for servers who yell orders at other! It makes it very fun and unique!

Wow, what a gem! The food here was incredible. Highly recommend it if youre in the area. Will definitely be back. Be sure to try out the duck chashu and get the salted caramel sake ice cream for dessert if available!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Arigato very much for your complaints! We will try our best to serve you even better on your next visit!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Met up with some work friends here for the first time and holy man was this place great! Rooftop views, very popular,  the food was tasty, we shared a bunch of smaller plates and the Saki sangria knocked it out of the park! There is a two hour limit on large tables but they let us stay longer than that which was nice of them if youre looking for a trendy Rooftop patio that serves up premium Japanese food, this is the place. A reservation is a MUST otherwise youre not getting in .

I came in for lunch with an associate, it took a bit to find, it is on the third level in a remarkably serene patio setting. It is a sheltered patio area with cover, it really was beautiful and serene. The service was very good and the food was excellent. We tried a number of things. We shared a sashimi combo, the sashimi was excellent. We also shared a variety of other things, Fluffy fish cakes, cod cheeks, octopus. And the miso soup was excellent.

Friend took me to Guu Garlic and I liked it. So I took the family out to Guu Garden near Air B&B where we stayed. Ordered miso fried squid, fried uni with scallop, pork cheek, black cod Kama (neck), agedashi tofu and two mixed drinks with cold sake. Everything is excellent with the exception of Kama which is on the sweet side but still enjoyable. Portion can be regular or small on some dishes. We had the regular. Meal for 4 is less than $100 Canadian before tip but includes the two drinks. Some complained about the wait but we went at nine and was seated immediately without reservation. They close at twelve.
Delicious and authentic Japanese izakaya place. Very popular though so highly recommend reservations.

I love their regular pub menu(especially Oden!) but also love lunch menu a lot. So many variations from popular Japanese dish, but everything is in their original creative way. It seems nothing is compromised even a simple appetizer. There are some Japanese pubs/restaurants which I can t be proud of, but this is it!

This izakaya serves some of the tastiest sashimi I have ever eaten! Their specials are excellent and creative. Their beer selection is also very convincing. The staff will gladly help non-Japanese speakers figure out the secrets of the menu. What a fantastic place!

I love Guu Garden. They have a wide range of vegan options (which is why I go). Their food is flavourful and their staff is always super friendly. It can get busy though so I would plan to go earlier in the night or make a reservation.

Booked for a Birthday party for 15 people due to the parade we got to the restaurant 30 mins late. good thing they didnt give away our spot which was good. The food was good! specially the pork belly!. The service was good and the waiter even helped us with the cake. The only downside was they took long to give us the bill because it got busy.  Overall, we were satisfied with the restaurant :)
Loved coming here for lunch. My go-to was the chirashi combo. Amazing food!

Nice place to go and hang out with friends or have dinner with your loved one. The staff are pleasant and friendly. They have a good selection of appys and drinks. We ordered chicken karage, squid rings (calamare), tuna tataki, takoyaki and some drinks. Nice Friday evening to end the work week. They have an automated ordering system where you use your smart phone to order and immediately pay for your order. Once youre done, you can just leave. They have a 2hr seating limit which is understandable in this current covid social distancing times. Btw, if you want patio seating, best to make reservations. They open up the patio ceiling/roof if weather permits.

Guu is where you go if youre not sure what you want to eat, but you want to have little bites of interesting, inventive food that isnt too far from your comfort zone. When I look at the menu I have no idea whats going on but everything Ive tried has been surprisingly delicious. I love this place! And of course the staff is extremely friendly and awesome.

Went there on Dec25th and they managed our reservation very well. So glad we found a restaurant opens on Xmas day. The only thing was we like to order 5 miso soup but there were only have 2 left. I understand it since it was a busy day. The Oden is delicious. Everything is in small portion so we can try wide variety of dishes. Polite staff, warm greeting.

name: Burnaby Palace Restaurant
description: Bright, classy space for traditional Chinese fare & dishes with a twist, plus online ordering.
address: Burnaby Palace Restaurant, 3110 Boundary Rd, Burnaby, BC V5M 4A2

detailed_reviews.review_text: Burnaby Palace is a nice hidden treasure situated on Boundary Road a block north of Canada Way. Their consistency with presenting solid Chinese cuisines is amazing given how long they have been in business. The restaurant has recently been renovated to look very clean and modern, offering a comfortable atmosphere for patrons. We ordered a number of fried and spicy dishes to try and all of them were exceptionally good. The braised beef was super tender yet flavourful. The fried squid was done just right to have a crunchy outer yet a chewy but tender inner. The green beans were fresh and cooked to perfection. The staff were very attentive to keep our teapot full while checking in periodically to ensure no empty dishes cluttered our table. For this level of service and quality of food, we would have expected much higher prices. Burnaby Palace is a wonderful value and a perfect hidden treasure to discover.

First time we tried this place  last November 3, 2023 for 20 people. Was totally impressed with the place. The atmosphere and food was great. We ordered food for 20 people and all of my families and friends were happy and and satisfied. Our server Peter was exceptional who went above and beyond in serving us. We will definitely be back for sure to eat at this wonderful Chinese Restaurant.

Excellent experience feeding a party of 35 people. We really relied on their advice for menu choices and quantities. Everyone was super impressed with the quality and variety. The restaurant packed the food in party trays that were easy to transport and easy to set up at our venue.  A great taste treat and easy option for hosting a a large party
How have I never been here before??? Holy smokes! Great food. Great service. I will be back. Thoroughly enjoyed the ginger beef. The shrimp dumplings were delicious too!

We go there about once a month for date night, also go there for Every family birthday celebration.  Food is always fast, hot, delicious.  You dont get just one server, All the staff serve you so you rarely have to wait for anything.  For birthday parties they provided the knife to cut the cake and even lit all the candles.  Best to make reservations, theyre always busy. The earlier in the evening the better.

I saw 5/5 stars with 700+ reviews and didnt think it was real. I was wrong. 18:52 arrived, smells good, open room so lots of talking carries, but not too loud. Told 15 min wait, but sat 5 minutes later. The servers were attentive the whole time without being intrusive. Complimentary tea. Big menu. Ordered at 19:03 and Wor won ton soup was served to us 6 minutes later.  About 15 minutes later the rest of our dishes started arriving. The prawns and cashews were light and had lots of extra vegetables. The ginger beef was a hint cumulaticely spicy and chewy in the best way. The mandarin pork was sweet forward then tangy. My boyfriend lived in China for a little over a year so weve only been to a Chinese food restaurant once before in the 10+ years weve been together. He says well be back.

Very nice modern decor and lighting inside which is a break from the norm of Chinese restaurants in the greater Vancouver area. Also have private rooms and an upstairs space for booking events/parties. Great service and easy to read menu items, and food was really good. The manager Wilson was also really good about greeting all the diners and checking on our meal. Will definitely be back!
Love this restaurant! Been going here for many years and it s never a disappointment! Food is delicious and the service is amazing. The staff is also really kind!
Amazingly delicious meal with fresh and quality ingredients, serene decor, and great service. The best meal out Ive had in a while, at a fantastic price.
Great, hot food, served quickly, friendly staff, front of house fluent in English. 2 large private party rooms available. Good prices. Very good wonton soup.

Wonderful service! Server knew each item on the menu like the alphabet. Food was hot, perfect size portion,  and most of all it was delicious! Best chinese food I have had in ages!      5 STARS THANK YOU BURNABY PALACE RESTAURANT
Great Chinese restaurant. Has been to go to since finding it. service is always excellent. You wont be disappointed!
Hands down best Chinese food in BC. If you havent tried it, you must. Promise you wont be disappointed Recommended dishes Green Beans w Spicy Pork, Chinese Food, Hot and Sour Soup, Fried
1001 Review! Ive been coming to Burnaby Palace for years and its my favourite Chinese Food Restaurant in the city. Large, delicious portions! I highly recommend!!
Awesome and delicious noodles experience, good service, really good quality and quantity Chinese food.

Great dining experience with friendly service and generous portions of tasty dishes. The private room was a perfect setting for a large family new years dinner.  The staff were incredibly helpful and friendly! I paid the bill and added a well deserved tip, not realizing tip was included in the total. The staff were so honest and came back to return the extra tip! Best lemon chicken in the city.
Our go to chinese place ,the best fried rice and beef and broccoli
Amazing food and fantastic service. Very reasonable price too. Cant wait to come back

Delicious Szechuan and Cantonese food under one roof. Although their take out food quality is great, their eat-in quality is superb! The portions are larger, the crispy noodles are crispier and the customer service is professional and polite. Burnaby Palace is undoubtedly a favourite of mine.

I cant order food from here as regularly as I once did due to my relocation, but for those in search of delectable Chinese fare, this place stands out! The staffs exceptional friendliness is also a bonus.

This is the best resturant .The food is to  die for .Absolutely delicious. The staff is incredible and very friendly .Top notch service .Love this place . Vegetarian options: Great selection of Very delicious vegetarian dishes . And they are accomadating to whatever you need .

Absolutely amazing food !!! Fast, fresh, consistent, large portions, very friendly staff and hands down they have the worlds best chili oil ! Wonton soup is so good .. shrimp spring rolls are my favourite and everything else on the menu!!! Will always order here!!

Very American style chinese food. I had cravings a few times so I got take out and they definitely do not disappoint. The food is high quality, fresh and tasty. Service over phone was great. The guy taking my order was really patient and nice.
Burnaby Palace is a culinary adventure fit for royalty!
Burnaby palace restaurant is definitely one of the better Cantonese style dishes in Burnaby..whenever I feel like some Chinese food it s always Burnaby palace
This place has by far the best chow main and stir fry 10/10 highly recommended i an addicted to ordering take out

Delicious dishes, very quick, friendly service, plus reasonable pricing. Parking is available in the back, as well as on the street. And if you have a larger party,  they have a separate room that can be reserved! A really lovely evening was had by all!
Great experience,  great food portions.  Great prices  and great great great did I say how GREAT  this place was
Always good. Always fresh-tasting. Attentive service.

Some of the best Chinese food Ive had in a long time. More than just the typical veggie options, too. Prices have come up a lot since covid, understandably. Some menu pics are out of date on price. Careful, dont make the same mistake as me. Had to call a couple times before they picked up the phone as it was right around the dinner rush, but once answered, the call was clear, concise, and polite, i felt confident my order would be correct when i picked it up, and it was.

Food is excellent and the service was fast and friendly. We ordered green beans with beef, the fried calamari and veggie chop suey and all three were amazing. Parking is limited and we had to find street parking.
Here are what yall must eat ! I highly recommend sweet sour deep fried pork
Good food to our liking, nice and clean, limited parking tho
Top shelf Chinese food in a small fun environment. I will go again
Best sweet and sour chicken balls in Vancouver. Excellent service. Very popular restaurant. Always enjoy eating here for lunch or dinner.
Always great food and service! It s my go to for Chinese! Was there yesterday, so good! Try the prawns and black beans!

Food was great, tasty and cooked well. Customers on nearby table all seemed to have been served well and enjoyed their respective dishes. It would be better to do reservations if you plan on dining out during weekends. Food assortment and pricing was relatively fair.
This is our go to restaurant for American Chinese food in the area. The food is consistently great. Portion sizes are quite good for most items. We always look forward to leftovers!

Food is good, excellent price, portions are big (I usually share a plate). Fried rice is so tasty. Ive never been to the restaurant, I order through Doordash app, and the food always came hot an well packed, its out new favorite place.
Very pleasant dinner, fair pricing, good service and tasty food.
smell good taste good yummy

Again great food and good portions. It did not disappoint. We had the sweet and sour chicken balls - crispy chicken breast meat in a lovely light breading, crispy ginger beef - just the right amount of heat and ginger, soft chicken chow mien - flavored well and perfectly cooked, the vegetables lotus - crisp and cooked delicious flavor, and mandarin sweet and sour pork - mild sweet and sour with garlic. All were excellently prepared and had unique flavors to the dish. Thank you Burnaby Palace.
Great dining experience. Friendly staff, good food and very accommodating team.
Only chinese restaurant I go to for past 30 years. No other place comes close to the high quality, tasty dishes they serve. Clean restaurant and friendly staff. The very best. Highly recommended.

Amazing Chinese restaurant, we tried chefs sea food platter with prawn dumplings and prawn shrimp rolls with seafood fried rice , they were super busy , we did not Have  to wait long , very fast , fresh and incredible customer service. Yeva and her group treated us really well . They served us extra chocolate to our family . Thank you very much for taking care of us . We will be back for sure!

I have admittedly been going here weekly. Prices are extremely fair. Food is fresh and delicious. Portions are big and worth the price. I have never dined in, only take out but they do great take out and packaging keeps food warm.
Absolutely amazing Chinese food, a lovely restaurant, and wonderful staff. Great place to eat in, or to get take out or delivery. You can call ahead for reservations. Highly recommend eating here.

My wife said this place changed her life. She is very picky but we both liked this place. The place is buzzing with people, the service is punctual and the food is freshly and properly executed. Lots of flavour in each dish. We had breaded lemon chicken, wonton soup, pineapple sweet and sour pork and chicken Chow Mein with vegetables. My fav. was the lemon chicken which I dont usually like. The chicken was fresh and moist while the breading was tasty and just the right amount. Yum
Been coming here for over 10 years with my family. Started from their old location. Great service, food is delicious. Food

We usually get our food delivered.  Their timing is pretty much right on time. The food quality is mostly excellent and the driver is cheerful and seems to appreciate the return customer.  He is truly fun and great at his job.  Amazing thing we feel is the food arriving hot. They are more than generous in their portions and we would recommend them for the finest Chinese food around.

Literally the best Chinese food in Burnaby! The staff are awesome and friendly, the food is fantastic, they have a huge variety, and everything tastes amazing. Personally my favorite is the dry garlic pork, it always makes me happy.
Always great food and giant portions.

Bright, good service, accommodating about allergies, top notch food. Three of us are five servings and had enough leftovers for one more meal. With generous tip, 5 dishes came to $29 per person. Ive been eating there for years, but the other two had not and were totally impressed. Three thumbs up
Our very favorite place for Chinese Food!! The whole family have been going here for years. We love them. So good.
Great food!! And terrific staff.
Great food great service great vegetarian options

My wife and went for dinner on a recommendation of a freind and we had the dinner for 2. Food was really tasty and staff very freindly, cannot wait to go again soon. Looking for a new place to eat try them out!!

Hats off to Wilson and Godfrey and the whole crew at BP.   its one of the constants in our little food universe where it doesnt matter what time you go, what you order, how much or how little your order, eat in or take out, you will always get a fantastic meal.... always.    A hidden secret:  their fried crispy chicken or Szechuan Fried Chicken with Garlic Sauce is the bomb.  took a few chinese food snobs to try it and theyre hooked... laughter.
So yummy! Weve been eating here forever and the taste has been amazing every time :) the staff are so friendly. Definitely one of our favourite places to eat!

Ive been coming here for many years and I ve never been disappointed. Friendly, welcoming staff, tasty dishes at reasonable prices. Dinner time can get busy and there may be a bit of a wait to get seated and served. That being said, just plan ahead so you re not starving!

Best Chinese food in BC. I hate to say that because it is already busy enough, but it is true. You can find individual dishes that are better elsewhere but the over all menu is great. You cant go wrong with there specialties they are a cut above. Our family has been going there for over 30yrs at this location and the old location. Whenever somebody is back in town thats where we always go.

Food is so good and the staff are super nice. Highly recommend. Parking is in the back but typically always full, which is a sign the place/food is good. Luckily theres street parking if the back is full. My go to order is always the Mandarin sweet and sour pork. So good.

Close proximity to my house. Very friendly delivery man.  Good prices! My girlfriend and I generally modify the dinner for 2 to have a $20 delivered meal that is more food than we can finish. The food is also delicious with an awesome NO MSG option.  I have heard from friends that the restaurant itself is very clean and inviting.

Food was great. Ready by the time they said it would be for pick up. Had a small mix up and got a whole container of broccoli instead of my black bean chicken, called them and they happily delivered it to my house. Really appreciate that they went above and beyond to fix that, shows they care about customer service. I will definitely order from here again

Our family has been coming here you years! We come here for the fresh food and great service. The honey garlic boneless pork is amazing! The hot and sour soup is great! The food is always hot and fresh and served with a smile. And they do delivery!!! Highly recommended!

They have delicious food, excellent quality and always cooked nicely! They are moderately priced and they will make 3/4 sized orders for cheaper upon request. The restaurant itself has a very nice ambiance and feel to it. Absolutely one of my favourite places to eat!

Had a great dinner at Burnaby Palace tonight.  We ordered their famous stir fried beans and ginger beef among several other dishes and found them to be well worth the recommendations.  Their fried rice reminded me of the good old days of Chinese restaurants.  The service was excellent as the restaurant us well staffed.  The seating was a little low on space but thats becoming the norm considering real estate prices/rents nowadays.  Next tune, we will definitely going to the side room with a little more privacy and space.
Good Chinese cuisine for sure! Good food and service. They scan vaccination QR code upon entering. You can reserve a small room for big groups. Parking is available at the back of the building.

Burnaby Palace has always been a favorite of ours. Their ginger beef is always a must have and theyre service is always ALWAYS great:) we held my daughters surprise birthday there and everything was perfect. The ones assigned to help us were great :)

I just wanted to leave a huge thanks and share our awesome experience from last night. We ordered some food online for pickup. The wife an I got mixed up who was going to pick it up, and both showed up home with without it. Hahaha!! It was 10 mins after they closed at that point, but we called them and they answered the phone. We explained what happened and the guy didnt hesitate to offer to deliver it right away. It arrived fresh, hot and tasty too. Very happy with the service and would absolutely order from here again! Thanks from Brent & Hilary.

I have always been interested in this restaurant as I live about 5 mins drive away. Tried them for the first time today and I can say that I have been missing out. Large serving sizes and extremely friendly staff. Free delivery for orders $20 + or 10% off for pick up orders! Will be coming back again very soon.
I ve driven past this place so many times on the way to the highway but never stopped.  Today I finally tried it out, great Chinese food, great service.  I ll definitely be back.
The BEST Chinese food on this side of the Pacific Ocean. You will not be disappointed when you eat here, but after dinning at Burnaby Palace, any other place will just not satisfy your taste buds.

Great prices and even better food. Cant wait to have again. Take out order due to covid but food was hot still once I got home. Had a little bit longer of a wait than I was told but I feel that was did to the immense amounts of orders they got. Food was worth the wait anyways

best chinese food i have ever had. tastes amazing, always served hot, tons of options and more than enough to share. almost always early with delivery, very friendly, nothing ever seems to be a problem. eating at their restaurant is even better with lots of seating (private or general) and attentive & POLITE staff! cant imagine anyone being disappointed!

By far the best Chinese food I have been to. Authentic Chinese cuisine. A lot of options, reasonable portion sizes and extremely good service! We even asked them to make items gluten free, and they actually did it! This place is awesome

Ill admit, I havent been here for a few years, but last time was just as great as any other time before! Food is delish (favs being hot & sour soup/ steam buns/ Shanghai noodles), big portions, friendly staff. Ive been a patron for as long as I can remember, about 30 years, my parents would take me as a child when they were at their old location. Old owners Winky & Danielle were the best, very nice people, let me walk around and come see them behind the counter as a child and it was our little tradition that they would always serve me a Shirley temple in my special cup - a funny pineapple mug :) and at the end they would bring me behind the cash register and let me pick out candies and fortune cookies from the big boxes they stored them in. I have very fond memories there, many family get togethers and celebrations. Its too bad to read reviews of bad/ rude service. Its on my to do list to eat there again in the near future.

Highly recommended old school style Chinese Food featuring house special spicy chicken, ginger beef, Mandarin sweet and sour pork and more. Very good quality, fresh and always busy takeout business. Very nice management and staff.

Best Chinese food in Burnaby! The staff here are so friendly especially the managers who do a great job remembering the regular customers and making a personal connection with them. One day I went in after losing my voice and one of the waitresses brought me over a lemon water to help me. Such a great environment and great food!

This is western Chinese food like I remember. Decent price, big portions, and above all fresh and delicious food. The server was fantastic and made the evening all the best with his humour a d great service. Will return often.

Wow! Havent ordered Chinese food delivery for more than four years. My friend just moved to North Burnaby area and we decided to look online to find the best place with most positive reviews, we quickly realized that Burnaby palace was voted #1 For very good reason. Its a Friday night we were very hungry and also very unfamiliar with ordering Chinese food for delivery, but as soon as the guy answer the phone we knew we were ordering from the right place. He was super friendly and very patient with my questions and was very knowledgable about all the dishes available. On top of that, the very considerate delivery driver called when he was five minutes away to let us know that he will be arriving soon, and he was such a nice man, very kind and very grateful that we ordered food from his restaurant. He sincerely hoped that we would enjoy the food that he brought to us In all of the 20+ years that Ive been ordering food for delivery, Ive never had such incredible customer service! Will be calling Burnaby Palace every time we crave amazing delicious Chinese food with impeccable customer service!
I love this restaurant so much! The food is delicious, customer service is wonderful, my food has never been delivered late... So I just keep ordering! Thanks for the good food!
Best asian food i always buy here! Great service! Winson and Jeffry are great! Recommend this restaurant to everyone you wont regret it!
Really high quality food, not greasy, but very savory.  Very clean venue with a peaceful atmosphere plus friendly staff as well.
Ive been getting take out from Burnaby Palace for years.. Love this place.. consistently great food.
Great food, very tasty, very good size dishes and portion for share Smells very good once you get in the restaurant The service was excellent Super nice staff, very attentive Favorite
Awesome food and authentic at the best prices ive seen in a long time.  Love the delivery app as well

We have been going to ths restaurant for the past 5-6 years. Dining in and pick up. Our favourite by far (for the dishes we buy) as we havent tried everything. Their house chowmein is so delicious. Lovely dine in area. This place is quite popular and can get extremely busy, especially on special occassions but so worth the wait. Excellent price for the quantity and quality of food. I only wish I didnt move to South Burnaby as Im outside their radius for delivery!
Probably the best chinese food around. I come from mission just for this hidden gem. Fried ginger beef, almond chicken, fried rice; its all top notch quality.

Excellent Cantonese style Chinese food.  Burnaby Palace has been a staple for authentic Chinese food for decades.   They use good  ingredients and the food quality is very consistent.   The place is always busy,  I recommend the dry garlic pork ribs and General Tsaos chicken.

Very kind Chinese owner or delivery man (?) delivered to our place. For some reason our online receipt order did not match with the address printed on the physical receipt, so they ended up having to travel an extra distance on top of it all (Sorry!). The food was delicious, thank you!
Great food, great service, and good prices!  What else could you ask for?   Highly recommended
The very best chinese food we come from Langley for great lunchs or dinner.  Try the Hot and Sour Soup, Special Chicken or any of their fabulous dishes.  So glad they are open again.
Great food! Excellent atmosphere! I am always tied up between ordering from here or the Chili Pepper House. If Im dining in, the Burnaby Palace is the place to go. Friendly staff and quality food.
One of our go tos whenever we visit our mother in law in Vancouver. Lemon chicken is one of the best in town and portions are decent for price. Wish there was one out in Langley!

food is delicious and they qre always very friendly and help full and i love that i can order on line.the spicey green beans are amazing the sweet and sour chicken and also the pork is so good and meaty not all batter and fatty.chicken fried rice is real chicken not that sandwhich meat kind so many things are so good
The food was excellent and well worth the reasonable prices on said food. The service was friendly and very attentive to our needs

Me my son and girlfriend ate here once and ordered from here once, food was awesome lettuce wraps, ginger beef, honey garlic pork, shredded chicken crispy cow mein, just a few things we had so far would gladly go back, I live close. Delivery said 45-60 mins took 20 so I was very satisfied
Food is always delicious and arrives hot.  Great menu and great delivery. Thank you for being there!
The service is fantastic. The food is fabulous. The tea always hot and fresh. The extras are always charming. It is a palace because of all those reasons. The orange chicken is to die for!

name: Guu with Otokomae
description: Bustling izakaya offering inventive Japanese small plates to go with sake, beer & unique cocktails.
address: Guu with Otokomae, 375 Water St #105, Vancouver, BC V6B 5C6

detailed_reviews.review_text: Had the steak, which was pretty good! Also had the mackerel, which is good. Definitely recommend this place, overall great food and service, as well at atmosphere, especially with the window seat! Food : 5/5

We came here as part of a food tour that goes through several places around the city. This place is very cool. We tried a dish that was fresh and yummy. We ll definitely come back soon to try the food

Salmon with 7 friends This was recommended by a friend, and I love it! Raw sockeye, 7 kinds of Japanese side dishes, natto, fried garlic slices, pickled radish, pickled plums, etc., mixed with seaweed and wrapped in seaweed, the taste and texture are very complex. If you cant accept natto, you may want to avoid it. Cheese Tofu SOOO delicious, with a little more honey and caramel sauce on top of the cheesy tofu I used to have, so it was sweet overall. Its dense but not greasy Sashimi Salad One of my friends favorite dishes. There are scallops and yellowtail in the sashimi. The large pieces are also very fresh. Surprisingly, there are shredded radish underneath, but I dont think the sauce is refreshing enough, its not Japanese vinaigrette, its mayo Tenderloin Beef Bibimbap Probably the most average dish in the whole place. Too little sauce, so some are bland. At the beginning, the rice is sticky if the eggs are not coagulated, and the dry and fragrant rice is more delicious when there is rice in the back.
Late night food here is the best. Hand written menus every night with the daily specials.

Visiting Vancouver we thought it best to tackle this cuisine and it didn t disappoint. It s a tapas-style menu, mostly small shareable dishes so take advantage of that with your mate. The only real criticism was the octopus was very over cooked other than that, the sashimi is what dreams are made of and the udon noodles were soft enough to sleep on.
If you wanna try a traditional Japanese food you have to try here, make sure you reserve before you go as they are usually full but still you can sit on the bar which is fun
I really enjoyed dinner here. I went on a Friday night and the vibe was great. Staff was very attentive. The food here is really good and a very decent price for the location. Can t wait to go back

Overall, nice experience. Its not highend, so dont go if you are looking for a highend izakaya. I love the food here and the price is reasonable. Their daily special is what gets me to come back time over time. I highly recommend this place if you are in the mood for some down to earth, asian izakaya dishes (not sushi. Although they do have some sashimi on their daily special menu). Happy hour ends at 5PM unfortunately. Wheelchair accessibility: Stairs stairs stairs. You wont be able to go to the bathroom in a wheelchair. Im not sure if there is an elevator for the dine in floor either
We ve tried all but one guu on Davie and this one doesn t disappoint.  Was not busy when we went in the morning which was great.  Food was tasty and enjoyed all the dishes we ordered.

Looking for a Japanese restaurant? You should try this out  Guu with Otokomae is an Izakaya restaurant (Japanese tapas) with traditional cooking with a modern touch in a wonderful bar. Also, if you are looking to taste some sake, this is the right place!
Great dining place for every kinds of occasional - from formal events to casual get togethers. The price-to-value is good given the quality and quantity. Highly recommended

All Guu restaurants are my favorite, and this one is no exception. I had a fantastic time enjoying some delicious food and drinks here. They do excellent small plates. The beer was light and crisp. Sake was beautiful, fruity, lovely aftertaste. The vibe in this place is perfect! Its fun without getting loud. Servers are fantastic and add much of its charm. I cant wait for my next Vancouver jaunt, and come enjoy this delicious restaurant again.
So I dropped by 10:15 and got out by 10:45, Food was good, waiter waitress were nice too. No complains, they have good promo. Got a sangria and multiple small plates of goodies
Good handled raw food. Though the octopus was a bit too much wasabi to me. Everything is good. The salmon used here is different.

This is one of my go-to places for dinner. Delicious foods and decent price. The mushroom and cheese bibimbap is great and kimchi udon is also pretty nice. If you are looking for a cozy, friendly atmosphere restaurant with decent foods and drinks, this is a perfect place to go!

Delicious experience. Food came out fast and it was all delicious. Would definitely go back for more! Highly recommend the Ebi Mayo. Huge, meaty pieces of ebi with a light crispy coating and a rich dipping sauce.
Generally been here many times , all the food quite delicious.

Must come here if you like Japanese (or just like trying new things). Very unique, never seen alot of the menu items before. And everything was deliscious and reasonably priced. Didnt have any but they have a large selection of sake by the glass and bottle.

I love their happy hour. It s $4 for Anahi glass and $5 for sangria. The combination of Asahi and karaage (5pc) is $10. Pitcher is $14. I also their service. If you are Japanese, just talk to them in Japanese. They are very friendly and nice!
We had the pork cheek, seared wagu tataki, takoyaki, chicken kaarage, grilled squid, pork and shrimp dumplings. All the plates were great. Service was quick and efficient. Great place!

Definitely recommend to always book in advance. Otherwise you might or might not get a bar seat.  However we enjoyed the bar seat. Food is served everywhere.  Waiters are nice and welcoming. The in-house beers are good. We ordered octopus, but it was hard to chew. The squid and pork belly were delicious.
I cant get over how polite the staff are here. I wasnt familiar with all of the dishes, but our server was more than happy to help. The food was delicious, and the dessert menu was amazing.
Attentive service with fresh food.  Nice vibe at lunch.

This location is alright.  I like the atmosphere of the original Guu on Thurlow more, but cant complain about Gastown Guu.  Great food, great service, great drinks. The only downside to this location is there are a lot of junkies in the area.
I love this place, foods are awesome. Daily handmade menu is so cute, the the freshest sashimi is so sweet and yummy. All the food are so great, it is a good place to go for dinner.
Every single plate we got at this restaurant was absolutely DELICIOUS. Great ambiance and fast service as well. I wish they had a location in California.
Great vibes and pretty chill place to hang! Guu Oromomae on Water Street is very progressive and served some rather experimental dishes. Staff are friendly and attentive. Recommended.

Came in for drinks and quick bites. I was able to grab a table before the dinner rush, hence the wait staff were very attentive and always topped my water. But noticed it started to get very busy around 7/8. Make reservations if you plan to come around dinner time.
A loft like bar style Guu restaurant that has daily special menu. There is a wide range of beverage on cocktail, wine, sake, beer, etc along with large variety of food for choosing
Always love this place. Excellent service. Food is great! Love their lunch specials. Everyday they have different lunch specials range from $10.50-$15.

Personally my favourite Guu location! I once had a birthday dinner here and they made so much effort to make it a special night :) I felt very safe and comfortable with the social distancing measures in place, and food was great as per usual!
My fav Japanese restaurant in Gastown. I am always super happy with the Japanese food and the service here. Great ambience too. Highly recommended.
The seating was little squished for a group dinner but delicious nonetheless! The portions are small and just right for sharing and getting a great varity. I recommend the plum wine.
Brie cheese covered with Panko was superb. Awesome Sapporo draft beer, and the Banana Tempura dessert was super tasty specially with the coconut ice cream

Been coming here for over 2 years fairly often. The food is always fantastic and they have a nice selection of Japanese single malts. Beer is cheap, best of all the staff are absolutely fantastic. Very attentive and quick to help. The menu is always new but keeps their staples, deep fried bananas all day! Thank you for the great good and amazing service!!!!!!!

Lunch special MUSSELS. Rich broth and garlic baguette. No sand and fresh flavor. Recommend. Service is friendly and very attentive. Lots of stairs and steps to go into the restaurant and restroom. Great food. Recommend for catching up with friends.

Went in thinking Id leave hungry but left surprisingly full. Had to ask what otokomae meant as the other guus were named after edibles. Apparently its because their manager is a good looking guy, otokomae means something along the line of handsome. I suggest getting the AAA new York steak Crockett? Its deep fried and o so good.
Very nice popular Japanese cuisine in Gastown. Mostly for drinks but decent food as well. Recommend trying when in the area.
Great menu selection, literally my dream menu with my favourite dishes
I really like this place in Gastown.  The food is yummy and price is reasonable.  I ordered two dishes and they surprised me with freshness and tastiness.  I will definitely come back for more.

Consistently good - love coming here for Japanese tapas. Ive been to this location at least 6-7 times now. Easy to book and usually room for walk-ins too! I almost always get the mushroom cheese stone bowl!

This is a great Japanese fusion restaurant located in  Gastown. They have many daily specials and I really liked the choice of hot and cold Sake. The Ebi-Mayo was a great choice along with some of the fresh seafood dishes. This place can get very busy so you may want to make reservations. I definitely recommend this place!!
The food is good. Nice setting and very friendly services.
Tasty food, great service. Great place to eat , enjoy beer and chat with friend.

Excellent Japanese restaurant. Prices a bit high but average for upscale venue, can get busy so reservations recommended. Absolute highlight is welcoming and amazing atmosphere and some of the best staff around for friendliness.
HAPPY HOUR 10CAD Sooooo yummy plus beer Sapporo
Perfect steak. Thank u chef
Had a fantastic time here. Restaurant had an aesthetic bar and a true Izakaya vibe that integrates western influence. Had the daily specials and Sapporo here. Highly recommend for a hangout spot
Good quality Japanese food with a reasonable price
This was some of the best food I have had. So beautiful and creative. Healthy and vibrant. The beer was so yummy as well. Thank you so much for squeezing us in! We loved it.
Always a great place to take your date. The menu has a great selection to choose from and each is unique. Nothing really ambiguous about it. Service is quick and friendly too.

We have been here a few times but our most  recent experience was particularly good. At first the menu looks a bit confusing. But persevere and you will understand the choices. It is a popular place and can be quite crowded in the evening. Reservation is recommended. We tried their steak this time. At medium rare it was soft and the seasoning was very nice. It comes cut in thin slices with a very nice sauce and fries. We also tried pan fried rock cod. It was delicious, cooked with a simple sauce in oil. They also have good beer. We had the IPA which went well with our food. We should be back here for the fish and steak.  Very nice.

10/10 excellent My partner and I ordered basically everything on the menu and it all tasted fantastic. Loved our window view of the street below. If youre hungry and have a big stomach youll be reaching for your wallet because either its all so delicious we had to have more, or the portions are small, or the ingredients are light on your stomach. One or all of those! We tried visiting again and they were booked up for the evening. Worth reserving.
Pretty good; it just tastes better - like Raisu but actually worth it - I even like their miso soup better than say your average sushi <insert_your_own_number> place.
Did takeout today but it was still very Guuuud!! :D

We dined here for the first time today and we were pleasantly surprised.  The service is great - friendly, helpful and attentive staff.  The prices are very reasonable and the quality of the food was exemplary.  We ordered deep fried shimp, and it was perfect - not overcooked, juicy, tasty and left us wanting more.  We will definitely recommend this restaurant to everyone we know.

We had finished working late at the tattoo convention and they stayed open a lil later to accommodate all of us. This was a great experience, very friendly staff and incredible food. It s all sharing Japanese style, so smaller portions but tastes amazing. We must ve ordered just about everything on the menu...twice. Drink selection is great and they always have some kind of special going on. If you re in the gastown area make sure to stop in here!

Fantastic place for groups! Everything is served in small portions and made to share. The food had so much flavor and there were so many different options. They also have a great beer selection! I will recommend making a reservation as they get pretty busy but its worth the wait.

First night in Vancouver after a never ending day of flight and driving. Wanted something unique and fun.  Found Guu in a search and decided to try it.  Great interior vibe and excellent staff.  Came in time for dinner menu & our server handed us a hand written menu,  with one page of many items,  which I prefer from a restaurant these days. Tried an imported rice beer, which was cold and light & my wife tried one of their cocktails. Ordered another one because it was a great drink.  Had the spicy agadashi tofu,  with an awesome sauce with just the right kick of heat.  I ordered the deep fried cauliflower with truffle mayo and the pork cheek and my wife orders the edamami and shrimp &  chicken dumplings.  Perfect portions and each dish was tasty and at the table under ten minutes.  Meanwhile they had great music in the background.  All in all,  I would recommend this place for couples and groups of friends looking to share unique dishes and partake of great cocktails in a great atmosphere.

This place had me as soon as walked through the door when I herd Lord Finesse banging on the sound system. If even if the food was bad which it WAS NOT! I knew I was going to enjoy my time in this establishment. The service was prompt the drink special was so good all I wanted was more. The food was cool tapa style dishes with Japanese flare the steak was meh cooked excellent but flavour could have used a boost. All other items we delicious done with care and intention. As the place filled up the music got louder and brought me back to my youth I could have stayed all night.  Highly recommend checking the slot out

It s a great place to go with friends for shared plates. There s always something everyone wants and the service is great! The tea has always been topped up frequently. I love that there are daily food specials and the price of drinks are alright as well. Plus, they take reservations.

Food is always delicious.  Even you end up ordering something that you happen to learn you dont like, they will work with you in order to make sure you have something you do like. My partner was a little dissatisfied with the cook on the Kuragi. He explained himself and what he expected politely to our server and they were sure to take care of us. The bar service is so excellent I cant imagine sitting at a table here. They have coat closets for you to hang your belongings in. (Though I wish they would get purse hooks.) Id give the place 10 stars if I could.
Wonderful dishes, nice soups. Welcoming and friendly staff.

My favourite Guu! The staff members are always friendly, attentive, energetic, and, yet, make you feel relaxed. I enjoy trying their rotating daily specials - the best was when they offered a melt-in-your-mouth grilled king salmon. However, their regular menu is the most solid and never disappoints. Our favourites include some of the classics, such as chicken karaage, ebi mayo, and yaki udon, as well as the sashimi salad, ikamaru, beef tenderloin bibimbap, mushroom and cheese bibimbap, and kimchi udon. Since the start of the pandemic, we haven t had many chances to dine in, but have been ordering takeout from Guu with Otokomae almost weekly! Our dishes are always packaged with care - hot food is separated from cold food, they fulfil special requests (such as omissions), and the staff even write thank-you notes on the boxes. Thank you so much, Guu Gastown!
Excellent pitchers of Sapporo.  Amazing fried, beef and their wasabi seems to be the real deal? Great experience overall

Always a great place to go for a casual atmosphere and delicious Japanese tapas / pub food. Good variety and options with the main menu as well as daily or weekly special menus. Bar seats are fun, nice layout with raised dining area and views onto Water street for a true Gastown ambience.

A fun menu with interesting dishes, really good drinks/cocktails and a vibrant atmosphere with great service. Would recommend if youre in the area for something thats not too casual but not too serious at the same time
Really awesome food and drinks. My sons favorite meal of the area! (Hes 8...)

Amazing place to go for dates, special occasions, or with a group of friends. The food is AMAZING and their daily specials on alcohol are really well priced. The staff are mega friendly. Make sure you get a reservation early as it is not a place you easily get a table in walking in.

Just an amazing resultant. The food was absolutely delicious. you HAVE to try the Panko fried Brie !!!!!!! Also loved the Guuu d yaki udon. Definitely will go back soon, super glad we have one in Toronto too
Amazing staff and food. Great place!

My partner and I love coming here, especially during a cold day for hot sake. The food is awesome! We had a salt brined fish the server used a hammer to reveal and pork cheek. For dessert their creme brulee is my favoriteeeeee - my dinners here remind me of good memories :)

We arrived on a Saturday evening expecting to wait since we didnt have a reservation, but luckily they happened to have a table available. My friend ordered the amberjack sashimi and they were accommodative enough to make the udon vegetarian for me. The food was excellent and so was the ambience. The restaurants location is quite enviable too as it has window side seating with views of Gastown.

It is hard to decide which I enjoy the most... The bamboo leaf cocktail is like some kind of other worldly lychee heaven. It is at least as delightful as the ikamaru grilled squid, which you can only order after 5 pm. Please try them.
they did an EXCELLENT job managing the new social distancing rules. i felt completely comfortable and safe. The waiter had all of the new processes down pat, and the food was great as usual!
Food and service was fantastic!! Cheesy tofu is the best dish Ive ever ordered in my life. also sashimi was mind blowing:)

I love all the Guus and this one is not an exception.  When I am expecting a bigger group I like to get a reservation at this Gastown location because it is more spacious and less loud.  Service and food is great, just a more formal atmosphere.  Ive always lucked out and was able to get a table here when needed.  Maybe it is less noticed because it is hidden inside another building.  Go early before they sell out of the specials!

Sharing food here with good company is one of my favorite things in the world. They really can t do no wrong. We always get some chicken karaage, takoyaki, takawasa and try a lot of new things. For the quality of service and food this is really one of the best value places you can eat and have a great evening with friends.

The food is all good. Ebi mayo is really good. But the staff and service is amazing I have them five stars because their service and atmosphere put them over the top. Otherwise it would be four. The music is unreal and the staff are such good people.

The food and cocktails are legit. The melon cocktail is a dangerous drink. I think we ate about 5 different things because I kept wanting to try as much as I could. Will definitely go back and try more next time Im in Van.
I had the Guus yaki udon. You could smell the umami as soon as the dish was brought out. Tasted fantastic and service was incredibly fast.

My boyfriend took me here for my birthday yesterday....and it was fantastic! We started with drinks...he had the sake mojito and I had the white sangria....wow! They really know how to mix drinks! We ordered and shared the tsukemono and spicy agedashi tofu. The pickles were expertly done...nice, light and crunchy. The agedashi tofu was   and tasty!  Next came our panko crusted brie and the sashimi salad...salad was so tasty and refreshing....  the brie was amazing! The ebi mayo....well...talk about huge juicy prawns!!! Yummm! We finished with the green tea ice cream with kinako kuro-mitsu....delish! Thank you to our wonderful server and all the friendly staff at Guu Gastown! We will be back!

This restaurant is one of our  go-to  places for the best and most innovative izakaya menus in Vancouver. Also, crazy cocktails and an ever-changing selection. Great for special occasions or a quick late night meal. Look for the tiny sign  on Water Street, up some stairs, and be greeted with a shout!

I love Izakaya and this place really hits the spot. Its great for having drinks with friends with shareplates to go between everyone. However, that doesnt stop 2 people from going in and having a massive feast. The agadashi tofu was great, takoyaki better and the tonkatsu was perfect. I come here whenever I can - especially if a friend is coming to town looking for good drinks and solid food.
Unexpectedly affordable and delicious Japanese food for where it is located and the interior atmosphere and design.

The food was a little bit cold when it came out, but it was delicious. The staff are friendly and the price is quite reasonable for Japanese restaurant. It is a little noisy because its an Izakaya, but if you are looking for a place to have drink and spend a good time, this is your place.

I was catching up with Calgarian friend for lunch and decided to bring him here for Japanese food. We ordered Tako Wasa ($4.90), Spicy Agedashi Tofu ($6.80) and Sashimi Salad ($11.80) and they were all fresh. Tako Wasa was good, but taste of wasabi was  a bit strong. Agedashi Tofu was yummy and so was the Sashimi Salad. Sashimi Salad tasted citrusy and refreshing it came with daikon noodle and some kind of cornflakes (or something crispy). Im not sure if the menu changed at all, but it had so less selections from what I got at Guu Garden last time. Service was fast. Guu Otokomae is definetely a good place for a hangout or a date night.
Best Yaki udon Ive had, and a really good Bibimbap. Fantastic value for the money! Always a Guud choice

Excellent food well presented with faultless service. If you like McDs you will not appreciate this place. The food is exotic and unusual. Spicy, savoury, succulent and sometimes unfamiliar.  A wonderful experience

i love all the Guus in the Vancouver area and have been to all of them with this store being my favorite! Their dishes are delicious, service is friendly and drink selections are great. Mushroom and cheese bibimbap and Kimchee udon are a must-try.

Yummy izakaya. Especially recommend the hearts and gizzards (a daily special during my visit), takoyaki, and hot stone pot dishes. Daily special had seriously good eats. Beer and drinks selection were also excellent.
Tried at least 8 different dishes, all were delicious. Food came out surprisingly fast and our server was friendly and helpful. I would definitely go back.

Hubby and I have tried just about everything on the menu and only ever been mildly disappointed once. Try the salmon and seven friends! Its a wonderfully delicious experience!  Great atmosphere, love their callbacks!

Everytime I go here I feel right at home. From the warm welcome at the entrance to the farewell at the end this place is amazing for drinks with friends, or Japanese food, recommend the Beef udon and chicken Karage. Also if you get a chance try to talk to the manager and bartender Jon, he is such a cool dude and delivers excellent customer service everytime I go there. Arigatou Guu!
In love with this place. Great food and drinks accompanied with the best old school 90s R&B is definitely my jam. Wicked vibes this place! Service is good. Very unique restaurant!

Definitly try their cheese and mushroom bimbimbap! The server mixes all the ingredients very evenly so every bite is tasty! Also the waiting time is fairly short even during weekends since they have plenty of seats. Service and food are nice
What a great experience. The food was fantastic. From the Bluefin and Amberjack Tuna, to the Kobe Beef and the brothless ramen. Service was friendly and attentive. Cocktails were also pleasing.

Of the many great Izakaya Restaurants in Vancouver, Guu is our favorite.  Of the three Guus in Vancouver, Guu with Otokomae in Gastown is, by far, our favorite.  In fact, it is our favorite restaurant in a city of great restaurants.  Everything weve had there, every time we went there, has been AMAZING! On this latest visit, we started with Takowasa.  Small pieces of raw  baby octopus legs were mixed with wasabi stems and served with nori to be wrapped.  A unique and wonderful taste and textural experience not to be missed. The Spicy Agedashi Tofu is absolutely the best weve ever had.  Small one-bite cubes of tofu is battered and deep fried, then bathed in a dashi and topped with pure goodness.  The batter is so light and thin that it serves mainly to hold the great flavor-packed dashi onto the tofu.  We slurped every bit of the fantastic dashi after finishing the tofu. The Spicy Shrimp and Pork Wontons were amazing.  The skin was a perfect al dente and the shrimp and pork filling was delicious.  With the spicy sauce, it was complete. Just when we thought that the meal was a complete success, along came the Black Cod.  It was grilled and presented in a white wine Saikyo miso sauce.  It was the most delicately textured, delectably flavored piece if fish that weve ever had. This restaurant goes on our Best Anywhere list, and we vow to come back on every visit to Vancouver.
Ordered 10 dishes between 5 people and everything was great. Left there feeling completely satisfied without being overstuffed. Really enjoyed my experience.
A very interesting kind of dining! I didnt really know what I was eating at times, but it was so delicious that I didnt even care! Also, one time I saw Chris Pine leaving this restaurant.
