name: Come Along Chinese Seafood Restaurant
description: Bustling dining spot with bright decor, featuring familiar dim sum options & Chinese dishes.
address: Come Along Chinese Seafood Restaurant, 2550 Kingsway, Vancouver, BC V5R 5H2

detailed_reviews.review_text: Good food. Service was great.  Will go back.
Like other dim sum restaurants, this place offers the classics at a great price.

Dim sum is really good here, big portions and lots of variety. They can also seat 10-12 guests at one table comfortably, me and my family of 12 come here for dim sum occasionally and the service is great every time.

Food is excellent, some dishes are very unique, services is good too, but the best thing is the price. Must come more often. The only thing is the parking is limited at the back and is not easy to get parking on the street.

Come Along is a decent and ideal Chinese restaurant for family dinners.  A good size restaurant with many large tables (seat 12 guests comfortably).  It is generally quite busy for lunch and dinner, but they do take reservations.  They have limited parking in the back, so its mostly street parking. The dishes are of generous portions and well prepared.  The service is prompt.  Over-all, a good restaurant for a decent family/group meal.
One of my favorite Chinese restaurant. Have been here many times in past over 10 years. Food and service always good.
Dim sum here is pretty bomb! Not only the size is bigger than normal, but their quality is quite good! Definitely recommend! :) gogo
Good food, lots dim sum and Chinese food to choose. Good service. Parking: Rear parkings and street parkings are convenient. Food : 5/5 |
My Dad is a regular here. The food is pretty good. Much like most restaurants, some days better than others. The service is solid and the atmosphere is old school. I like the place.

Very excellent authentic dim sum. Flavors are more full bodied and flavorful ( maybe MSG ? Lol) But everything is pretty good I like it a lot. Price is good! Try their cheung Fun s. Very good and smooth. Rice pots are softer mushier rice but flavor is good.

You cant go wrong with this place! Affordable prices, fresh and hot dimsum. Everything was flavourful. The sauces arent diluted like some cheap dimsum places. Portions are great. And lots of options!!
Great restaurant with attentive staff and delicious food. Easy to recommend!! Food : 5/5
One of my favorite places for dim sum in Vancouver! Great prices and the yummiest food! The golden tofu and dee fried squid are a must!

Dim sum is good and always feel welcomed here. Big portion, great selections and fair price. Environment is not the best but okay for the price. They use single-use table cloth so pretty clean. Our go-to place for dim sum on weekends.
Best dim sum in Vancouver. Authentic places are closing down and replaced by  luxury dim sum  but this place is still very authentic and delicious

One of our go to dim some spots. Excellent food and large servings. We recently just started going back to dine in. Over the past couple years weve been doing takeout. Never a bad experience. Parking: Lots of free parking around the restaurant.
Fantastic Chinese food for a good price. Great place for big gatherings. Service was fantastic. A gem in vancouver. My family love coming here.
Very delcious dimsum , pretty pricey but quality is very good.
Very good food.  Pleasant and helpful staff.
Great dim sum at reasonable prices

I am so glad this restaurant still exists.   Not many left.   No fancy decoration, no fancy waitresses, no fancy dishes.  Just good good Cantonese food. Not Cheap at all... I would dare to say pricy. Full House on a Saturday night.  That says something. Definitely a repeat.

This place is a very underrated Cantonese restaurant in the area. Lot of friends said its not good but I went there recently and their food was actually really good, better than a lot of restaurants actually.

Though we couple arrived late 8:15 pm, the server was so cosiderate with good service. And by her good suggestion we had very nice experience, the grouper ball with Choy sum and black bean steamed grouper were so delicious. Thank you lady for your good suggestion and service.

My family comes here for dim sum a lot as its close by.  There is always an insane wait out the door on weekends after 10am, as with all other dim sum places in Vancouver.  I dont believe they take reservations for dim sum.  I am always trying to find places that do!  We really like the deep fried squid tentacles here as they are lightly floured and fried, without the heavy batter that some other places do.  The usual dim sum staples can be found here, at the standard prices, and the usual service as other dim sum places.   Its just an easy neighborhood low key place for us to go for dim sum.   Tables are VERY tight inside, so its tough to navigate around the tables sometimes, they really squeeze them in there.  There is parking along Kingsway in the front.
I love this place! Family has been going here for years. Came back here for Mother s Day and it was as good as I remembered it. Portions are big and food is delicious!
Very tasty dim sum and efficient service. Got there around 11 and there was lots of room but by 12:30 it was packed.  Will definitely return

The first time we were in the area around lunch time, we didnt even notice this restaurant. So we ended up eating fried chicken nearby out of desperate hunger :-0. Then I researched the area on Google maps and found Come Along. After looking at the helpful food pictures online, I decided that we should try it next time we are in the area. I had to convince my partner to walk in because the lack of activities and people outside gave us the impression that it cant be that good. We were really surprised after we got past the front door. The place was not that big, but buzzing with activities. Lots of people eating their lunch happily. And these people looked like they are regulars. The interior even looked fresh and new. We ordered a simple lunch of fish congee, fried Chinese donuts, tofu skin with baby bok choy in vegetable broth, and shrimp dumpling. The congee was delicious. They used cod filet which was very tender. The Chinese donut was reheated so that was disappointing. The tofu skin dish was very good also, the har gow were huge. We returned for dinner another night with 5 friends. We tried Peking duck, there was duck meat attached to the skin which my friend said is the Cantonese way of doing Peking duck. The skin was crispy. The pancake was freshly made, but a bit on the thick side. They had a special on rock cod. We order a 2 lb one. It was excellent! We were all surprised how tender the cod was, usually, rock cod over 1.5 lbs tend to be on the tough side. We ordered two kinds of tofu; egg tofu with steamed dried scallops, and braised tofu with vegetables. I was not impressed with the braised tofu, it seemed dried and pre-made. The egg tofu was fine. I think we didnt necessarily pick the right mix of dishes. I did, however, see a lot of interesting dished coming out of the kitchen to other tables. The manager was friendly and helpful, and the service was pleasant. It was a Monday night, so we avoided the crowd. We intend to return to explore other dishes.

Very good  food that is reasonably priced and the staff are helpful and friendly. I have been frequenting this seafood restaurant for months and am fully content. My home away from home meal eating, I recommend this place to everyone. Seat reservation is advised.
Best weve found in town! Been here dozens of times, everything is always fresh and reliably tasty! Top notch.

Good food,  little busy...  Waited for about 10 min even though with reservation but understandable sometimes customers take a bit longer to leave.   Over all worth the wait.  Busy but service was prompt.
Very good! And lots of yummy food! Recommend!! Also, this restaurant is nearby my house so I will just takeout during the pandemic. ;)
Mid range Chinese restaurant.  Dim sum Ok but not particularly outstanding. Friendly efficent staff. Crowded both at lunch and dinner time. Very limited parking
Always good here. Large portions. Favourite orders: deep fried calamari, wasabi free range chicken, chicken fried noodles.
Good food, good price, free parking on the street, very busy.
I really like their deep fried squid, although it has been a hit and miss the last few times. Overall I still like coming to this place
Friendly staff and good dim sum. Very loud inside - but thats usually a good sign of good food.
Good Chinese restaurant in east van on kingsway. Great for large groups. Dim sum is good. Price is reasonable.
Awesome dim sum! The servers are so amazing and treat us like home.
Always come here for delicious dim sum and friendly staff that remember their patrons.
The price is reasonable. The food is good. The servers are very friendly.
Ho sek! So yummy
Food quality are stable, good service, price is reasonable, good for family gathering.
Good food and has sanitize  for customers before  get in restaurant  excellent
this is the very special restaurant,i always referral my clients to eat there,because i like a lot of special dishes there
Good foods but next order for lunch pls tell customer after 10 Am service Ty
Great place for take out dim sum with discount!
Good, reasonable priced dim sum. Efficient service. Covid protocols in place.
Very friendly counter staff and the food is delicious
Excellent Dim Sum, always very consistent, great value.
Delicious dim sum and food. Wont be disappointed.
Good service and good food! The goose feet are so good!
Good food,  fair price,  comfort place.
good food good service in reasonable price.
Good quality and fair prices
This is my favourite place for dim sum!
Foods are delicious and prices are reasonable
Very good dim sum there.
Has Yellow Tapioca pudding.  I highly recommend it.
Food is very good and fresh.
Good food N price
Excellent Seafood place
Best dim sum
Very good food.
very good
Good dim sum
I love it .
Great food
Really good meal
Foods..........yummyyyyyyyy.
Good food
Great food

Golden Dragon Boat     is now open  The parking lot behind it There are only 14 stations under gazebo  The distance between all stations is more than two meters The boss is very conscientious Very good service from the staff But I hope customers respect the neighborhood and the others customer.  The parking lot has been changed to [special]! Please do not park in places where you should not park to hinder others   self-respect
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: 14  under gazebo respect the neighborhood and the others customer.                !                     self-respect

detailed_reviews.review_text: Due to the epidemic, the number of diners at lunch is no longer what it used to be. But the attitude of the employees remains high. Many people come to pick up takeaway food. 30 yuan for a vermicelli meat crab takeout is really good.
Full of color, flavor and taste
The dim sum is big and delicious, just right.
The production is okay.
have different food
Get big items with your food!

name: Kalvin's Restaurant ( Song Lin Ju  )
address: Kalvin's Restaurant ( Song Lin Ju  ), 5225 Victoria Dr, Vancouver, BC V5P 3V4

detailed_reviews.review_text: If you crave for authentic Taiwanese cuisine, Kalvin s is the place to go. Had them weekly since I was a teen and twenty years later they stay magnificent! Their pre-order specials are all awesome, especially Pork shank in brown sauce, minced prawns wrapped in lettuce, fish head in chili hot pot Anyways, you won t regret it! They are however cash only.

Extremely authentic Taiwanese foods they served here! The three cup chicken and braised pork dishes are my personal favourite as the meats are flavourful and succulent. In addition, the cooked luffa with clams is another signature dish as it s very appetizing and refreshing; a perfect dish for the summer. Last, the staffs are super friendly as well. Great place to dine for sure.

Drove by this place so many times and finally gave it a try. Have to say I ve been missing out. This place serves some pretty amazing food. The restaurant is a bit small so go early if you don t want to wait in line (or make reservations).

Small but very popular place! Was told serves northern Taiwanese style foods. We had pork belly, fish, hot pot, and a couple of different of of veggies and they were all really good. Very highly recommended!

Being there for so many times, definitely one of the best and authentic Taiwanese restaurants u can get in Vancouver. The service is always so good, and all dishes are unique and made with strong wok flavour.   very addicting as well, be aware to get hooked on going back there over and over. They have really good value to lunch combo too. Highly recommend it. Oh yeah, and have to call to make reservation as the restaurant is quite small.

The best Taiwanese restaurant in the city. From the moment I stepped in, I was greeted with warm and attentive service that set the tone for the rest of the evening.  Each dish that graced our table was a masterpiece in its own right. The menu showcased a diverse range of options. Every bite was a burst of flavor, meticulously crafted and beautifully presented. The ingredients were undoubtedly fresh and of the highest quality, reflecting the chefs dedication to delivering an exceptional dining experience.
Awesome Taiwanese food, so much better than I expected! It s relatively cheap too! Taste is well balanced, not too salty/sweet. Love it!

We ordered a couple of dishes and they were all delicious!     and    are all one day pre-orders, so make sure you call ahead to secure these dishes for your meal. The     comes in this gigantic pot so make sure you are sharing with a group. Would definitely come back for other menu items. The    was yummy and fun to eat.
The dishes are all tasty!!! Recommend      and     Better to make a reservation. It s always full of customers and we have waited for ~30mins for a table. Also they only accept cash.

Great food with a reasonable price We ordered two rice two dish and a soup, they all taste amazing. It bring me back to the memory of having these dish in Taiwan, tastes just like how it is in my memory. Highly recommend calling in to make reservations, we waited 30 minute but it is worth it.
Definitely one of the best Chinese restaurants in Vancouver, everything is above standard!! Service is exceptional, price is good as well. Will come back to try other dishes

Looking for Szechuan food and came across with this place. The pricing is pretty fair, but I would say the food are more leaning toward Taiwanese taste than Szechuan. Out of the six items we ordered, I would recommend the - special fried noodle with seafood, pork, and vegetables - spicy Pork Ear The rest are: - chicken with chilly sauce (photo) - Fondue with fish in spicy sauce (mild)(photo) - Pig Intestine with 5 sauce - soup dumplings Total bill is around $65.

insane food here, taiwanese flavour is delicious amazing and spot on. no words to describe how much i love the food in this restaurant! definitely very busy as there were many take outs and only two workers. i also think the price is very affordable as well. definitely a must try taiwanese cuisine if you re near the area

A small clean Taiwanese restaurant with 7 dining tables, offering delicious food and superb service. This is the only restaurant we felt comfortable dining out during the covid period. Now we come here nearly once a week, love their pork&pickle noodle soup, pork stir-fry in garlic chilli sauce, soup dumplings, hot and sour soup, beef pan cake ..

Ive been coming here for at least a decade. As a Taiwanese person, believe me when I say Kalvins is the best place in Vancouver for Taiwanese food. Most Vancouver Taiwanese restaurants serve more trendy and street-food focused dishes, and not things that Id eat at my grandmas table. Kalvins is the only place in Vancouver that Ill go to to eat food that reminds me of home. The owners are Taiwanese, and theyve been running the restaurant for 15+ years. Everything is delicious, and I would highly recommend trying dishes youve never heard of. Everything is family style and larger portions, so make sure you go with a group of at least 4. It is cash only, and parking is a bit of a challenge, but these are things I definitely dont mind when the food is that good. Reservations are recommended as it is a small restaurant with limited tables.

Top quality food, polite service as always. This place is a favourite, and we drive out from Richmond to come here. The three cup chicken is a must (I have tried many in this area and so far, they make the best three cup chicken in all Vancouver). They also make a mean spring onion pancake that would pair really well with just about anything. They also make their own wontons, gyozas and baos that you can can buy frozen to eat at home.
Every dish is delicious. Everything here looks simple but it tastes absolutely different than what you made at home. Their tomato fried eggs is the best. Staffs here is very friendly as well.
This is a great restaurant that offers great food.  Lots of choices, and free instruments.  This is one of those restaurants that you will eat first before you remember to take photos.
Very authentic Taiwanese cuisine. Been eating there 20 years, keep up the good work

Super tasty! Always enjoyable experience eating at Kalvins; friendly staff, great food, and fridge of frozen dumplings you can buy to take home. Recent menu highlights for me were the squid with garlic and chili, Shanghai dumplings, and hot and sour soup.

This maybe the oldest Taiwanese Restaurant in Vancouver. Food was tasty and authentic! Came here to eat with my family and friends since 2011. If you just want good Taiwanese food and not care too much about the decor, you should give it a try
Taiwanese fusion Szechuan food. Service was really good. Nice and polite Taiwanese courtesy.

Honestly the best place to find some authentic Taiwanese dishes!! Our favourite is forever their pork blood and intestine (    )! If you are into dishes with intestine, they have a few! They also have frozen dumplings, wheel cakes and buns as well if you want something to go. Always make a reservation as they are super busy all the time and they don t have a lot of seats. Recommend take outs as well if you want more space. They pack your food nicely and even provide a little cardboard box for ease of carrying! Gotta love the service when they are so so busy already.

Great size! Eight tables (so call ahead to make sure you get a spot) Good variety. Friendly staff. Efficient kitchen. Tasty Taiwanese Szechuan dining. . Our perennial favorite dishes: crispy salty peppery chicken, beef noodle soup, and beef roll (gotta eat the beef roll while its still warm - so goo-ood)
Food is delicious bur it s too busy, feel like they need more staffs
Great authentic Taiwanese dishes. Good prices. Highly recommend.
I love themmmmm they are the best the staff are super nice I ve been coming back here several times over the last 10 yeafs

Ive been to Kalvins a bunch of times over the past 20 years and the food is sooo good.  The owner is such a nice guy,  always made my friends and i feel so welcome.  I now live over an hour away and its still the only place i go for Szechuan.
Food was flavourful and reminds me of Asia.

Ordered hot and sour soup, fondue with fish in spicy sauce, shredded beef with bamboo shoot, chicken with three spice, fried Taiwanese cabbage, and onion pancake stir fried with beef (not on the menu). All dishes were delicious- clean plate club.
Authentic Taiwanese cuisine, you must call ahead to reserve a table cause the restaurant has  only minimum tables available and its a very popular place for dinner.
The eggplant dish was fantastic. The Chinese staff were so kind, they smiled and came over to guide us. I commend them for their service. Vegetarian options: Eggplant food

The place to get classic legitimate taiwanese food. Dont get tricked by the exterior, it is not a place you want to pass on. The original chef of this restaurant trained many other chefs in the lower mainland when it comes to taiwanese food. Unfortunately he has retired, even though the food took a slight hit, it is still quite a big better than any competition in Vancouver.

Wow cant complain. We ordered 3 dishes and every dish was super delicious. I was even more surprised about how amazing their service was. Though it was busy they worked quickly and was very attentive to each table. Made sure we were taken care of. Gave them 5 stars because it exceeded my expectations. Perfect food, perfect service. Oh but make sure you have cash, they do not accept card.

My gf always makes me try food from her home country Taiwan, and Kalvin is definitely one of the favorite ones! Food is delicious and staff is helpful. I wish the price was more reasonable and that they accepted other payments besides cash

My favourite Taiwanese restaurant in Vancouver producing consistent food for years now. The intestine and pigs blood stew and Taiwanese style stir fried clams are a must, but there are lots of other great options on their menu. Portion size is also great.

Most ethnic Taiwanese food in lower mainland.  Features are written in the menu and can never go wrong.  Staff is very friendly and honest about their food, she recommends another veg dish because the one we order was not in season.  Dumplings are made to order and recommend the beef roll.  Small restaurant so gets filled up very quickly.

Most authentic Taiwanese food you can ever try in Vancouver. There are too many dishes to recommend especially when I would literally recommend the whole menu. Kalvin the owner is definitely the reason people have been coming back to this restaurant for 25+ years. I would highly recommend this restaurant to everyone. This is our familys favorite restaurant, a MUST visit!

Came here with high expectations and I have to say that they truly delivered. The food was delicious and authentic, the portions were huge. The staff made you feel that you were a regular for 20 years. A super small place however it is still not very known about yet so we got a table very easy. Highly recommended!!
Really delicious Taiwanese dishes. The special dishes that need pre ordering are especially good! Napa cabbage soup is an explosion of flavours

Yummy! Yummy! Yummy!  A small, clean and very welcome restaurant. The lady who runs the place is incredibly helpful and friendly. Been there twice. Loved the food. Substantial portions. You can buy bags of frozen dimsum to steam at home. Highly recommend this place.
Authentic Taiwanese dishes. Delicious and recommended.

Been there since 1998. Excellent Taiwanese and Taiwanese style Schezwen food. The owner is really friendly and would sit down and chat with you no matter where your background is. Now I only wish the owner doesnt retire because still cant find the any Taiwanese food as authentic as his.

The best food in Vancouver. Period. Taiwanese/Szechuan fusion. Small restaurant, so reservations are recommended. Reasonable prices, and again, incredible food. Never had a bad dish there. Personal favorites are the pork blood and intestine fondue, and the Taiwanese style intestines.
Always delicious authentic taiwanese food.

The place doesnt offer a lot of seating and its usually very cramped when you do have a table. That said, it offers a true Taiwanese flavours. Its one of the must go to restaurants when my parents come to visit from Taiwan.

Small homey Taiwanese restaurant. My Taiwanese boyfriend loves coming here. He raves about it all the time and says the food here reminds him of Taiwan. Very tasty! Make sure you make a reservation! We always buy a bag of housemade dumplings with us after were done eating.
Owners son here. This place is my fathers lifes work, who has literally broken his body for; in his heart, his nervous system in his arms, physically, emotionally and psychologically.

This is the pearl of Asian restaurant. It s small but always packed. Make sure to call before go. Dishes are delicately prepared with excellent skill and good quality materials. Highly recommend to anyone who love Chinese foods.
Oh my god where have you been all my life. Amazing food

This is not a typical Sichuan restaurants. It s Taiwan style Sichuan food. The focus is not pure spice, instead, the chef lets the natural flavour of the food shine through Been coming here for about 7 years, the taste hasn t changed. Same chef, same food
Food and service is top notch for this small establishment.
Very good food, small place!
Went there by chance with my Taiwanese friends. We all enjoyed the food a lot. They say the food is very authentic and in good taste. Staff was good too.
Favourite place in Vancouver for Taiwanese food. Serves some of my favourite Taiwanese dishes and does them very well. Always busy. Closed on Wednesdays.  Reservations recommended.
A hidden gem in the south van. Traditional Taiwanese Chinese food. But it s cash only.
Delicious and authentic Taiwanese food! Staff is super friendly. The cold cucumbers and Taiwanese pepper chicken is amazing.
Our favorite Chinese restaurant. Always make a reservation because theyre usually busy and limited tables. Everything weve tried on the menu has been tasty.

I haven t had a chance to eat there yet but I just picked up an order I am in Uber eats driver they immediately sent me down gave me tea told me the exact time the food was going to be ready and they were awesome that s that s service. Out of over 2000 deliveries that s the best I ve ever been treated at any restaurant

Actually the best service I ever had in Vancouver. And one of the best food as well. Their entrance was dark in night, so we were hesitant to enter for the first time. It s really hidden gem restaurant.
The staff were super friendly and made some great recommendations. The string beans with pork are amazing, as well as their chicken with three spice.
Food is amazing! Very small though, kinda want to keep this place a secret or else it will get super packed, but the food is too good to not recommend and this place deserves the recognition!
Girlfriend ordered pork sauce on rice and didnt finish it. She asked to take out the rest and the lady asked if she wanted to add more sauce to the rice. 10/10.
no better place for Taiwanese standards. Hard to explain just how delicious the fried vermicelli is. Service is also invariably friendly and efficient.
So many yummy Taiwanese dishes.  Attentive service.  Only downside is that it is a very small/tight restaurant, but I think it adds to the character of the restaurant.
All the food that I ordered were delicious and well balanced i think it s very comforting food nothing was very over whelming overall this place is amazing

A small, busy restaurant with a great menu. Its hard to order something thats not good. Xiao long bao is a must. Staff are very mine. The place is really small and always crowded, a reservation is recommended.
5 star all the way! My new favourite Chinese restaurant.
Food is always fresh and amazing, family has been eating here for many years. They make their own dumplings and noodles!
Great taiwanese place (Im not taiwanese so take this with a grain of salt). I like: salted duck egg chicken fried rice, red fermented deep fried pork, and pork organ stew.
They provide really good service. Food is taste good. Specially the deep fry bun. Will recommend friends to go and try out .
Great place and excellent food at a reasonable price.  Very friendly staff too. Gets crowded during peak periods so timing is important.
Best Taiwanese restaurant in Vancouver
Their Gua Bao is legit - identical if not better than the street food version I had in Taiwan. They recommend reservations.
It was my first time coming here with friends, and the food was phenomenal, like literally ranked and the service was fantastic!
one of the best Taiwanese restaurants. there duck is sooo good! dont know why the name is szechuan, not szechuan food at all.
Very tasty food, very friendly and attentive staff. Busy place though so good to make a reservation.
Still the best Tw quick fried restaurant IMO
Food and the service are very good.  Highly recommended for Taiwanese food
My favorite Taiwanese place! Cash only! Small place so make sure you have a reservation
Tasty and easy to share with a group.
some of the best food in vancouver! the appetizer three spice chicken is out of this world.
Food is authentic. Highly recommended for big group of people to dine in here!
Super good Taiwanese food
Old time favorite for Taiwanese style Sichuan food. Its longevity is due to good food, fair prices
One of the most authentic taiwanese restaurant. Restaurant may be small and crowded but great food.
Probably the best Taiwanese food in town! So yummy
Very unusual and at the same time great food tastes, good portion sizes, very friendly staff.
Honestly the best chinese restaurant in Vancouver by far. Friendliest staff and the most delicious food.
Have been coming here for almost 10 years, and I ve never had a bad meal. This place is busy for a reason.
Their food is very delicious. Always will come back for more.
Great foods and service. I like it that you can request for less salt, less oil, and/or without MSG in the dishes.
Been going here for over 20years, still the best Taiwanese cuisine in town!
Simply Best Taiwanese Dishes in town. Survived 20+ years with good reason.
Black pepper soup. Order in advance. Trust me... Food : 5/5
The best Taiwanese food in Vancouver! Food quality is amazing at a low price!
Great food worth very reasonable price, must visit restaurant in Vancouver.
Has been the best taiwanese food in vancouver for 20 years
A really nice restaurant with some great food and service. The kung pao chicken was a real killer!

name: ETEA cafe
address: ETEA cafe, 3281 E 22nd Ave, Vancouver, BC V5M 2Z1

detailed_reviews.review_text: I really like the overall atmosphere of the restaurant. The staff is very helpful and attentive. They have variety of food and drink options. Their prices are reasonable and great portions for most dishes. Can t wait to try more dishes from ETEA! **RECOMMENDED Dishes and Drinks: -Thai Chicken Fried Rice -Deep Fried Squid Tentacles -Popcorn Chicken -Shanghai Fried Udon -Mango Slush / Mango Paradise -Hong Kong Style Milk Tea Parking: Free Underground Parking (limited stalls). Theres free/paid street parking around the area.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thanks dustin. this is an amazing review for us. lots of nice pic too. we are glad that you had a good impression. see you around. cheers

detailed_reviews.review_text: After rebuild the whole building, the cafe looks very bright and comfortable! Same staffs and cooks :) I always come here since high school, and it has been more than 10 years already. Love their Thai chicken fried rice and rice noodle. New menu has more dishes and new drinks available. We had the mango paradise, and it came with an adorable bear shape tea cube. Ofc, the taste is 10/10. Highly recommended. Thanks again for all the delicious food and the service is always great.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: we are happy to see u again.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ordered the  build your own noodle soup  with laksa, beef, fish and ramen noodles and the flavour was really good! I would pick a different noodle next time, the ramen was a bit soft / over cooked for my liking but still good. Also ordered the baked pork chop rice. The portion was HUGE. Overall good value and fast service.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you Sim. we are glad that you like our food and service. laksa soup is the most popular soup base. looking forward to seeing you Again.   cheers

detailed_reviews.review_text: It s been many years I ve went back to Etea since they shut down as the property was being rebuilt. I was so happy to find out that the restaurant was going to come back and as soon as it opened and I passed by, I dropped by with my partner to reminisce the past. The food is just as good as before, I d say the Thai fried rice was pretty much similar to what it was before but a little bit less seasoned compared to before. It could just be a hit or miss but I d say that was a 9/10. I ve always come to Etea just to order Thai fried rice. The second order was popcorn chicken nuggets, a little saltier than expected but the seasoning was really good. The portion could be bigger for $10.80 since it was a small plate but the quality is good and technically there are other restaurants that do charge it for more expensive. The Taro slush with pearls was really good, the portion size was not as large as I thought it would be but the price for the bubble tea was standard, not as expensive as other bubble tea shops and they made it well. I found it pretty interesting that there was a bear on top (it s ice) as part of the decoration. Presentation was really good, but because the cup was smaller than usual when I ordered a size large, I would say the bear takes away the portion size. Overall I would order again and their idea of putting the bear on top overall is a creative idea. Would definitely come back again, was a regular before and will be a regular as per usual. Parking: 8 spots, pretty small and weird parking spots. A few blind spots. There is street parking which is more recommended.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thanks collin for your advice and detail review. we are happy to see you guys again. cheers

detailed_reviews.review_text: Seems newly renovated. Only tried the bubble tea and curry fish ball this time as I just stumbled across this but they were pretty good   will definitely need to come back They have free underground parking too! And usually open until 10 or 11 pm. Mango slushie  > white chewy pearls mmmm and the flavour was perfect! Atmosphere is bright and big. IG: Mishinnoms for more eats! Parking: Underground
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you Michelle. its our pleasure

detailed_reviews.review_text: Went to ETEA cafe after work, and we re so satisfy with their food!!!! We had salt and pepper chicken, deep fried squid tentacles as starters while waiting for other friends .. and I m busy eating so no pics for the entree hahha Drinks are bomb too, they have a series of drinks (NFC fruit) made with real fruits! Love it! Definitely give it a try if you re in that area!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you Marion

detailed_reviews.review_text: It was so nostalgic heading back to the restaurant that started back when I was in my highschool days.  Food tasted exactly, deliciously the same and happy to see the same faces that originally served since the beginning. They have a nice clean Interior with friendly service.  So excited for them to see they are successful and havent lost any clientele from the Renos!  They even sell cute pillows of their mascot....how could I say no to that? Parking: Free underground parking
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: time flies. its nice to see you again. thank you for giving our logo man a home.

detailed_reviews.review_text: It was not good back in 2018, right now they are all newly renovated, everything s been improved. Food n drink are pretty good. recommended !
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the 5stars review. We will keep up the good work. And looking forward to seeing you again.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Nice Tan Tan noodles!! So tasty and rich! And the pork chops is the perfect match with the noodles. Also  Mango paradise  is a must try drink there!!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Mancy. We were ask to bring back some of our hit items from the old menu. This tantan is one of them.   we are glad that you like it too.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Etea is finally back after it closed back in 2019   Since it closed I couldnt find another restaurant that makes Hot and Sour soup perfectly. When I heard they re-opened I immediately made a trip down to my fav restaurant and honestly it did not disappoint! It looks much more modern and cozy than before. The booths are more comfy! and the environment seems much brighter and welcoming than before. Hot and sour soup taste exactly as I remember! Their menu is smaller than it used to be but everything taste the same as it used to. Only downside is they no longer have parking. Overall I am so happy Etea is back
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: htnak you erica. its nice seeing you ahain. we brought back some hit items from he old menu recently. come try them and they will bring you back lotsof memory.  . our parking is now hidden underground

detailed_reviews.review_text: Brought my family in for a nice lunch at this reasonable priced (generous portion too) little gem in the east side neighborhood. We love the black sugar bubble milk tea, slushies, hainanese chicken and braked pork chop rice. Will be back soon for sure.
Excellent cuisine and service. Fair prices and adequate parking too. Love their popcorn chicken. Recommended.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you james.

detailed_reviews.review_text: This place is awesome! Super happy they finally reopened, me and my friends have been coming here since we were kids and as always the food and service was great! The staff are all extremely hardworking and I m very happy to be supporting this locally owned restaurant again.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thanks Rylee for the supprt. we will keep it up and will not disappoint you.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Yummy fried noodle and the mango drink was good . Food
Great place with good prices and huge portions. A wonderful addition to the neighborhood and you can enjoy it almost anytime. Come on down, youll be back!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you Kareem for the 5 stars review. we will see you around. cheers

detailed_reviews.review_text: Homey atmosphere, friendly and hardworking staff, good portions, and great not-too-sweet milk tea!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you and we will keep it up

detailed_reviews.review_text: Edit: My friends and I are overjoyed they are open again! The items taste the same, to our relief. This has been my bubble tea spot for two years. Always treated well, havent had any issues with mixed up orders, and the prices are amazing. I always go for the original milk tea, and some of the food items which I love are: Thai chicken fried rice, honey garlic chicken wings, beef noodle soup, and squid tentacles. Love me some E-Tea.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you so much. we are so excited seeing everyone again

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great local neighbourhood restaurant. I am glad they came back after the new development finished. Combos that comes with free bubble at an affordable price. Friendly staff. Loved their Thai Chicken Fried Rice.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you mike for visiting us again after all these years.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Me and my brother s high school memories  . The foods is a bit salty
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you for the advice. nice to see you Again.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Excellent food, excellent service. Loved the baked porkchop rice and mango paradise.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Trevor. Nice pic of the scar face
thank you Scott.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Arrived just before last call in the kitchen and they served up a delish pork ribs smothered in sauce. And for the soup combo. The soup portion was a good size. Good price for the combo
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thanks for the 5  review. look forward to serving you again.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Everything tasted exactly the same as before, very delicious! The staff are very kind and hardworking. They just reopened and are very busy so service is a little slow but cut them some slack! The food is definitely worth the wait!
Good food and good service, one of the better milk teas Ive had.

I ve been going here ever since their re-opening and so far, I d like to say that the food was been really good! I ve had the popcorn chicken on rice, the squid tentacles on rice, and the deep fried pork chop on rice (katsu rice).
I just went to et and got brown sugar milk tea. It was bitter at first, but I realized I had to stir it, and the pearls were chewy. I also enjoyed the flavour of it. I would recommend you go here.
Bubble tea was perfect new favorite spot  highly recommend!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thx kris

detailed_reviews.review_text: I came into this restaurant looking for bubble tea, I left with a full stomach and dinner for later. They have a nice selection of food and drinks, I recommend getting the ones with the stars beside them since theyre the most popular. I got the Thai chicken fried rice, price is good, portion size is HUGE and the taste is pretty good. Service was nice and fast, the ambience was good but Id say gets even better at night. All in all Id definitely recommend giving this place a try.
Love this place!! Been waiting 3 years for it to reopen. Hands down the best thai chicken fried rice ever
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you monika for still remember us.   thai chicken fried rice is still the top seller.

detailed_reviews.review_text: It is a cantonese style restaurant that basically serve many styles of food including Taiwanese foods and bubble tea. To my surprise, everything is better than average. Their stir fried dishes are very good and their bubble tea is definitely more hongkong style than Taiwanese. If you like Hong Kong style food like me, you will like it. The place is big so you dont need to wait. Size of the dish is big also very cheap. Food will be 4 stars but add on everything, becomes 5
A great place to go for  HK-style comfort food, whether its a big bowl of noodles or a large plate of fried rice. The bubble tea options are good, and very competitively priced.
Love their bubble tea! Great place to grab a quick, light, fast meal. Came with a few buddies and we all enjoyed the food in each others company.
Good spot for a late night Bubble Tea/Slush. Good service, clean restaurant.
Came here with some friends just as they were closing. They were so accommodating and quick, and everything was delicious!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you. glad that everything went well

detailed_reviews.review_text: I was very sad when this place closed I am glad it s back
We go there for their bubble tea and a few main dishes. The food is cheap and always hits the spot. They have some of the best and most consistent bubble tea in Vancouver.

My wife and I accidentally found this hidden gem.  Nice clean family owned restaurant with great food and great price...  Plus you also get a free bubble tea with your meal!  I eat here all the time now
Service is great. Their drinks are great. I always get the Dan Dan noodles with popcorn chicken, delicious and well worth the price.
Went there as soon as we heard its back in business. Same good service and food.
Very friendly servers n must try honey toast with icecream/ whip cream. Mine shaved ice red bean drink was really good also.
Nice lady
Curry beef stone pot is the best
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you for 5stars

detailed_reviews.review_text: Very tasty popcorn chicken and mango bubble tea
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you very much.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Good food ,friendly, good service
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thank you. we will keep it up.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great food at great prices. Would come back again!
finally reopened! welcome back, really busy upon reopen but thats great!!
Recently reopened in the new building!
Good food and bubble tea.
Great bubble tea place, good food and bubble tea. Really like a lot of their dishes.
spicy deep fried pork and rice is 5/5 bubble tea is also high quality
Had the spicy beef and popcorn chicken, both highly recommended!! Super tasty
Great bubble tea, great food and super affordable. Im tempted to come here all the time.
This place has great food. Good portion and awesome flavor
Great food. Large portions, afordable prices.
Delicious, a lot of food, and goo services
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: thanks

detailed_reviews.review_text: 4 words. Thai chicken fried rice
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: 4words. Thank you so much

detailed_reviews.review_text: I love this place! Best in the hood of East Vancouver!!
Taste really good, but can you clean the mens washroom please
Quick and delicious place to eat. My go to restaurant for a meal with a drink.
Awesome food at a reasonable price.  Plenty of selections
Great bubble tea, decent light meals
Happy this restaurant is back!
Best food always. Good stuff
Go to place to meet with friends. Friendly service and good food!
good drink, try hot teas sometimes.
My favorite lunch spot ! :)
Never disappoints. Always awesome.
Great food and service
Fast and friendly service.
Best chinese food
Love this place
Good food good price
Nice
Good drink!
Very nice place, highly recommended!!!

thanks for a 5   review

name: Sal y Limon
address: Sal y Limon, 1752 Commercial Dr, Vancouver, BC V5N 4A3

detailed_reviews.review_text: Their nachos and tacos were delicious and heavy! Easily had our tummies full half-way!   For the tacos, we tried their carnitas and lengua.   Their pinacolada was yummy and refreshing! Plus points for the Alebrijes art work hanging on their walls

I absolutely love this place! -food was delicious and came out quick considering that it was busy. -lovely staff, good vibes and music -their cinnamon horchata is to die for -mouth watering tacos, with fresh guacamole  (Al pastor is my favourite) I recommend this place to anyone who loves Mexican food like me.   I ll most definitely be coming back to try other things on the menu, thank you!

I went there with a friend of mine last Friday and had a really good time. I was skeptical at first, thinking it would be fast food quality, but I was surprised that the food was actually pretty good. I had four different tacos; I recommend the chicken and the fish the most (I forgot their actual names). I do not recommend the churros; they arent very tasty. The price is actually reasonable.
Their fish taco and shrimp taco is sooo amazing.  I also thought the price $3.75 for a signature taco is very reasonable and affordable. Beautiful interior as well. Love it!!
Delicious tacos! Friendly staff and the whole restaurant was very clean. Horchata was a bit too sweet for my liking; however, it does have very good flavour

New addition to The Drive, we had the burrito and chimichanga both were phenomenal. The beans and the rice had authentic Mexican flavours. You can tell they re made in house. Proportions were very generous.

I really love their tacos and that you can order them by one - so you can try many at once! I recommend to add guacamole. Delicious with guava limonade! (It is also less expensive than several other Mexican places on Commercial Dr. Like where else around here do you get churros for 4 dollars?!)

So excited to have them on Commercial Drive!  Some of the best Mexican in the city.  The tacos and burritos are great, the salsas are great, the churros are great, the decor is great, the patio is great.....you get the point. I very highly recommend this place, and will be back very, very frequently.

Love coming here. Everything is always super fresh, the avocado in their guacamole always perfect, the service is fast and kind. I always recommend this place to my family and friends. Their slush margaritas are amazing too and have an option to make them spicy.
Nice to see a second location with the same colourful and wonderful vibes, friendly staff and delicious burritos and sauces.
Sal y Limon is fantastic and Im so happy to see another location. They have great authentic Mexican food.

Tried their Tacos! Very tasty and flavoury!! I would definitely recommend Visting this place. Its clean and tidy. The food very nice b. They have great customer service. Very humble staff. Jesus was very helpful and had a very sweet attitude! Highly recommended for Mexican Food.
Foods are good and fresh. Food Portion was good enough. I am satisfied. However, i found their menu kinda confusing.
Best mexican food!!! General contractor bought everyone on the jobsite lunch.... some of the BEST Mexican food Ive had absolutely killer!!!!!!
We had the chimichangas delivered, and they were delicious! Received our order in under 30 minutes, food was hot and well packaged. Would recommend!

Wasnt sure about this place but when I saw that they had Barbacoa de Cordero (Roast Lamb) and Panela Cheese for their Burritos I had to try. The burrito was amazing and incredibly tasty! I had the spicy salsa on the side and it was incredible as well, a spicy and smoky salsa that I would gladly buy by the jar.
So glad they opened in East Van. $3 tacos washed down with horchata
Very good burritos and well served. Comes with some salsa in the side that makes burritos extra special

A group of 5 of us went to this location (commercial drive) and had a great time. The food is always excellent but most importantly one of the servers (Martin) was very attentive, polite and patient. He appeared to be enjoying delivering excellent customer service.

Ive been a loyal client since they first opened their tiny torta counter on Kingsway & Fraser. They have since then knocked down the conjoined wall, and successfully expanded into multiple locations while maintaining the same authentic Mexican recipes that made them popular. Ive introduced a few friends from Mexico to their dishes and they are confirmed with authenticity. Highly recommend the chicken asada or super veg burrito ahogado (baked with sauce)   The salsas are to die for. Mouth watering flavors. Treat yourself to the canella horchata (cold cinnamon rice milk drink) its crazy delicious and hits the spot to quench your thirst and cool your palette if youre a spice lover like me. Honestly, try everything on the menu - Ive been pleasantly surprised by each item, and eat here regularly. Love that its owned and operated by Mexicans. The art on the walls is reminiscent of the film Coco and is so soothing to look at. Vegetarian options: Super Veggie Burrito or Torta, crazy yum.
Great food and great location! Fairly priced and delicious tacos!
My boyfriend went here today and after trying the food I had to go get some for myself. Best tacos I ve ever had! Will be coming back often.

One of my go-to takeout places in East Van. The super marinara is reliably delicious and filling, although sometimes a bit spicy. You can ask for lower spice if you are sensitive. Service is always quick and pleasant.
Mexican casual dining with  great food choices and friendly staff. You can pick anything from the menu and customize it to your taste. Some wicked spicy sauces to add flavor and youre set! Food
I love this place.  Great tacos, burritos etc.  They do a great Chicken in Mole and there Sal Y Limon burrito is always very satisfying.  My new favorite taco place.
Great location, friendly staff, clean and tidy place and delicious food!
Very tasty, must try fried cauliflower
Lovely tacos, all flavors were legit
Always great food and vibes here. Quick service, fair prices, laid back and low key. Nice little patio in summertime. Vegetarian options: Tasty

Flavourful tacos for decent prices, Sal Y Limon is my go-to for takeout tacos. The setting isnt special if you want to dine-in, but perfect to take to a park or home. 3-4 tacos are a decent meal with plenty of options to choose from
The menu says 4 tacos- the last 2 times I ordered I ve gotten three tacos. Please stop this injustice! I love you guys! You re so yummy! I want the 4 tacos!!!!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: HI Alexis, can you please provide further details by email us at info@salylimon.ca? We are not clear what you are referring to as tacos are sold by unit. Thank you!

detailed_reviews.review_text: The tacos were phenomenal - try the lamb, carnitas, as beef tongue. The cinnamon horchata is definitely worth a try, especially if you re ordering spicy food. Definitely will be coming back for more! Super legit food!

My Favourite Lower Mainland Tacos! I love the sauces and Sal y Limon is not as outrageously priced as some taco places get. So happy to have this place on the drive. Theyll be taking lots of my money, Im sure! Ha ha
We had lamb, beef tongue, and fish tacos! All great choices. Tortilla soup wasn t our favourite, but I think that was just personal preference. Glad we tried it!

Fantastic addition to Commercial! I tried two varieties of their tacos - the fish and the carnitas - and they were both delicious and authentic. Great service, cool vibe, and an obvious candidate for best Mexican in the area. I will be back!
The chicken was fresh and tender.My burrito was so tasty and filling and the hot sauce was brilliant 5 alarm for my taste buds, just the way I like it. Great food and great service.

If youre really hungry grab a jimichunga it was excellent with shrimp and lovely guacamole and fresh salsa. Friends ordered various tacos and everyone enjoyed their meal. Very affordable and nice and fresh.

Welcome to The Drive! Finally able to pop by for takeout last night and love the space. Very friendly staff, not long to wait. And then walked up to McSpadden park to eat with friends and we all agreed that burritos make excellent picnic food!

So glad they have moved into the neighborhood. We have been visiting the Kingsway location for years as it is the best place for tacos in the city and now they have brought that closer to home. Everything here is just as good as the original location, expertly made and fast. My favorite is the lamb and fish tacos.
Highly recommended!!!! The tacos were amazing and the drinks are on top! Friendly staff and affordable prices! Definitely coming back when I visit Vancouver.
Friendly staff.  Casual dining, tasty food and reasonable prices.
Sal y Limon rules. Probably the best Mexican quick grab spot in Vancouver, and definitely in the neighbourhood. The burritos and tacos are good, but I think the torta is the standout of the menu.
Thoroughly enjoyed the delicious food and the kind, warm service on January 31st. Sweet oasis on a busy street.
We always love coming to Sal y Limon! The tacos are delish. My daughter loved the Pollo  , my faves are the al pastor and fish.
Super professional and friendly staff, quick order time and good food. Guac portions are a little stingy but overall awesome experience. Glad to have this place on the drive!
Super organized, clean, and fun. The staff was very friendly and, as youd expect from this reputable brand, the food is top notch. Such a welcomed addition to the drive!

Already way better than the Kingsway location, which is the OG location but has really gone downhill in quality the last two years. Got an order last night and the Torta and Burrito were stuffed with goodness.
I had their shrimp quesadilla and it was delicious. Flavourful, used a different kind of cheese which was cool!
Getting better every time I go there!
The tacos are reasonably priced (<$4 each) and are absolutely delicious!!
Awesome burrito and great service. Super fresh ingredients. Not too sure about the chipotle mayonnaise but it  somehow worked.
Great service and excellent food. I have special dietary needs and they accommodated happily. Thank you Sal y Limon, we ll be back
Chorizo burrito is one of the best in town . I never been disappointed:)
the staff are always so lovely and I love the double corn tortilla on the tacos, prevents them splitting and going all over!
Best authentic Mexican food in Vancouver. The fish taco is numero uno and the Tortas are fantastic. Love it.
Excited about the new location! Staff are very friendly, service is fast even when busy and food is just as great as their Fraser location. Love their salsas.
Burritos were super tasty but the service puts this place over the top! Thank you for sharing your joy!
Delicious as usual. Polite, good service. Loved the cards on the table to let us know if it was sanitized or not.

The wait time at the commercial location seems quite a bit shorter. The staff arent quite as efficient, but I think as the location is open longer thats sure to change. Also, parking in the back? on Commercial? Amazing!
The best burrito in Vancouver! I hope they will never change their quality. I would give 10 stars if I could.
Im super happy Sal y Limon is here on the Drive. I love the bright, bold flavours and the fresh tastes.
Excellent service & amazing food!
Their juicy burritos with ahogados sauce.
I love the vibe every time I come here! Awesome food paired with great Latino music and the colours of the paintings!
Great staff here! Had the pork belly taco and barbacoa ahogada and both were divine
Super friendly staff and really good food. I ordered the Mega Sal Y Limon Burrito and it filled me up!
Food is prepared very quick and is very tasty. A great quick spot for tacos.
Amazing experience, as a Mexican I can tell you feels like being home. Special thanks to Isabelle for her great service!
Great service from the staff all around, especially Santiago. Ordered the lengua burrito, and it was amazing!
Tacos with guac was good! I got the Al pastor and the Lengua. Lengua was really tender.
Found my new go to mexican food spot. This place was super clean and the food was delicious. 10/10
I liked the food a lot, the services of Santiago was super. What a friendly guy and his recommendation was amazing!
Great service! Very nice staff, especially Santiago! Best burritos in Vancouver
I had the huaranches for the first time. Very tasty ! Very polite and helpful staff. Super clean bathroom.
You can t go wrong with Sal.
I dont know why I havent been here before. It was delicious and the service was amazing. We will be back :)
Amazing food and the staff were so friendly. I recommend checking out this great spot
We go through life with many regrets, but rest assured that ordering from Sal y Limon will not be one of them!
Amazing place, tacos were so good, good value
Very rich nachos and excellent attention from the lady who attends a very attentive and friendly little chaparrita excellent quality of service
Fire spot great service! Wish they were open later! 9 seems a little early to close.
Great food, friendly staff and relaxed environment. Highly recommended!
Tasty, fast, solid portions, good variety of options, great value.
Extremely good food, atmosphere, and music. Feels like Im back in Mexico!
I love these tacos. So quick and yummy.
Lovely, clean, and accommodating atmosphere. Staff is super friendly   highly recommended on the
Good food and friendly staff. Nice food and great menu
Excellent service! The food it s really cool
So freakin good. Make sure you get a lime margarita.
Super fresh & tasty tacos and burritos!
Always loved Sal Y Limon, stoked to have them on the Drive!
Everything tastes very good and its very authentic
Great Mexican food, air-conditioned room, friendly staff.
The food here is always good.
The breaded shrimp taco is awesome and is a must try
Food was fantastic! Thank you Sal
Always excellent. This new location doesnt disappoint.
Love the bean tacos! And the churros, too!
It was very amazing had a lots of flavor
Good food fast service this place is great

name: Guu Davie
description: Bustling izakaya offering inventive Japanese small plates to go with sake, beer & unique cocktails.
address: Guu Davie, 1239 Davie St, Vancouver, BC V6E 1N4

detailed_reviews.review_text: Came here with some friends yesterday and was pleasantly surprised. Friendly staff fast service and great food. The beef tongue was made very well. Soft and flavourful. The oysters very fresh and the sashimi very fresh as well.  Overall great experience and would definitely come again soon.
Really good Japanese food.  A mix of sashimi, grilled food, and other Japanese dishes.  Everything we tasted was excellent, except the non-Japanese dessert was not so great.

Hands down best Sashimi in the city! Service is soo amazing. Clean and very Japanese oriented. Their sashimi is very fresh, and the cook prepares it right in front of you. The waitresses will also recommend their best dishes of the day.
Love this place! Daily menu has lots of exciting tapas dishes. Service and atmosphere are also great :)

Food was great, but what made our experience amazing was the service from our server, Eddie! Eddie went the extra mile helping us order with his own suggestions, and was very thoughtful e.g our hotpot wouldn t fit on the table so he cooked it on another table and took photos of videos of the food for us   Eddie was just absolutely amazing and would also tell us about where they sourced their ingredients (he said he picked out the oysters from Granville himself that morning) thank you so much eddie!

Great food and very nice vibe inside the restaurant. Service was very friendly and welcoming but a bit slow at times (we got forgotten a few times but nothing major). Definitely try their chicken karage and speciality drinks.

It doesnt get much better than this. Service, food quality, presentation, and interesting menu items are all things that Guu excels at. Ive now been to three of the four locations and all have been spectacular. My favorite menu items have been the various udon dishes and pork. Out of dozens of restaurants Ive eaten at in the Vancouver area who has arguably the best service.
Great place for hang out, beer, sake,moctail, and the food and staff are amazing
Nice food with nice service! Their beef tongue steak is pretty nice, worth a try Food
Went here for happy hour and was not disappointed. Great price for soju cocktail pitcher which tasted great and everything else we ordered hit too. The oysters are super cheap and taste fresh.
Great food, great staff, great selection of Sake! Its quite new, so still a hidden gem. Special menu is always great and I love going there for quick bite as well!

Excellent location and menu. Staff is friendly and accomodating. One of our dishes was missed by the kitchen but the waiter was really nice about it. The food here is bomb. Great place to go for drinks and good food.

Beautiful. Super friendly and attentive staff. Atmosphere was lovely and the food was exceptional. Shared with friends. Best gyozas weve tried. Will go again when in the area. Vegetarian options: Noticed on menu. Had roasted edamame was delicious. Dietary restrictions: With a nut allergy was aware to be careful. Parking: We parked about a block away and paid. Could probably find free off main streets but we didnt want to waste time in downtown area. Paid $2 for 2 hrs. Kid-friendliness: Didnt notice kids but could definitely bring them there. Wheelchair accessibility: On main street. Flat to get in.
We come here all the time, the staff, the food , the atmosphere is all perfect!! Get the chicken karaage best we ever had and prawns too, I could go on :) love this place so much!

Absolutely delicious food. The service was very friendly. We went for dinner on a Tuesday night around 630pm and it wasnt overly busy. The appies were yummy, especially the garlic shrimp. I loved my main dish, Miso Katsu Don.

I have tried the dinner here at this restuarant. Today, I walked by and saw that they also had a lunch time schedule. I tried the ramen salad which they had for todays special menu and Daifuku icecake after. It was nicely filling and very delicious! The tastes and looks was very unique and had Its own originality. The staffs were friendly, even the price was reasonable. Ill definitely come back again!
Another amazing Guu establishment! We arrived after 3 pm and they were accommodating to let us order the cold ramen from the lunch menu. Amazing food! Oden, karaage, and cold ramen. Staff A+++
Great raw oysters at a good price! The rest of the happy hour food was also fantastic.
Amazing Japanese restaurant on Davie. Great service and great price
Davie st location of the guu-izakaya chain, one of the few spots on Davie st with a decent south facing patio. Friendly staff and good food!

I went here for the first time during their happy hour and ordered white (sake) sangria and poutine. The sake sangria was actually so good that I kept on thinking about it after leaving the place. I personally dont like sake but this drink was very good. The poutine portion was also big and good! Definitely going back for more. The staff was also nice.
I dont know how they make the beef tongue so soft and tender, its so good that we come back for it year after year and its always consistent!
Best pork gyoza I ever had.  Very decent quality.

Last year during pride we really enjoyed sitting on the patio with some delicious food, good drinks and THE most fresh oysters I have ever had. They were so fresh the moved when we put lemon on them. Would recommend.

From the moment you are welcomed upon entry to the final goodbye, youre in for a good time. Very interesting and unique menu. Be sure to look closely at the daily sheet. Theres always amazing gems there. Youd be missing out if you dont try the Guu Poutine, which is outstanding and must be experienced.  Oysters are prepared fresh and are a treat. Theres also a great patio during the good weather. Top notch.

Very drunk writing this review. Its good, get oysters and karaage. I just found out I started this review and didnt post it but even after not being drunk I will always remember how good the food was.
Their lunch specials are inexpensive for what you get, plus the ambiance is beautiful, and the service is great. My wife & I are definitely coming back here again
Amazing food as always. Service was top notch, thanks Eddy! :) Food : 5/5

I love Izakaya food and Guu Davie absolutely nails it. The menu, service and vibe, everything is authentic. My fav is their deep fried skewers which are quite special, unique and fun - tomato, cheese, onion, egg, etc, very impressive.

Very friendly service! They offered us an extra piece of scallop sashimi (its supposed to be three but we had four people), and also recommended the order of tasting the five sorted sashimi. The waiter was attentive to the just-right extent, and very mindful to ensure that we have the right choice and the best experience with our meal. All food and drinks were excellent! The sunset beach shot was awesome, the oden was delicious, great fresh sashimi, and I like all the shared plates too, the aburi saba, wagyu tataki, tako wasabi, and salted beef tongue. You wont go wrong with anything here! Would definitely come back and recommend this place to my friends.
Great staff! Super enthusiastic and helpful. Also really patient even when we were waiting on the last person to show up!

Been here a few times now within the past year. Everything on their menu is really good. Portions are great along with the price (especially during happy hour). Staff are very attentive and friendly. Some of my favourites are their chicken karaage and the tofu and avocado salad.
They have Phoenix Darts (Soft Tip) !!

Alright, I cannot stop talking about how much I love this place. At first, it was just my husband and I there for happy hour and we fell in love with their patio, their food, and their happy hour menu. One of my favourite spot during my visit to Vancouver and we went back their with my in laws, and then friends, and then my kids, and then more friends. Chef Jeff ended up giving us some complimentary food during our last visit there. We must have went back to this place at least a good handful of times within a months period. I LOVE this spot and I HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT!
This place is so good! Shout out to Koji for making me feel welcome there
Oysters are super affordable, service is excellent, staff is clearly engaged and enjoying themselves, overall prices are very good. Would recommend to anyone, anytime.
Attentive and professional service. Great food!
Excellent atmosphere with great reasonably priced food. Tomoki made our night!
wow the food is legendary     I would recommend any hot pot and some small dishes too. Service is pretty good too.
Amazing quality seafood & salads! I ll be back!

Really cute spot with a nice patio on Davie. What can I say? Guu is always guuud :) Food from the special menu was excellent as usual. Service at Guu is always polite, attentive and quick too. Highly recommend especially for folks visiting Vancouver because Guu is truly a gem in our local restaurant scene.

Amazing food with friendly staff. Try one of their delicious cocktails or enjoy their house special of Oden, a selection of meats and or vegetables gently simmered in a light soup broth until delicious and tender. Definitely my new favourite comfort food for cold or rainy weather. You can also never go wrong with their friend chicken and a cold beer.
Delicious izakaya, friendly and professional service, and a surprisingly well-chosen local selection of wines. The rooftop patio is wheelchair accessible! My experience was really great, thank you!
Very good restaurant. The Oden are very good portions for the price. The fries are very delicious Tables are very large for larger groups. Covid restrictions were followed well by staff
Delicious food with a great selection of different flavor profiles and very friendly service.
very good place for drinking during the weekend. food is up there and goes well with booze, very spacious and surprisingly not that busy often

This place is so good. Wonderful staff and delicious, interesting food. We have gone back twice and love it more each time. Wagyu beef tataki and the baos were our faves but there is so much to choose from.

One of the best Asian meals that I had in a while. I havent left a single grain of rice! Service there is great and I received helpful advices about Vancouver. Their GuuudAle is very tasty although a bit costly. I must recommend

Had the mackerel aburi, tuna tataki, sashimi, grilled squid, a few other dishes and 18 Royal Miyagi Oysters. It was all incredible. Exceptional value, food was very good, the oysters were fresh and well shucked, and the vibe is very welcoming. Restaurant is casual, and they are open pretty late. Definitely will be back, and I recommend giving this place a shot for a great, casual Izakaya with oysters
Very affordable pricing with friendly staff and good looking one :) The ambience also very welcoming and make you feel like you want to stay there forever. An amazing hangout place with friends!

Enjoyable but not inexpensive Japanese restaurant on Davie.  Spacious, modern dining room.  Attentive and helpful service.  Delicious and hot food.  Wide selection of liquid refreshments.  Overall, a wonderful place for a nice meal.
Fantastic food and amazing service. Highly recommend. Will definitely be back when I am in Vancouver again. (Get the Yuzu gin and tonic!)

a bit more expensive than the other locations (best to go with larger groups to water down the cost) but the taste lives up (i thought the food was best out of all the locations i ve been to).  their main feature is the shabu shabu hot pot, which was fantastic and comes with multiple broth options.  i felt like the decor was still in progress. bonus: japanese style bidets!!!!
Their happy hour menu is excellent. A dollar for one oyster cant beat. They also offer very reasonable launch box options.

The experience was amazing, food was impeccable and staff were really sweet and accommodating.  favourite dishes so far have been the seafood shabu shabu and the stone bowls from the izakaya menu. favourite drink has to be the ume sour.
Great food and customer service. Will be coming back.
Great japanese isakaya food, very authentic. Just give it a try.

Excellent shabu-shabu - highly recommend the spicy miso.  All the dishes were great - make sure you save room for the mochi covered matcha ice cream with strawberry sauce.   A laid back izakaya experience worth a visit, especially towards the end of the day.  Solid cocktail offerings and a house beer brewed by Stanley Park brewing.
Every Guu is so unique with its own way, I am so happy we have Guu in our neighbourhood. The price is reasonable and the service is great. Will go back again to try different dishes on the menu.
Very, very good place. Chicken karaage, shio cabbage and gyoza are amazing. Anything I tried from the special menu has been great. I highly recommend this place to anyone who likes good food.
Wish I took pictures of our meals but it was so good I forgot! Awesome staff, amazing hot food, great drinks   Im going to come back with different friends who Id know would love this place!
Food was good. Service was great. Buck a shuck
We were treated like family. Amazing food and drinks. Wow!!
Guu has a fantastic atmosphere, the food is incredibly good! Super recommend!
Very warm and friendly staff, good atmosphere and delicious and authentic food. This was a highlight during my stay in Vancouver.
Nice place, love their seating. Not very crowded, though weve always been there late nights. Great food and great price.
Food and drinks were great. Staff were very friendly and helpful. Guuu on Davie is one of my favorite places.
Service is nice, food quality vs. price is very good and I like the bartender s outfit. Pack your food togo and they will give you a nice Guu bag.

detailed_reviews.review_text: They serve very reasonable noodle. If you dont mind to spend time to look for a parking, highly recommend!

Got some dim sum via delivery on DoorDash as a sort of late Lunar New Year treat for me and my boo.  The delivery time expected was the fastest offered when I used dim sum as a search term-and they did NOT disappoint! For those of you who would like to read further, I shall elaborate.  The packaging was thoughtfully done with sturdy circular cardboard containers-not the kind I can keep as tupperware but eminently recyclable.  The sauces were kept in cute lil plastic containers inside the containers of their respective dishes-as a result of this thoughtful packaging, all foods and sauces arrived with only a few drops of spillage. We ordered a combination of hot dim sum and cold Hong Kong style iced tea as well as some frozen dumplings for later.  They were kept in appropriately separated paper bags, keeping the hot stuff hot (but not burningly so), and the cold stuff cold.  A solid A well deserved on the delivery front.  Now to taste. The frozen potstickers I ordered I sadly cannot include in this review as I have not eaten them. The Hong Kong style tea was very strong, but not very sweet.  I have a bit of a sweet tooth so I didn t love it myself but if you prefer watching your sugar intake I think you ll definitely like it. The dim sum selection wasn t huge but the items were excellent!  I had red bean sesame balls, black sesame buns, steamed shrimp dumplings, char siu (pork dumplings with a single wonton wrapping), deep fried pork buns, and popcorn chicken. I ll list them in order: Red Bean Sesame Balls: Fantastic.  I had them elsewhere and found them quite greasy.  Here they weren t, but still had their wonderful earthy character. Black Sesame Buns: My boo especially liked these due to their softness.  For me the black sesame filling was quite competently done.   Nuff said! Shrimp Dumplings: Exactly what you would expect in this town-nice, moist and warm.  Went with the mild soy sauce quite nicely. Char Siu: Wonderfully juicy.  The mild soy sauce that dripped on them slightly played off the pork brilliantly too. Deep Fried Pork Buns:  What is rich and salty for me is quite beloved by my boo, and these treats were no exception.  I let him have the majority. Popcorn Chicken:  The lone disappointment-though well seasoned, the popcorn bits were very often small enough in this dish that they could not contain chicken.  The pieces that did have chicken though were quite tasty and went quite well with a sweet ish sauce we mixed up ourselves. Overall, this delivery was extremely well done and I very much look forward to the day that I can visit this Hon s branch in person.
