name: Kowloon Inn
address: Kowloon Inn, 5625 3rd Ave, Ferndale, WA 98248, United States

detailed_reviews.review_text: I love their food!  Most people, including myself, get take-out from here.  The food is still hot when I get home.  I love the sweet & sour pork & my husband loves the almond chicken.  The people who own it are really nice & work very hard.  As with many places, they are short staffed, but dont let that stop you!  Its so good!
Wonderful place! Great quality food, very fresh every time. I highly recommend checking this place out! The general tsos and low mein are my favorite

We were hungry and ordered a #9 to go. Fabulous soup,prawns,  almond chicken and fried rice. Every bit was exquisite. Ironically we live 5 minutes away walking. We will be dining here often. The inside looks amazing. Old school Chinese restaurant much like Seattle. Loved it.

We came in an hour before close and were greeted cheerfully. We had a fairly large to-go order and the woman working was friendly and efficient. It turned out to be some of the best Asian-American food I ve ever had, and it was around $13 for a huge 3-item combo. We will be back and often!

Great place for the whole family. Or just the two of you. Never had a bad meal here. Everything on the menu is GREAT. If you have hesitation on ordering? Dont. The service is excellent. Fast and polite. Highly Recommend.

Ive been coming here since the early 90s and Ive always loved their food. Their service is always friendly and accurate, their spring rolls are magical, and their vegetable lo mein is amazing. Cannot say enough good things about this restaurant, if they ever close Ill need therapy.
Great little place!  Food is awesome
Food was delicious and reasonably priced, they like most places are low on staff so plan on having a bit more patience with them as they navigate these tough times.

Ordered Mongolian Beef. Waitress asked me if I WANTED IT SPICY I CHOSE MEDIUM. It was so flavorful and just the right amount of spice. And I lived the positive words for my life ...from the fortune cookie!
Great food, lovely people. My new go-to.
Small restaurant with great Chinese food
This place is amazing. The almond chicken and egg drop soup are the best
Fantastic food, lots of options. Nice sized portions. All tastes very fresh. Will definitely be back.
I cannot say enough about this place. Best Chinese ever! Great staff. Large portions and very tasty. Eat here often!
Thursday lunch buffet is the best!  Great service and something on the menu for everyone - Golden Fried Rice and Sesame Chicken are my personal favorites.
70s Chinese-American chic.  Very good food.  Great service.  Worth your time and dollars.
Every time I come the service is excellent and the food is wonderful too. Hot, flavorful, and fresh.
A family owned Cantonese restaurant. In my opinion, one of the top three restaurants in Ferndale along with Lux Thai and Mazatlan. The food is very satisfying :)
I really love this place. Excellent Chinese in Ferndale.  Good service if you re sitting there and fast preparation when you call an order in.
Great Food!  The lunch buffet, only offered on Thursdays, is fresh, tasty and very reasonably priced...
Seriously, the best hot and sour soup in all of whatcom county! Love this place <3 Benn going for years
We enjoyed our meal very much!  Great food and good service!
My favorite place to eat chinese food.  I love the server, she is so nice and friendly every single time.  <3

LOVE THEIR FOOD SO MUCH, but dont go there when they are busy, very slow service - order and pick up instead!
Love this restaurant and its owners. The food is always good and the service is top notch.
been going here since I was a kid. Love their food and have always had great service!
Food and staff are excellent! One of our favorite places to eat! :-)
Great place for Oriental Food! Great food, friendly Service, Highly Recommended!
The food had so much flavor!  Great service.

Always good quality and  flavorful dishes.  Have been visiting Kowloon for over 13 years!

Great sweet n sour. Havent had anything I dont like.

Extra spicy should be much spicier but I understand not wanting to make a customer angry by making it too spicy. Otherwise it was pretty good, not as good as I remember though, the recipe seems to be a bit different
Excellent service, plenty of menu options to choose from. Seats are a little worn (patched with tape) but very clean. No alcohol served here. Hot tea served with meals.
Its nice quiet, neatly decorated, with simple and polite servers. I had honey chicken and chow main noodles(soft kind). It tasted very good. Try out this place

Food is amazing, but the servers spend most of the time in the back not really paying attention to customers. I personally am fine with the inattentive staff because the food is so delicious. After eating at kowloons I cannot eat at any other Chinese food places anymore because their food is so nasty to me now.

Good consistent quality Chinese cuisine local in Ferndale. Have eaten here a number of times over the years and cant say Ive ever had a bad experience. If youre looking for a decent Chinese restaurant that is local in Ferndale, I would recommend it.
Still an old familiar favorite. Great American style Chinese cuisine for a decent price.

name: Guu Toramasa
address: Guu Toramasa, 757 Seymour St, Vancouver, BC V6B 5J3

detailed_reviews.review_text: We tried this newest Guu location for dinner and lunch recently. After the first visit we felt it was okay comparing to our favorite Guu Thurlow. However we came back a few more times within a month (unplanned) for the reason that its more spacious and easier to get a table for bigger group. After a few more visits this Toramasa location started to grow on me. The service from the friendly staff and food are consistently good just like their other locations. Our favorite here is still the same signature dishes like yaki udon, kimchi fried rice, pumpkin coquette, chicken karaage, and grilled fish  . My only suggestion is please add more Japanese decor because right now the inside feels a little too modern. Other than that, I would say this place is good for bigger group! If just small group like 2 people I personally prefer Thurlow location.
Been there for lunch & dinner, definitely recommend to try their dinner menu more than lunch selection. Very nice atmosphere with great staffs!

Different from the other Guu locations and initially thought we wouldn t like it but when we got to try the food it surprisingly good. What we ordered was basic but it was still a good lunch although a bit pricy but inflation everywhere.

Right across from TELUS in nearby the bed so good for tourist and local so like for a real authentic Japanese experience with young energetics staff and cooks with defined dishes, including appetizers, entrees and dessert. Wow the cheesecake U2 with green tea is just amazing so go check it out and be a regular to experience this wonderful neighbourhood place that s better than their other locations photo three

Ordered the yellowtail sashimi,  pan fried upon, squid, and fried chicken. Everything was great.  Good portions and dishes came out fresh.  A little wait for the food but worth it.  Would definitely go back.
Great place to have decent Japanese food and all Japanese Service. Ticking all the boxes (except the bento one ;-) ).
We threw a surprise birthday party and the staff were great and so accommodating. We brought in a cake and they sang happy birthday as well. The food was also delicious.

Tasty dishes, comfortable atmosphere, very friendly and attentive staff. We went in almost closing time, but I would like to go again at earlier time to enjoy more of their dishes!! This is must go place!!
Way too busy but if you can stand to wait for everything and I mean really wait, the food is incredible. Fresh sashimi and flavorful dishes. Ill be back. Compliments to the chef.
Love the new location! Came here for my dad s birthday and the food and service was excellent, just as we ve experienced at their other spots
So awesome! Beautiful simmered mackerel!!! Amazing, friendly, and helpful service! I highly recommend it here!
Excellent new Guu!! Amazing service and food as usual and I like the location! Definitely a great experience thanks
10/10 food and energy in the room   the sparkling white wine yuzu sangria is amazing !
Another great hh place
Amazing service, great food and the matcha ice cream is so tasty
Similar menu as the other Guu s, and you ll probably find this location a little more spacious.
Another fantastic addition to the Guu family! Looking forward to coming back again. Hana who reviewed below sounds crazy.
excellent service and foods!!
Very good experience overall.

This is a branch opened by the core members of Guu Original after moving to it. The food is still delicious, the price is affordable, its more spacious, clean, and pleasant than the main store, and its nice that the main store sells daily specials as regular menus. Hormon, eel omelet, and carbo udon are recommended.
Japanese izakaya feel The staff are friendly and the food is delicious Recommended beef tataki!
its delicious. The atmosphere is nice, clean and stylish. The temperature is also appropriate.
A newly opened restaurant with a clean and pleasant atmosphere. The young female server was very friendly.

A slightly different concept than what I m used to and really wanted to give it a try. I m glad I did, there were some interesting flavor combinations and the dishes well cooked and well presented. The staff were really polite and the overall atmosphere good.

Similar to other Guu locations, with some interesting daily specials. Id suggest going with at least a couple people to be able to try more of the tapas style dishes. Would definitely recommend getting the Oden - it was light but flavourful and a nice contrast to some of their other heavier dishes.

Typical Guu menu with daily specials. Food quality was good and prices are fair considering todays inflation. We ordered 7 dishes for 3 people and the bill was under $30 each. We didnt order any drinks though. Atmosphere was loud loud as we were sitting in the middle of the restaurant. Overall, it was a good experience at a convenient location.

For those acquainted with the Guus four other locations in Downtown Vancouver, Guu Toramasa brings the familiar izakaya style experience with a focus on Osaka specialty dishes. One of their must try is the Takoyaki. Instead of serving it as is, each takoyaki comes with crackers in which you sandwich it to create a wonderful combination of both soft and crunchy. The rotating daily specials is what keeps every Guu location exciting and I highly recommend looking at it first and then choosing from their regular menu. Service at this location was also great as all staff are friendly and attentive leading to a positive experience.

New guu location on Robson and Seymour! Guu toramasa offers the typical guu izakaya concept and dishes, but introduces Osaka street food as well. I made a reservation on open table and we were seated promptly. Ordered a few dishes to share between two people. My favorite was the smashing takoyaki with the prawn crackers ($7.80). Flavourful and fun to eat. The yaki udon ($15.50) was great with beef, mushroom, green onion and bonito flakes as well. The ikamaru ($13) had amazing umami flavor. Loved the grilled whole squid with garlic mayo. The most disappointing was the ebi mayo ($14.80)- they were not what we expected. The prawns were so small and not worth it. We were expecting the bigger ones at the other guu locations. I really enjoyed the lychee beer ($7) and service was nice and prompt.
Good oden soup. Ive been to other Guu locations, and every one of them is great! This place is one of them- never fails! Great place!

Very different feel from the other Guu locations, but still great izakaya. 3 appetizers for $15 is a good deal, though portions are (understandably) small. Felt like there could have been some more substantial options. Also, the okonomiyaki was a bit dry.

We love the Guu restaurants across downtown and were super excited about a new one opening here. As always, the food was amazing but services was extremely slow. It did take an hour to even get a server to ask us what we wanted to drink. I m sure it s been a busy time opening recently, so we will give it another shot later.
Great spot for lunch. Only thing is that menu is too limited and cant add snacks or appes to my meal. Still very good!

The food was great, as usual, and the servers were excellent. However, the waiting time was too long it took 40 minutes to have our food on the table after we ordered. I noticed many experienced staff members who seemed to be working from other locations. There were enough servers, and they were professional, so perhaps the issue lies with the kitchen being slow or not adequately sized to handle the demand at this location. I will go back to my preferred location, which is Davie.

Service was great at this location, all the floor staff were kind, happy, and very attentive to the guests. The sashimi was great quality and plated nicely. However, the pork belly tasted like it had been sitting in an insert in the back of the fridge for several days, waiting for someone to order it. The marinated enoki mushrooms on my raw tuna was slimy and also looked like it was prepped days ahead of time.
Food was OK. Monkfish liver was strangely fishy. Staff/service were amazing.

Im sure guu has pretty high standards to their food but my experience, specifically this one, at lunch hour is very poor. Ordered a chirashi Don and that was it. The presentation  is quite fancy as it was served on a plate(instead of a bowl, where you would expect of from a don (rice bowl) item). The sashimi were all chopped up.. there were scallop, tuna, bbq eel, salmon, seaweed, the usual.. pickled radish was also in the mix which adds a nice touch. Food was generally okay, service was prompt and friendly.. I just have 2 problems: The first problem was that they seem to be trying to be fancy just for the sake of being fancy. The chirashi don had BBQ EEL in it, this is definitely atypical and I think theres reasons for it.. what are you supposed to do then, if you were to add soy sauce in for the sashimi, it would ruin the bbq eel, if you dont add soy sauce, then the sashimi is kinda tasteless (and why serve soy sauce if that was the intend? Also, everything came chopped up so its hard to pick out specific fish (in this case the bbq eel) and eat them separately.. not to mention that eating a rice dish on a plate is just clumsy (and Im Chinese).. the food is great, just not very practical. The second, and bigger problem for me is the portion. Im pretty sure a grown man can eat at least two, or even of three of these. And that even petite women could find this portion unsatisfying. I understand that guu is an izakaya place and therefore their dish is sized accordingly. But not a lot of people is going to enjoy izakaya during lunch hour. I would much rather they price it higher and just give double the portion.

Theres plenty of Guu restaurants to choose from but this is probably not one of them. Usual warm welcome when you enter through the door but I wouldnt expect much more than that for service. They didnt complete my order and the servers dont check up on you. Food is the usual fare they would serve. I would recommend the other locations over this one.

Some food was still frozen and not thawed well, we had to wait a lot for dishes to arrive at the table, they forgot to bring some dishes so my friends almost didnt eat anything. Taste wasnt good, one of the worst izakaya in town. Im sorry!

I had dinner with 10 friends before going nightclub yesterday. Even though we made seperate 10 orders, we had to split bill equally by 10 ppl. I felt so angry, awkward at this restaurant and never go back again. My boyfriend and I just order Beef tendon Yokisoba $18 and three kinds of Appertizer $15 so that means our bill was $33 + tax for both of us. Unlucky, we must paid $25.35 for each person. It was unbelievable & unexpected. BAD SERVICES EVER .

The food was very good. But the service has more space to improve. They didn t take our order properly, I had a small flies in my drink, and they charged us wrong. We could hear what they are talking about customers. I think staff assumed that we don t understand Japanese, but we did. Compare to other Guu restaurants, this place need better trainings. It was not a comfortable place to go. I won t come here again.

WARNING: Went here on Saturday, July 1 in the evening. We ordered the takoyaki, chicken karaage and kimchi fried rice. About 10 hours later my partner and I had severe food poisoning symptoms (fever, chills, vomiting, diarrhea) that lasted for more than a day.

name: Sol Lee's Korean Restaurant
address: Sol Lee's Korean Restaurant, 329 North Rd Unit 550, Coquitlam, BC V3K 3V8

detailed_reviews.review_text: He had the seafood hot pot here, and I really enjoyed it. It had cod eggs in it which my mom used to eat as a child and they were really interesting texture wise. I like the button that lets you call your server when you need them, they were always fast and helpful, and the side dishes were really pleasant too.

Great little Korean restaurant. Standard Korean dishes and friendly staff. Love their Mul Naengmyon and seafood pancake. The pancake is one of the best. Crispy and not too much batter/dough. Its busy on weekends for dinner.

I highly recommend you to make a reservation because it can get real busy in there, especially on the weekends. Its such a welcoming restaurant as it seems like its family owned? The food quality was so homey and I enjoyed everything we got. We asked the server who recommended us a lot of good dishes. We got the pork bone soup, sashimi bibimbap, and seafood pancake. They were all very delicious and not overly oily or salty. We were lucky to get a reservation on the day of and was seated right away. The restaurant is in a huge parking lot, so parking wasnt hard. Prices were very decent compared to Richmond or Vancouver!
Amazing food, great place to hang out on a night out. They also have private dining space.
One of my fav Korean restaurants in Metro Vancouver Dont forget to try Beakseju(Korean drink) Recommended menu : grilled fish and aguzzim

One of the Korean restaurants in Lougheed mall area. We tried cold noodle dish, codfish soup, and deep fried fish, everything was fresh and delicious. We enjoyed even the complimentary side dishes. The staff were warm and inviting. We will go back to try other items for sure. They don t accept same day reservations though since they seem to have lineups usually. I will book a table in advance next time.
We finished almost everything and forgot to take pictures until the last dish pork cutlet.  They are too tasty. We ordered soft tofu seafood soup, seafood pancake, spicy pork rice and cold noodle.

A very homey type of Korean restaurant specializing in more traditional Korean cuisine. We ordered the pork back bone hot pot, shrimp tempura, pancake and bibimbap. The pork bone hot pot was super flavourful and came with a lot of pork pieces! It could ve used some more cabbage but otherwise a great dish with a complex soup base. The shrimp tempura batter was very light and crispy. The pancake was filled with lots of chives and tasted clean and not oily. I believe this restaurant excels at a  steamed seafood with bean spouts  dish as every table seemed to have ordered it. The service was prompt and efficient and restaurant was very clean.  Will come back to try the steamed seafood with bean spouts lol

I don t usually review Korean food unless it is really bad because I have a quite high standard. I didn t even take any pictures in the beginning. But I have decided to do a review. And I took a picture while eating lol. Ordered 2 - Spicy Fish roe soup(  ) and hot stone bowl bibimbap(     ) Spicy Fish roe soup(  ) - was SO good. No unpleasant smell fish usually have. Tasted like crab/seafood based soup. (       - clean,deep,spicy) Plenty of fish roe in it!! It comes with rice in the hot stone bowl. Hot stone bowl bibimbap(     ) - was a little bland but you could add red spicy sauce(   ). It comes with miso soup. I heard that    ,   ,      are great. I am not a big fan of Korean restaurants in Vancouver but I would definitely try out other food here as well. - Update on April10th,2022 Had codfish soup & SoonTofu soup. Codfish soup : Same great quality as spicy fish roe or even better. Clean, deep, spicy taste. Would definitely come back for this again. Soon Tofu : First taste was good. But it tastes like Korean Ramen soup. It is still better than typical soon tofu soup from other places. But I would choose other dish next time. Overall : They make quality soups. Would definitely recommend.
Love the cod fish soup! The cod fish is so fresh. 3 big chunks of cod. But not recommended for those who don t like fish bones. I was fine because I am professional
One of the best Korean restaurants in town. I love their Cabbage Kimchi and Daegutang a lot. Especially Daegutang is super legit. I will definitely go here again.

First time ordering from this rest and it s a take out. I wasn t too sure how a hot pot would transplants into take out version but wanted to give it a try. It sure did not disappoint! The meat are so flavourful and size is generous. Will be sure to come back!

Food is excellent Good service at a slow pace. If you are a fast paced person, do not recommend it. If somehow, like me today one of the guests cant eat spicy food for a certain reason. makes sure the order is not spicy. Because the menu doesnt label it. As you order, make sure you ask, no assuming. FYI, the hot pot we order is octopus and pork hotpot.
Everyone enjoyed the ahgujjim. Very large portion with reasonable pricing point. I enjoyed the choouhtang very much. Im so happy I can have it in Canada!
One of my favorite Korean restaurants! Whenever I visit, I cant resist ordering the grilled mackerel fish, bibimbap, and the beef ribs. These dishes never disappoint!

Very friendly, the food is amazing, theyre so relaxed and chilled and accommodating tactful and thoughtful. Portions are big restaurant is clean and servers are responsive and would highly recommend this place to others especially bigger groups of people.
Recommend seafood tofu soup! It d be better if the soup could contain shrimp inside. Overall good!

Their kimchi is fxking good, I had experience of making fresh kimchi so I can 80% sure they freshly make it overnight. We ordered their Loach in hot bean soup however a little bit dissapoint it was minced in soup. But that was not their fault we didnt ask properly. Such precious place shouldnt dismiss by others who visit this town for food. Very recommend visit this store for the atmosphere and Korean Dish !!
Taste delicious, reasonable price, and friendly staff = no reason not to give 5 stars. We had 1 cold noodle with yulmu kimchi + 1 LA galbi = total 42.95 + tip
The fried fish is delicious and the price is good as well! The place is not very big but always busy, so I would recommend making a reservation on the weekends.
Not my favourite, but my parents favourite. Maybe too authentic for non-koreans.
This is one if my favorite place .. The agu-jjim made with steamed monkfish is the best one
Authentic Korean cuisine at reasonable prices. We ve been here three times and are satisfied each time we dined here. Services are good too, friendly staff.
My go-to Korean place. The deep fried fish is a must get.

A great place to enjoy k-foods with affordable prices. No tough ingredients, asking spicy level by dul-map-gae.. it has decent interior. so do not expect to be treated as a king with your partner. tables and asiles are tight. wheelchair could be a challenge. parking good outside..... Parking: it is inside the mall. enough parking space except 1500-1800. Wheelchair accessibility: not good. its a challenge
Excelente food and customer service 100%. Recommended the pork backbone stew.
The agujjim is delicious and huge
Came here for the first time. Love the seafood dishes and the tofu soup is great too. Portion is very friendly considering the price. Will visit again!
Everything was super tasty.  We saw someone with the deep fried halibut and follow suit.  Best decision ever.

Located in corner of a strip mall in Hanin Village at Burnaby/Coquitlam. Never been disappointed with their foods! It is unfortunate that they have replaced some of my favourite dish, but we still visit them every time we visit Vancouver. Most recently, we had Ah-goo jjim (steamed monkfish). I have never been a fan of this dish, but it was absolutely perfect!! Highly recommend it and its best to have fried rice with it. It is bit more expensive, but wont regret it :) Kids had their non-spicy dishes which were top class.

Went there with my gf and her dad about 2 weeks ago because they wanted seafood. I am not a fan of seafood but they did have Bibimbap and it was delicious! one of the best I tried by far, ingredients were fresh, bowl was on fire so when I mixed the rice, egg, beef and vegetables everything just cooked so well. I cant say for the seafood but if you are there, give the Bibimbap a chance cause Im a picky eater and this dish was worthy enough of a review.

Incredible value! The deep fried halibut (entire fish) was around 1.5 lbs, and cost only $17 before tax. And apparently, our fish was below their standard weight and they gave us another halibut tail! The meat we got was probably 3 times the amount of a one piece fish and chips, yet the same price. And their fish/tofu soup is very good, and though priced slightly higher at $16-$17, the portion is also much bigger. My wife and I got the halibut fish and a fish soup, and we could barely eat all of it because of the large portion.  One minor critique is the soup has some MSG. Will come back and try their other items.
My friend and I went for dinner here. We ordered Gamjatang one each. Very friendly staff and good portion of food. Meat was tender and tasty. Enjoy the supper here.
I am so glad to know here. I will visit again when I want to eat korean style seafood menus.
Winter in Vancouver is wet and cold. Rice in a hot stone pot comes with  lunch menu is perfect for this weather. Have dup bab, ka ga mi ku i, al tang, dae ku tang is tasty. Food
Bad staff but good food? I dont think its possible to rate the place any lower in terms of food.

Ordered from SkipTheDishes, food was absolutely fantastic it tasted delicious, a little bit spicier than I expected but it was so good, I was crying from the spices and loving it at the same time. Definitely going to be my go to restaurant for orders for the future. :) EDIT: A year or so later this is definitely my go to restaurant for my Weekend Netflix & Wine nights. I only order the Stir Fried Beef with mixed vegetables and rice because it is just so damn good especially with red wine!!!
Great authentic Korean food. Always very busy so  be sure to reserve a spot or arrive early. Food tastes good and comes in good portions. Service is snappy and the ring bell also helps.

They serve common Korean food such as BulGoGi, spicy pork, spicy tofu pot(Soon Tofu JiGae), etc. However, there are some authentic options such as deepfried whole fish, spicy fish with bean sprout like more pan fried and steamed style. Some dishes might not be served like at other Korean restaurants but more authentic.

Fish egg soup(Al Tang), and Deep Fried Halibut are must-try. If you go for lunch, it comes with stone pot rice! Make sure to scoop the rice into the given separate bowl(hot!) and pour water(one cup?) into the stone pot, and cover up again. Once you finish your meal, enjoy your congee (Nu Reung Ji)

If I tell you I have driven 10 hours from Calgary to Coquitlam just to have dinner in this fantastic and unbelievable restaurant you might wont believe it. The service and food is awesome I really appreciate it  . Rcommending to whom ever wanted a  tasty and delicious Korean food to try.
Best Korean style seafood restaurant in the town!
Authentic Korean food. recommended
Unexpectedly busy place for a weekday lunch, but had excellent food. Tofu soup is delicious.
Must try Alzzim and Agutang. Always satisfying visiting.
1st time, fresh and delicious food made my day. And also good price.
Best Korean food Ive had so far in Coquitlam
Delicious food and quick service. Had seafood tofu soup and bibimbap
All dishes is so delicious
Friendly and speedy service. Food was delicious and fresh. Fried halibut was da bomb!! Thank you
steamed monkfish with bean sprout is my favorite! And also fried flatfish is awesome
I love this place.  Very generous portions. Great food, staffs are amazing.
Significantly improved menu since change of ownership. Their kimchi is probably the best in the city.
Food is so so delicious!!! Pork cutlet is both sweet and savoury! Staff are so nice too
Tried moolhoi naengmyun(    ) So delicious for hot summer Price Food
The deep fried cod was tasty and the spare ribs were really good
Good service, It was very friendly. The deep fried halibut was so good!!

I loved everything about this restaurant. Definitely come back again!
Way better than my expectation! Especially seafood menus!
Great Korean fair. Very authentic Korean seafood dishes.
Big portions, tastes great and excellent service!

Food was excellent and the service was wonderful.
food was so delicious. Parking: they are located at big Korean town mall so I could use lots of parking spaces to park my car.

Im pregnant so I cant eat well... I run a pizza shop and am exposed to food smells all day long, so I cant eat Korean pizza right now, even though its delicious... Sols food that nourishes me and satisfies my appetite~~ Its close to my house, so I stop by once or twice a week on my way from the store. Even if I go alone, there are so many things I want to eat^^ Because I couldn t eat all day~ I like spicy and light taste ^^ Agujjim~ I ordered a generous portion of nutritious fried flounder and hot stew menu, savored it little by little, took it out, and enjoyed it.^^ Ah~ The steamed monkfish and fried rice packaging are a must-have~ Be sure to get it~ Parking: Ample parking space in Korean Village! Kid-friendliness: The partitions are well made. Its perfect for families or those who want to enjoy quietly.

This restaurant is truly delicious. I ate grilled flounder and packed some steamed monkfish. Since stone pot rice is provided, the taste of eating Sungnyung is amazing and the portion is generous. My child said the grilled flounder was really delicious. Im full, but I keep reaching for the monkfish stew. Delicious and spicy without causing stomach upset~ Im going to try gamjatang sometime soon.

This is my third visit, and I have tried steamed monkfish twice, but today I had steamed seafood. The seafood was perfect for two people to eat. Neither much nor little. I really liked the large shrimp included. The seasoning is a bit strong, but I think its great in Canada. The kids really enjoyed the fried flounder.
Why did I only discover this restaurant now? I enjoyed the loach stew, fried flounder, and radish cold noodles so much!! I will definitely come back to eat monkfish stew! Service is ordinary~
Gamjatang is spicy and has a lot of meat, so its delicious. Thank you for being so kind to the female staff who serve you.
Its far from where I live, so I come here occasionally, but the food is fresh and clean. Gamjatang is so delicious. Its the best Ive had in Vancouver
Agujjim is delicious! Huge portion! I only eat monkfish stew every day, but today I ate bulnak stew and it was so delicious

Visited during a trip to Vancouver. My family of three went and ordered and ate flounder, codfish soup, and pork rice bowl. If you go before 3 oclock, you can eat stone pot rice, but we ate it with stone pot rice. I couldnt take a picture because I was eating, but the flounder was very delicious and the quantity was huge. Daegu tang was very cold and delicious. It was nice to eat Jeyuk-deopbap with rice and meat on top of a stone-cooked stone pot. Three side dishes, including kimchi, were served, and I wanted the portion to be small at first, but the staff brought it to me and told me to tell you more if it was not enough, so I ate it and refilled it once more. The main portion was large, so I didnt order more side dishes, but it was really delicious. The side dishes and main dishes are really delicious, so I want to visit again next time I come to Vancouver. This is a restaurant that you can recommend to your friends. If you visit before 3pm, you can eat rice in a stone pot, so it would be nice to refer to it. Gajami tempura is highly recommended.

This is the best brush that I cant help but write a review about!!! Steamed seafood = bean sprouts < seafood Bibimbap = Rice < < < Namul The seafood and green onion pancake also has a lot of seafood compared to other places! The kindness of the servers Thank you for making a happy meal :))
It was a bit spicy, but it was delicious Ill have to try the roe stew next time
So delicious agujjim :)

This is my go-to restaurant every time I go to Vancouver. All of our kids eat really well too! They are kind and have a lot of food. Steamed agu, grilled flounder, cod soup, and altang are all delicious! Ill go again next time I go to Vancouver~

Its really delicious. Not to mention steamed agu, grilled flounder and especially gamjatang are great. The quantity is really good. I hope it doesnt change. Go here again. Go two or three times and eat =) This place is much better than Tangmaru, which specializes in Gamjatang.

The reviews were good, so 4 people went and ate a large steamed agu dish. The side dishes were also good and tasty. Im really very satisfied!!! Even if the price of food rises later, the price of food should not be saved by saving ingredients to make the food taste different. Dont change and always make it delicious ^^
When I come home to my daughters house, the food I always eat is Sols food. My daughter really likes the restaurant. It s delicious and the quantity is huge~
Sols Dolsot Bibimbap Daegutang is so delicious. I recommend it.

My family likes agujjim very much, so there are times when I really want to eat it. I ate at Seafood 1st Street a few times, but the seasoning was good, but I was always disappointed that the bean sprouts, which account for most of Agu-jjim, were overcooked, so the water was drained instead of crispy, and the texture was thin and tough. Sols Agujjim was rumored to be good, so I ordered it after seeing a review, but the rumor is really true. The crunchy texture of bean sprouts is the same and the seasoning is delicious. However, there was too much red pepper powder and it was very spicy. Next time Ill have to order a little less spicy. Its a strong point.
it is delicious
